{"id": "2855", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2855", "title": "Dried Finger", "text": "The Dried Finger is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Dried Finger is found in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;. Drop down onto the balcony, from first left turret when facing the castle from the &lt;a href=\"bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Dried Finger can only be picked up once, the player won't be able to pick it up in the next playthroughs again. However, it can't be dropped and won't disappear in a &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20Remastered\"&gt;Dark Souls Remastered&lt;/a&gt;\", the dried finger is now sold by the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Male%20Merchant\"&gt;Undead Male Merchant&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt;, and the item from its former location is now a &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Humanities\"&gt;Twin Humanities&lt;/a&gt;. He will also drop it upon death.\nGeneral information.\nIn \"Dark Souls\", there is a special &lt;a href=\"invasion\"&gt;invasion&lt;/a&gt; timer that starts to count down every time you complete a fight where someone invaded your world, whether you win it or lose it. It is set to around 10 minutes, and no one can invade your world until it has depleted. Once picked up, the Dried Finger can be used unlimited times to reset the invasion timer to zero, allowing the player to get invaded more often.\nThe Dried Finger is a highly valuable PvP item, as it allows the player to get invaded much more often in several places where people often invade. These places are for example generally everywhere in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, Darkroot Garden or the &lt;a href=\"Kiln%20of%20the%20First%20Flame\"&gt;Kiln of the First Flame&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "130289", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130289", "title": "Dried Finger (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Dried Finger is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; for 2,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nIncreases the number of maximum guest players in a &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt;' world from 3 to 5. Host will go from a maximum of two summons and one invader for a total of four players, to three summons and two invaders for a total of six players. In territory defender areas (&lt;a href=\"Crucifixion%20Woods\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt;), the numbers are increased from one phantom and two invaders, to two phantoms and three invaders.\nUsing the Dried Finger will also move the host's world to the top of the invasion priority queue and reset the cooldown timer for being invaded, while also decreasing the minimum interval for subsequent invasions. As well, whenever a host-allied phantom enters the world (whether by being summoned via &lt;a href=\"White%20Sign%20Soapstone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;White Sign Soapstone&lt;/a&gt; or by covenant through &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt;), the invasion cooldown timer is immediately reset."}
{"id": "41956", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41956", "title": "Dried Fingers", "text": "The Dried Fingers are an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nFunction.\nAlthough it's not in the item description, the function of the Dried Fingers is to reset the invisible '&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;Invasion&lt;/a&gt; Timer' of the game. Once invaded, the game starts a timer that must expire before the player can be invaded again. If the Dried Fingers are used, the timer is automatically expired\u00a0and the player may be invaded again.\nLocation.\nLocated in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt;. In the room with the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Ditch\"&gt;Undead Ditch&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, as soon as one enters this room from the main hall, to the right there is a dead end with a ladder in the corner. Go up this ladder and be sure to kill the &lt;a href=\"Leydia%20Priestess\"&gt;Leydia Priestess&lt;/a&gt; up there. There is a chest next to her containing the Dried Fingers."}
