{"id": "143022", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143022", "title": "Earth Seeker", "text": "The Earth Seeker is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Snowy%20Mountain%20Pass\"&gt;Snowy Mountain Pass&lt;/a&gt; area, inside the large valley area being patrolled by &lt;a href=\"Millwood%20Knight\"&gt;Millwood Knight&lt;/a&gt;s and the large tree in the center. The Earth Seeker is within a cave area at the back of the valley, being guarded by a Millwood Knight who is himself wielding an Earth Seeker.\nCharacteristics.\nAn unorthodox greataxe, the Earth Seeker is designed for specialized builds and unconventional playstyles.\nUnlike most other weapons, the Earth Seeker &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; with both &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;. The Faith scaling is applied to its physical damage, much like weapons like &lt;a href=\"Wolnir%27s%20Holy%20Sword\"&gt;Wolnir's Holy Sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Yorshka%27s%20Spear\"&gt;Yorshka's Spear&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Morne's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, and as such both stats have to be leveled in order for the weapon to inflict any meaningful amount of damage. This means that the weapon does not easily fit into any standard build archetype, which limits its utility.\nWhat makes this weapon even more unique is its skill, which creates several area-of-effect explosions around the wielder. While this means that the wielder has no way to augment the damage of their weapon through &lt;a href=\"Warcry\"&gt;Warcry&lt;/a&gt;, it also grants the ability to deny ground to the opposition by turning the entire area around the caster into a hazard zone.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "46537", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46537", "title": "Earthen Peak", "text": "The Earthen Peak is a &lt;a href=\"Locations%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;location&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nEarthen Peak is situated inside a large, decaying fortress covered with windmills. The area features many &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Traps%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;environmental traps&lt;/a&gt; that cause &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleeding&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe huge windmill next to the Central Earthen Peak &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; can be destroyed by setting it on fire with a lit &lt;a href=\"torch\"&gt;torch&lt;/a&gt;. This will drain the poison pool in the boss arena of &lt;a href=\"Mytha%2C%20the%20Baneful%20Queen\"&gt;Mytha, the Baneful Queen&lt;/a&gt; as well as other poison pools throughout the area, including the pool near the first bonfire in &lt;a href=\"Harvest%20Valley\"&gt;Harvest Valley&lt;/a&gt;."}
