{"id": "4294", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4294", "title": "East Wood Grain Ring", "text": "The East Wood Grain Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe East Wood Grain Ring is bought from &lt;a href=\"Shiva%20of%20the%20East\"&gt;Shiva of the East&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s. Players must be in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20Hunter\"&gt;Forest Hunter&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;, even if &lt;a href=\"Absolution\"&gt;Absolution&lt;/a&gt; has been purchased.\nGeneral information.\nThe East Wood Grain Ring slows the loss of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, making it a prime candidate for use with weapons that have low durability, such as &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; weapons or &lt;a href=\"Katanas\"&gt;Katanas&lt;/a&gt;. It's also useful to bring to areas that have &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; that degrade durability, like the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Ruins\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, though it does not directly reduce the durability damage of those attacks. It does not reduce weapon durability loss from special attacks such as the &lt;a href=\"Drake%20Sword\"&gt;Drake Sword&lt;/a&gt;'s two-handed strong attack, either."}
{"id": "7877", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7877", "title": "Eastern Armor", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt; \nThe Eastern Armor is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Set\"&gt;Eastern Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nSurrounded by &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Foliage\"&gt;Demonic Foliage&lt;/a&gt;, near a cliff in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Garden\"&gt;Darkroot Garden&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nLike the other pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Set\"&gt;Eastern Set&lt;/a&gt;, it has a very poor protection to weight ratio. It may be viable in the early game for its high resistances, but it is easily surpassed in protection by other chest pieces.\nCuriously, as if to compensate for this statistical weakness, this armor piece alone greatly reduces the wearer's sound emission while two-handing any small / medium weapon. While gripping anything roughly longsword-sized or smaller in this fashion, and so long as their equip load stays below 50%, the wearer may slip up behind enemies at a normal movement speed whilst remaining completely undetected. Moving around after switching to a large weapon or one-handed grip will alert enemies as normal, as will rolling, attacking, and sprinting in their vicinity. Nevertheless, this tiny special attribute gives the armor piece a niche for those who may enjoy occasional light stealth, but who eschew either the &lt;a href=\"Hush\"&gt;Hush&lt;/a&gt; spell or &lt;a href=\"Slumbering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nRequires 200 &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
