{"id": "134507", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134507", "title": "Eastern Iron Shield", "text": "The Eastern Iron Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for 3,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once she has been given the &lt;a href=\"Easterner%27s%20Ashes\"&gt;Easterner's Ashes&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nWith high &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; absorption and very good &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; that &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; well with upgrades, the Eastern Iron Shield is best thought of as a pocket &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Medium Shield&lt;/a&gt;. Boasting the highest physical resistance of all Small Shields in the game, it can be used to reliably ward off physical attacks, though at the cost of tying for the second-heaviest Small Shield in the game, and lacking the ability to &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; incoming attacks.\nDue to its ability to use the &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; of the right-hand weapon, it is best utilized on offensive builds that are lacking in the &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to equip a &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heavier&lt;/a&gt; shield.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
