{"id": "3224", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3224", "title": "Effigy Shield", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"small%20shield\"&gt;small shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Effigy Shield is found on a corpse in &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt; on a path close to the second &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. The plateau with the two &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Beast\"&gt;Skeletal Beast&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"giant%20skeleton%20archer\"&gt;giant skeleton archer&lt;/a&gt; has a slope leading down. Take a right to find the corpse with the shield. A &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight\"&gt;Black Knight&lt;/a&gt; guards the path to the Effigy Shield.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Effigy Shield has the highest defense against &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; of any shield in the game which unfortunately is not affected by the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Upgrade%20Path\"&gt;Lightning Upgrade Path&lt;/a&gt;. It has light deflection and normal &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; speed. The &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;crystal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; is 18.\nThis shield can be used without meeting the &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; requirement, as with the &lt;a href=\"Sanctus\"&gt;Sanctus&lt;/a&gt;. The Faith requirement only applies if it's used as a &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. Blocking and parrying remain unhindered; however, the &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; will be penalized, increasing the likelihood that the player's guard will break.\nResistance defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "2763", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2763", "title": "Egg Burdened", "text": "Egg Burdened are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThey appear to be prone humans with a large clump of eggs attached to their backs.\nPlot.\nMost, though not all, Egg Burdened, including &lt;a href=\"Eingyi\"&gt;Eingyi&lt;/a&gt;, are passive and all serve the \"&lt;a href=\"Quelaag%27s%20Sister\"&gt;Fair Lady&lt;/a&gt;\". Eingyi appears to be the most devout of all the Egg Burdened.\nInfection.\nWhen hostile they attempt to &lt;a href=\"grab\"&gt;grab&lt;/a&gt; the player. If successful, a maggot will burst forth from one of their eggs and latch onto the player, infecting them with a parasitic egg. After a short time, the \"Egghead\" status effect will take hold.\nKilling them will burst the eggs, releasing five &lt;a href=\"Vile%20Maggot\"&gt;Vile Maggot&lt;/a&gt;s that can spray red fluid which can also infect the player.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%23Egghead\"&gt;Egghead&lt;/a&gt; status effect will prevent the player from wearing a helmet, as well as decrease their fire resistance, replace their kick with an \"egg attack\", and decrease the amount of souls gained by 50%. The only means of a cure is the &lt;a href=\"Egg%20Vermifuge\"&gt;Egg Vermifuge&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nThe Egg Burdened are easily avoided thanks to their slow speed. This may be the best course of action, as their drops are hardly worth risking gaining the Poisoned or Egghead status.\nSpoiler:\nIntentionally infecting oneself with Egghead status, then speaking to Eingyi, creates additional dialogue, as well as pyromancies for sale."}
