{"id": "131441", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131441", "title": "Eleonora", "text": "Eleonora (\u30a8\u30ec\u30aa\u30ce\u30fc\u30e9) is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt;. Guaranteed drop from the already awoken &lt;a href=\"Monstrosity%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Monstrosity of Sin&lt;/a&gt; found on the lower level of the ruined chapel that lies in the &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;toxic&lt;/a&gt; swamp.\nCharacteristics.\nAt first glance, Eleonora is a rather unimpressive weapon. It possesses high base damage, but its mediocre scaling and inability to be infused means that this advantage will be diminished as players continue to level up their stats. At higher levels, Eleonora\u2019s AR will be more comparable to that of a straight sword, rather than the standard axes that it shares its weight class and slower moveset with. This disparity is especially apparent when compared to a Heavy Millwood Battle Axe, which shares its weight of 6.5 with Eleonora, but significantly out performs in regards to AR.\nEleonora isn\u2019t without advantages however. Players willing to overlook Eleonora\u2019s below average damage may find value in its superior range when compared to most of the other axes, mitigating a common shortcoming of the Axe weapon class. More notable though is Eleonora\u2019s weapon art, Feast Bell buffs Eleonora with a powerful health drain on hit, in addition to potent bleed buildup. While active, Eleonora becomes a surprisingly effective weapon against large groups of enemies, or against enemies with large health pools, especially if said enemies are prone to bleed.\nThese benefits give an otherwise outclassed weapon an interesting niche in builds or strategies centered around HP regen and sustainability.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nVideos.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
