{"id": "145768", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=145768", "title": "Elfriede", "text": ""}
{"id": "143722", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143722", "title": "Elfriede's Blackflame", "text": "Elfriede's Blackflame is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen performed, the user holds the sword up and slashes diagonally, buffing it with black flame. Doing so will add 145 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage for roughly 45 seconds.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nThis skill is useful for adding more damage to the weapon when facing particularly tough opponents. Of note, since it adds Fire damage it is capable of inflicting stagger on enemies that are weak to the element such as &lt;a href=\"Birch%20Woman\"&gt;Birch Women&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pus%20of%20Man\"&gt;Pus of Man&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnline gameplay.\nIt should be noted that the Onyx Blade itself deals innate &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage, and thus this skill adds a third source of split-damage rather than augmenting an existing element. As such, it is not quite as effective as one would otherwise believe, though it still adds additional damage and pyromancers will have no shortage of &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; to cast this skill.\nHitting an enemy with a two-handed weak attack, and then performing the skill immediately after, will result in a true combo that inflicts high damage while also buffing the weapon."}
{"id": "143723", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143723", "title": "Elfriede's Stance", "text": "Elfriede's Stance is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen activated, the wielder enters a stance where the support scythe is held in the off-hand and the primary scythe is wielded in the main-hand. Entering the stance consumes no &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;Focus Points&lt;/a&gt;.\nPerforming weak attacks will cause the wielder to leap forward and perform up to three attack chains with the paired scythes, while granting &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; with 30 &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; health. The primary scythe will deal purely physical damage, while the support scythe inflicts purely &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage. The physical damage portion of these attacks inflict a reduced multiplier of the weapon's Attack Rating, and each scythe inflicts 85% of the weapon's &lt;a href=\"Frost\"&gt;Frost&lt;/a&gt; build-up, resulting in 170% of the weapon's build-up per successful attack chain. Like the stance, these attack chains consume no Focus Points.\nThe strong attack will bring the support scythe back and then slash upward while conjuring a field of frost in front of the wielder. This attack possesses 35 Poise health, and inflicts 1.15 times the Magic portion of the weapon's Attack Rating as damage. This upward sweep of the support scythe will inflict the weapon's normal Frost build-up, and then the frost field will inflict 10% of the Frost build-up per tick to any enemies that remain in it. Finally, after a short duration, the frost field will erupt, staggering any foes still in the field and inflicting 2.0 times the Magic portion of the weapon's Attack Rating as damage, as well as 150% of the weapon's innate Frost build-up. This attack consumes 18 FP, or 14 FP if the wielder has the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Ring\"&gt;Farron Ring&lt;/a&gt; equipped.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nElfriede's Stance allows the wielder to unleash a flurry of powerful attacks at point-blank range, and is the only way to utilize the Magic portion of the weapon's Attack Rating. The weak attack can lock down foes to be helplessly cut to shreds by the paired scythes, as well as inflict tremendous Frost build-up. The strong attack can be useful when dealing with crowds of enemies in a single direction, as the frost field can deal damage and build up Frostbite in an area. This skill is best used on enemies that have little to no Poise, however, as the prolonged and repeated stagger inflicted by the weak attacks are the strongest aspect of the stance.\nOnline gameplay.\nBecause of the heavy Frost build-up and long stun-lock duration, this skill is very popular for dealing large amounts of damage, especially in co-operative gameplay. Additionally, because the attacks possess Hyper Armor it gives the wielder a very strong option for engaging enemies that manage to sneak within the arc of the primary scythe's blade, a problem that other reapers have no counter to. However, one should be wary that the physical scythe can be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;, so recklessly leaping at a foe with the paired attack chains can be easily countered by prepared opponents.\nThe strong attack, as it uses the support scythe, cannot be parried, and the frost field can create a terrain hazard that discourages foes from approaching to punish should they manage to avoid the initial upward swipe."}
{"id": "8481", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8481", "title": "Elite Cleric Armor", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Elite Cleric Armor is a &lt;a href=\"chest%20armor\"&gt;chest armor&lt;/a&gt; piece that was removed from the final version of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Cleric%20Set\"&gt;Elite Cleric Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nThe only way to obtain this armor piece is to either modify the game or to procure one from someone who has already done so.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Elite Cleric Set looks the same as the &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20Set\"&gt;Cleric Set&lt;/a&gt;, but with increased plating and the leather straps have a brown coloration.\nUpgrades.\nRequires\u00a0200 &lt;a href=\"souls\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
