{"id": "5306", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5306", "title": "Elite Knight Set", "text": "The Elite Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Garden\"&gt;Darkroot Garden&lt;/a&gt;, down a path to right of the &lt;a href=\"Gate%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;Gate of Artorias&lt;/a&gt;. It is guarded by &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Foliage\"&gt;Demonic Foliage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Knight\"&gt;Stone Knight&lt;/a&gt;s.\nPlot.\nAttire of high-ranking knights from the realm of &lt;a href=\"Astora\"&gt;Astora&lt;/a&gt;. Worn by &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Prince%20Ricard\"&gt;Undead Prince Ricard&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Oscar%2C%20Knight%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Oscar, Knight of Astora&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe set boasts one of the highest &lt;a href=\"defense\"&gt;defense&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; ratios in the game, with stats comparable to that of &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Set\"&gt;Havel's Set&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Set\"&gt;Stone Set&lt;/a&gt; when fully upgraded, while &lt;a href=\"weigh\"&gt;weigh&lt;/a&gt;ing nowhere near as much. On the other hand, the Elite Knight set features generally unremarkable &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. As this set can be acquired relatively early in the game, it stands as a viable choice for low-level characters to rely on, and potentially throughout the entirety of the game with frequent upgrading. Due to its low weight compared to much heavier sets with similar defenses that are much more costly to upgrade, a high level player could be able to obtain full mobility despite the weight, resulting in much more effective combat with both defense and agility.\nNotes.\nThe Elite Knight Set's poise was nerfed in 1.04, but buffed in &lt;a href=\"Patch%201.06\"&gt;Patch 1.06&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "50579", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50579", "title": "Elite Knight Set (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Elite Knight Set is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nPurchased from\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Maughlin%20the%20Armorer\"&gt;Maughlin the Armorer&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0for 11,600 souls after spending 1,000 souls at his shop.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Elite Knight Set is a very well-balanced medium armor set, boasting great &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"elemental%20defense\"&gt;elemental defense&lt;/a&gt;s, as well as decent &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; resistances, and some appreciable, but rather unremarkable, &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. While the set does boast a great defense/&lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; ratio, some heavier medium armor sets still outperform it significantly, namely the &lt;a href=\"Throne%20Watcher%20Set\"&gt;Throne Watcher Set&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt;, though the latter is only obtainable via a &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Sunken%20King\"&gt;DLC&lt;/a&gt;.\nBeing considerably easier to acquire in , the &lt;a href=\"Aurous%27%20Set\"&gt;Aurous' Set&lt;/a&gt; is a much better alternative, as it outperforms the Elite Knight set in every possible way (except for the durability but with only 20 points of difference).\nHowever, many new players may be warded off by this set at first, as the high weight, coupled with a low &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;vitality&lt;/a&gt; stat, is quite an ill combination."}
{"id": "131734", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131734", "title": "Elite Knight Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Elite Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for a total of 13,500 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; upon the death of &lt;a href=\"Anri%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Anri of Astora&lt;/a&gt;, either from the completion of &lt;a href=\"Yuria%20of%20Londor\"&gt;Yuria of Londor&lt;/a&gt;'s questline or from killing Anri.\nCharacteristics.\nJust as in the previous games, the Elite Knight Set is widely regarded as an overall excellent and well-balanced medium armor set. It boasts impressive physical and elemental defenses, resistances and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, despite being in the middle of its class in terms of &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;.\nMuch like other metallic armor sets, it is notably weaker against &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; attacks and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage; however, it is also much more resistant to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage and &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; attacks, to boot."}
{"id": "9099", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9099", "title": "Elizabeth", "text": "Elizabeth (\u30a8\u30ea\u30b6\u30d9\u30b9) is a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"merchant\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt; in the\" &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC, and is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Sanctuary\"&gt;Oolacile Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. She is the only\u00a0source of &lt;a href=\"Elizabeth%27s%20Mushroom\"&gt;Elizabeth's Mushroom&lt;/a&gt;, apart from one you can pick up in the forest. If the player kills &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20of%20Oolacile\"&gt;Dusk of Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;, Elizabeth will also die.\nElizabeth is voiced by . \nAppearance.\nShe is a giant mushroom, with a white stalk, and light-red cap. In this sense she\u00a0looks quite similar to the &lt;a href=\"Mushroom%20Parent\"&gt;Mushroom Parent&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Garden\"&gt;Darkroot Garden&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Great%20Hollow\"&gt;The Great Hollow&lt;/a&gt;, however, she is armless and immobile.\nLore.\nElizabeth is the guardian of the Oolacile Sanctuary and is the godmother of &lt;a href=\"Princess%20Dusk\"&gt;Princess Dusk&lt;/a&gt;.\nBy the events of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", Elizabeth is revered as a saint and legends tell that Saint Elizabeth was a beautiful woman of great virtue, who devoted her life to healing the ailments of the needy by concocting medicine and potions. Little more is known about her, apart from the fact that her unique medicines were still widely used long after her time. Her name was passed through verbal tradition from her time to the time of Drangleic.\nBy the time of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\", what looks like her corpse can be found in a cave in &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, by a chest with the &lt;a href=\"Antiquated%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Antiquated Set&lt;/a&gt; and Golden Scroll. How she got there, or whether or not that truly is her, is unknown, but the items found around her heavily imply it is indeed her corpse.\nShe is associated to the creation of troches and a specially treated &lt;a href=\"Elizabeth%27s%20Mushroom\"&gt;dried mushroom&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8246", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8246", "title": "Elizabeth's Mushroom", "text": "Elizabeth's Mushrooms are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". They are only available in the \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;AotA&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC.\nGeneral information.\nUpon consumption, the player regenerates &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; at a very high rate over the course of 30 seconds."}
