{"id": "130328", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130328", "title": "Ember", "text": "Embers are consumable in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nWhen an Ember is consumed, the player will become a &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt;. This will enable invasions and summoning, as well as restoring all of the player's &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; and increase their maximum HP by 30%.\nAlternatives.\nThere are other methods to become a &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt; without using an Ember. This can be useful for players that lack Embers or who simply want to conserve them. These include:"}
{"id": "158854", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=158854", "title": "Ember (Firelink Greatsword)", "text": "Ember is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe wielder brings the sword up and gathers strength, then slams it into the ground, igniting the sword while sending forth a trail of fire. The sword is buffed with 80 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, which lasts for 45 seconds.\nUsage.\nSingle Player.\nThis skill has several uses in single player, such as damaging a group of enemies at range with the flame trail while buffing the sword, or getting a powerful attack in by hitting a foe with both the sword and the fire trail for major damage. As the skill requires only &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; and not an &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot, nor does it scale, the buff can be handy for dealing powerful Fire damage on a build with little/no investment in &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnline.\nBecause the buff adds Fire damage on top of already-existing Fire damage, this skill is very useful in that it greatly reduces the effect that an opponent's Fire flat defenses have against the weapon's attacks. As such, it is noticeably stronger than applying &lt;a href=\"Charcoal%20Pine%20Resin%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Charcoal Pine Resin&lt;/a&gt; to any other weapon.\nThe fire trail can be useful in a myriad of ways, from restricting an opponent's movement, to damaging them from range, to dealing guaranteed damage in a tight corridor where they can't easily escape it. As well, the fire trail lingers longer than the invincibility frames of a roll, allowing it to easily catch players that roll through the initial forward surge. The slam itself can also be handy as a wake-up, as hitting another player with both the sword and the fire trail can easily finish them off if they have just been riposted or backstabbed.\nCare should be observed when using this skill against enemy players though, as not only can it be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;, but the long recovery frames leave the wielder extremely vulnerable to backstabs. Careful spacing and judicious management of stamina can prevent foes from easily taking advantage of the recovery frames."}
{"id": "158857", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=158857", "title": "Ember (Ringed Knight Paired Greatswords)", "text": "Ember is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen activated, the wielder brings both greatswords together to the left, charges them and then launches a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; projectile forward, while buffing the greatswords with Fire for the second phase. A normal attack will cause the wielder to lunge forward and thrust with both greatswords, while a strong attack will perform a leap into a downward slam that creates an explosion at the impact point.\nUsage.\nSingle Player.\nAll phases of the skill can deal tremendous damage when they hit. Against tough enemies, it can be useful to initiate the skill at point-blank range, to hit the target with both the greatsword sweep and the projectile, then performing the second phase and letting the enemy's hitbox block the momentum to strike in place.\nOnline.\nThe initial projectile is difficult to use, as it has very little steering capability once activated; the wielder will launch the projectile in the initial facing direction and will have little control over changing its direction. However, the second phase of the skill has considerably more steering power, being capable of being directed to the sides of the initial direction of the projectile.\nWhat this skill provides is strong gap-closing power, as the projectile has moderate range and both the normal and strong attacks possess strong forward momentum, carrying the wielder closer to a distant target."}
{"id": "158856", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=158856", "title": "Ember (Ringed Knight Spear)", "text": "Ember is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen activated, the wielder leaps forward, thrusting the spear while simultaneously igniting it. Igniting the spear will buff it with 90 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage for 30 seconds.\nThe initial thrust can be chained into up to two strong attacks. The first strong attack will perform a strong clockwise spin, trailing fire behind the head of the spear. The second strong attack will thrust the spear upward, launching a surge of fire forward.\nUsage.\nSingle Player.\nThis skill gives the Ringed Knight Spear a powerful buff as well as strong thrusting and spinning attacks to suit the situation. The flame surge has a moderate width, giving the spear a way to deal with multiple enemies at once.\nOnline.\nThe wielder will have full control over direction for the entire duration of the skill. This allows skillful players to change the direction of their leap, sweep targets that get behind them and then launch the trail of fire to catch opponents who try to roll away. As well, the initial leap can act to foil players that try to keep out of the spear's long reach, closing the distance quickly.\nBeware that all phases of this skill can be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "158855", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=158855", "title": "Ember (Ringed Knight Straight Sword)", "text": "Ember is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen activated, the wielder enters a stance which brings the sword up to their side and ignites it, extending its length with fire.\nThe normal attack will chain up to three different attacks. The first attack will have the wielder swing the sword twice horizontally, from right to left then back. The second attack is similar to the first, only wilder in arc. The third attack will perform a strong clockwise spin. Subsequent attacks will start over again from the first attack.\nThe strong attack can chain twice. The first attack has the wielder lunge into a powerful thrust with strong forward momentum, while the second attack results in a powerful overhead slam.\nUsage.\nSingle Player.\nThis skill can give the wielder a strong burst of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage with the attacks, useful against enemies that are weak to the element. Because the Ringed Knight Straight Sword is largely a quality weapon, this gives the wielder the ability to inflict strong Fire damage without investing into caster stats.\nOnline.\nThis skill provides strong horizontal coverage with the normal attacks, as well as strong chasing power with the strong attacks.\nThe first two normal attacks are a true combo, allowing the wielder to hit an opponent up to four times. This can be followed up with the strong attack to chase them down as they try to roll away to recover, and has strong roll-catch potential. However, care should be taken when using this skill, as all parts of it can be &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parried&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "177118", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=177118", "title": "Ember (Tool)", "text": "An Ember is a &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;weapon enhancement&lt;/a&gt; tool in &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;. These tools can be given to blacksmiths in &lt;a href=\"Lordran\"&gt;Lordran&lt;/a&gt; to unlock certain weapon ascensions and reinforcements. Only one out of the four (&lt;a href=\"Andre%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Andre of Astora&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vamos\"&gt;Vamos&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Rickert%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Rickert of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt;) will accept a specific Ember, depending on their experience and nature.\nThere is a total of ten Embers scattered across Lordran hidden in chests or in corpses."}
