{"id": "38581", "revid": "346375", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38581", "title": "Emerald Herald", "text": "The Emerald Herald is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". She is voiced by .\nPlot.\nMuch like the &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3AMaiden%20in%20Black\"&gt;Maiden in Black&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Souls\"&gt;Demon's Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", the Emerald Herald serves as the player's means of leveling up, replacing the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfires&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" in this respect.\nShe gives the player an &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; upon introducing herself. Bringing her &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20Shard\"&gt;Estus Flask Shard&lt;/a&gt;s will increase the total amount of charges that the Flask can hold.\nShe gives the player the &lt;a href=\"Aged%20Feather\"&gt;Aged Feather&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0when spoken to upon arrival in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aerie\"&gt;Dragon Aerie&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Emerald Herald's real name is Shanalotte, a name given to her by the &lt;a href=\"dragons\"&gt;dragons&lt;/a&gt;. Born of dragons but contrived by men, she was created specifically to break the &lt;a href=\"undead%20curse\"&gt;undead curse&lt;/a&gt;, but her creators failed and she did not come out as intended. Despite this, she guides &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; towards the &lt;a href=\"Throne%20of%20Want\"&gt;Throne of Want&lt;/a&gt;, waiting for a powerful undead that might defeat the &lt;a href=\"Four%20Old%20Ones\"&gt;Four Old Ones&lt;/a&gt;, succeed &lt;a href=\"Vendrick\"&gt;Vendrick&lt;/a&gt; and end the undead curse.\nShe eventually finds this someone in the &lt;a href=\"Bearer%20of%20the%20Curse\"&gt;Bearer of the Curse&lt;/a&gt;, an undead with no memory of their origins from a far away land. Shanalotte guides the Bearer of the Curse in their quest, telling them to seek &lt;a href=\"Soul\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; and to seek the king. She will guide the Bearer of the Curse to seek out the Four Old Ones in order to claim their powerful souls. Once the Bearer of the Curse has done this, the way to &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt;, the home of Vendrick, will be open. Shanalotte will wait outside the castle, directing the Bearer of the Curse to enter.\nShe will next appear in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt;, where Vendrick now wanders aimlessly. After the Bearer of the Curse has claimed the king's ring, she will direct them to follow the mark of the king and journey east, and warn them that if they continue on this path, they too will one day walk these same grounds, without really knowing why.\nShanalotte will once again appear once the Bearer of the Curse has reached the Dragon Aerie. Here, she will reveal that it was her manifestations that led them here, and has been guiding them all along. She directs the Bearer to the top of the aerie, where the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Dragon\"&gt;Ancient Dragon&lt;/a&gt; awaits them.\nShanalotte will appear one final time when the Bearer of the Curse is approaching the &lt;a href=\"Throne%20of%20Want\"&gt;Throne of Want&lt;/a&gt;. She will tell the Bearer of her origins and her true name. She will warn them that &lt;a href=\"Nashandra\"&gt;Nashandra&lt;/a&gt;, desiring the power of &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;the Flame&lt;/a&gt; and the Great Soul will come after them, but that they must persist nonetheless.\nShould the Bearer of the Curse choose to claim the throne, Shanalotte will narrate their ascent, explaining that linking the flame will cause souls to flourish anew but that the events that have transpired will play out all over again, and that it is the Bearer's choice whether to embrace or renounce this.\n&lt;a href=\"Royal%20Sorcerer%20Navlaan\"&gt;Royal Sorcerer Navlaan&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0tells the player many people believe the Emerald Herald is the last firekeeper. Navlaan will also say she is sometimes known as the \"Muse\".\nStrategy.\nIf the player lowers her health down to half, she will refuse to talk and will simply stand still. Resting at a bonfire will reset her health to normal, but she will still ignore the player until they have spoken with &lt;a href=\"Cromwell%20the%20Pardoner\"&gt;Cromwell the Pardoner&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe drops the &lt;a href=\"Aged%20Feather\"&gt;Aged Feather&lt;/a&gt; if killed."}
{"id": "3870", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3870", "title": "Emit Force", "text": "Emit Force (\u653e\u3064\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30b9) is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"Siegmeyer%20of%20Catarina\"&gt;Siegmeyer of Catarina&lt;/a&gt; gifts the player this miracle in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt; after helping him out in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;. The player must answer \"yes\" to his question.\nGeneral Information.\nUpon casting, players will charge up an energy ball and release it. It will travel a short distance in a straight line before exploding with a fairly large &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20Effect\"&gt;area of effect&lt;/a&gt;, that creates a shockwave on impact that causes damage, and can knock down or stun enemies. This shockwave deflects projectiles such as arrows, Crystal Soul Spears, and firebombs similar to &lt;a href=\"Force\"&gt;Force&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wrath%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Wrath of the Gods&lt;/a&gt;. This spell also benefits from &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20Synergy\"&gt;miracle synergy&lt;/a&gt; in terms of its magic damage in an incremental way by 0.1 for every miracle synergy level of of its 2.4 MagAdjust modifier. The range for the spell is minimal, shorter than other offensive spells like Lighting Spear or the Soul arrow variants, but it is slightly longer than any weapon can reach. \nOverview.\nEmit Force is useful in PvE as a way of greeting a larger group of weak &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt;. It is also good against stronger enemies as it can often stun them.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, Emit force can be tricky to use owing to its inordinately long casting time, but this is slightly compensated for by its very large area of effect. Emit Force may best be used in narrow corridors to limit opponents' options. In terms of hitting an opponent, it is often best to 'dead aim' (i.e. not be locked onto your target) Emit Force and instead direct it manually towards your target or where your target is likely to dodge, as the large projectile and area of effect makes hitting non-aimed targets slightly easier.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52312", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52312", "title": "Emit Force (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Emit Force is a &lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nEmit Force is in essence a thrown &lt;a href=\"Wrath%20of%20the%20Gods%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Wrath of the Gods&lt;/a&gt;. The spell does less damage than Wrath of the Gods, but still causes knockback to those caught in the blast.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike many other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "133488", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133488", "title": "Emit Force (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Emit Force (\u653e\u3064\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30b9) is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained as a gift from &lt;a href=\"Siegward%20of%20Catarina\"&gt;Siegward of Catarina&lt;/a&gt; by exhausting his dialogue in the kitchen found after the sewer area in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nThe caster briefly charges an orb, and then launches it forward. The orb will explode upon impact, inflicting 1.2 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst as &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; damage with direct contact, and stagger or knock down enemies caught in the explosion. The explosion inflicts 0.6 times the Spell Buff of the catalyst.\nThe orb has a long travel distance and does not arc, allowing the caster to knock down targets from very far away.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "131076", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131076", "title": "Emma", "text": ""}
{"id": "131075", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131075", "title": "Emma, High Priestess of Lothric Castle", "text": "Emma, High Priestess of Lothric Castle is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". She is voiced by .\nLocation.\nFound inside the cathedral at the end of the main courtyard in the &lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt;, opposite to &lt;a href=\"Vordt%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Vordt&lt;/a&gt;'s boss arena.\nDescription.\nHigh Priestess Emma presents the player with the &lt;a href=\"Small%20Lothric%20Banner\"&gt;Small Lothric Banner&lt;/a&gt; when she is first talked to, an item which grants passage to the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;. She also lets the player join the &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;, upon talking to her a second time.\nAfter defeating the first three &lt;a href=\"Lords%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lords of Cinder&lt;/a&gt;, she will give the player the &lt;a href=\"Basin%20of%20Vows\"&gt;Basin of Vows&lt;/a&gt;, which is used to trigger the appearance of the &lt;a href=\"Dancer%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Dancer of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt;. She also drops the Basin if killed at any time, allowing the Dancer to be encountered early."}
