{"id": "4948", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4948", "title": "Ending", "text": "To Link the Fire and The Dark Lord are the two endings that can be chosen in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". The &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt; may choose to perpetuate the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Age of Fire&lt;/a&gt;, or instead bring about the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Dark\"&gt;Age of Dark&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0There are no other requirements, aside from defeating the final boss, to access either ending.\nTo Link the Fire.\nThis ending is obtained by\u00a0lighting the &lt;a href=\"bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0that appears after defeating &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Gwyn, Lord of Cinder&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0In sacrifice, the Chosen Undead links the First Flame as Gwyn had done before him/her, thus fulfilling\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Kingseeker%20Frampt\"&gt;Kingseeker Frampt's&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0goal of continuing the Age of Fire. The Curse of the Undead will be broken, but one day the flames will fade again, and all will play out as before.\nThe Dark Lord.\nThis ending is obtained after exiting the arena where the Chosen Undead felled Gwyn instead of lighting the bonfire. All the primordial serpents bow before the new ruler, the Chosen Undead, who has thus become the \"Dark Lord\". By choosing\u00a0this ending, the Age of Fire is relinquished and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Darkstalker%20Kaathe\"&gt;Darkstalker Kaathe&lt;/a&gt;'s goal of starting the Age of Dark is fulfilled."}
{"id": "117134", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=117134", "title": "Ending (Dark Souls II)", "text": "In \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\", there are two endings from which the player may chose: Proceed to Throne or Leave Throne. The Proceed to Throne ending was the default ending until \"\" version was released, and was the default in the original \"Dark Souls II\" before the \"Scholar of the First Sin\" update. \nProceed to Throne.\nAfter the player defeats &lt;a href=\"Nashandra\"&gt;Nashandra&lt;/a&gt; (or &lt;a href=\"Aldia%2C%20Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Aldia, Scholar of the First Sin&lt;/a&gt;, if his conditions are met) at the &lt;a href=\"Throne%20of%20Want\"&gt;Throne of Want&lt;/a&gt;, a cutscene will play showing the player walking atop the &lt;a href=\"golem\"&gt;golem&lt;/a&gt;s, who create a bridge for the player to cross, and into a throne room. In this ending, the &lt;a href=\"Bearer%20of%20the%20Curse\"&gt;Bearer of the Curse&lt;/a&gt; will accept their part in the cycle of the world and take the throne. Doing so means that they will either sacrifice themselves to link the &lt;a href=\"The%20First%20Flame\"&gt;flame&lt;/a&gt;, or allow the flame to continue to fade\u00a0and become the Dark Lord. Which the Bearer of the Curse chooses is known only to them.\u00a0\nLeave the Throne.\nAvailable only to those with the \"Scholar of the First Sin\" version or any patch newer than 1.10 for the original \"Dark Souls II\".\nThis ending only becomes available after the player has defeated &lt;a href=\"Vendrick\"&gt;Vendrick&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Crypt\"&gt;Undead Crypt&lt;/a&gt; and after having spoken to Aldia at every bonfire he spawns at throughout the game. Upon defeating Nashandra, Aldia will fight the player as an additional final boss. Upon defeating Aldia, both endings are available to the player, and choosing to exit the Throne of Want through the fog wall will result in this ending.\nIn this ending, the Bearer of the Curse rejects the throne, and bitterly walks away, seemingly to seek another, more permanent way to end the curse.\nAfter the credits.\nRegardless of the ending chosen, the player is warped to &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt;, allowing them to finish any remaining business. The player may then begin the next &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;New Game+&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Majula%23Bonfires\"&gt;Far Fire&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "134267", "revid": "1087082", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134267", "title": "Ending (Dark Souls III)", "text": "In \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\", there are four endings from which the player may choose:\nTo Link the First Flame.\nIn this ending, the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; attempts to repeat what all the other &lt;a href=\"Lords%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lords of Cinder&lt;/a&gt; of the past had done before them: to link the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; in the hope of preserving the current state of the world. The Ashen One stretches out a hand and the flame spread to their body that begins to burn and then they merely sits beside the bonfire. However, unlike in the past, where the act of linking the fading Flame restored its strength and brought its influence back to the world, this time nothing happens. The Flame is too weak and the world remains dark and covered in ash, with the sun still obscured by a fire-dripping eclipse that resembles the &lt;a href=\"Darksign%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark Sign&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo get this ending, the player must light the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0that appears after defeating the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Soul of Cinder&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe End of Fire.\nIn this ending, the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt; takes the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; into her hands, causing it to die out entirely. The light in the sky quickly fades together with the Flame and soon after the world descends into complete darkness. Although the world has now finally entered the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Dark\"&gt;Age of Dark&lt;/a&gt; which should have naturally succeeded that of Fire, there are still multiple &lt;a href=\"Lords%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lords of Cinder&lt;/a&gt; from the past who possess fragments of the First Flame within them. Sooner or later they too will rise from their graves and begin to wander the world and use the power of their tiny flames conserved in the form of &lt;a href=\"Cinders%20of%20a%20Lord\"&gt;cinders&lt;/a&gt;. \nTo get this ending, the player must first give the &lt;a href=\"Eyes%20of%20a%20Fire%20Keeper\"&gt;Eyes of a Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt; and summon her after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Soul of Cinder&lt;/a&gt;. Her sign appears next to the bonfire.\nThe End of Fire (Alternative).\nIn this ending the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; strikes the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt; down before the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; is completely extinguished by her. The Ashen One then tramples her limp body and takes the Fire from her hands. Kneeling, the Ashen One raises the Flame, offering it to the sun obscured by a fire-dripping eclipse that resembles the &lt;a href=\"Darksign%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark Sign&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo get this ending, the player must strike the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keeper%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Keeper&lt;/a&gt; before the light fades and everything turns to darkness.\nThe Usurpation of Flame.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; stretches out a hand and the flame spread to their body that begins to burn. However they are able to absorb the entirety of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt; inside of their body and the strain makes them collapse on the ground. \nAn indefinite amount of time later, the Ashen One rises again, having successfully controlled the power of the Flame within themselves. The sun obscured by a light-dripping eclipse that resembles the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Sigil\"&gt;Dark Sigil&lt;/a&gt; follows the movements of the Ashen One, indicating that the Flame lives within them, but the world is shrouded in a patina of darkness and time is still. In front of them, &lt;a href=\"Yuria%20of%20Londor\"&gt;Yuria&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Liliane\"&gt;Liliane&lt;/a&gt;, the last two sisters of the Sable Church of &lt;a href=\"Londor\"&gt;Londor&lt;/a&gt; kneel at their feet and pay their respect. Behind them, &lt;a href=\"Anri%20of%20Astora\"&gt;Anri&lt;/a&gt; kneel in service and dozens of Hollows are prostrated in prayer, adoring their long-awaited Lord of Hollows. The Lord then sets out into the world, with both the powers of Fire and Darkness under their control and thus the ability to shape the world in any way they wish.\nTo get this ending, the player must complete a strict and complex questline:"}
