{"id": "6720", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6720", "title": "Endurance (Dark Souls)", "text": " Endurance is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nInvesting in Endurance increases maximum stamina, equipment load, and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; resistance. In terms of equipment load, Endurance softcaps at 40. It is not usually worth going over this softcap. \nStamina.\n Stamina is represented by the green bar on the top left corner of the screen. One large chunk of the bar is approximately 28.57 stamina. Actions such as dashing and attacking reduce stamina which after a brief pause begins regenerating. \u00a0If the player runs out of stamina, they temporarily cannot attack or dash.\nIf a character is blocking and a blow exceeds the amount of stamina needed to absorb the damage, that character is then staggered, left wide open, and takes the excess damage. This mechanic is dependent on\u00a0&lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;.\nStamina is capped at 160, which is reached at level 40 endurance; further levels do not increase stamina. Stamina can also be increased by the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Favor%20and%20Protection\"&gt;Ring of Favor and Protection&lt;/a&gt;, even if the 40 endurance cap has been reached.\nStamina Regeneration Rate.\nStamina has a base regeneration rate for all players, regardless of soul level or stats: 45 stamina per second. The regeneration rate can be increased passively while wearing the &lt;a href=\"Mask%20of%20the%20Child\"&gt;Mask of the Child&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Grass%20Crest%20Shield\"&gt;Grass Crest Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cloranthy%20Ring\"&gt;Cloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt;, consuming a &lt;a href=\"Green%20Blossom\"&gt;Green Blossom&lt;/a&gt;, or casting &lt;a href=\"Power%20Within\"&gt;Power Within&lt;/a&gt;. Green blossoms and Power Within do not stack, but all other effects will stack with each other.\nRegeneration rate is lowered by 80% while the player has his/her guard up or while climbing a ladder. Wearing heavy armor pieces reduces this regeneration rate by 1-2 stamina per second. If the player is heavily burdened (more than 50%), then stamina will regenerate 20% slowed. If the player is over-burdened, the penalty is 30% instead.\nEquipment Load.\n Equipment load determines how much equipment the player can equip before being affected by movement penalties. The softcap for endurance is 40 in terms of carry weight. The\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Mask%20of%20the%20Father\"&gt;Mask of the Father&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Havel's Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Favor%20and%20Protection\"&gt;Ring of Favor and Protection&lt;/a&gt; also improve equipment load. Though Mask of the Father is so heavy it usually cancels out its own effect. \nIt is generally advised to keep equipment load at or below 25% in order to stay nimble. For more information roll types visit the &lt;a href=\"Rolling\"&gt;Rolling&lt;/a&gt; page. "}
{"id": "50148", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50148", "title": "Endurance (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Endurance is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nIncreasing one's Endurance affects several attributes of the player. Endurance's main effect is to increase both the player's &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Stamina&lt;/a&gt;, as well as their total &lt;a href=\"HP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; however, this does not increase it as much as raising &lt;a href=\"Vigor\"&gt;Vigor&lt;/a&gt; will. Endurance is also interactive with &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;, the sum of which determines the player's natural &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; Defense. Finally, Endurance is also interactive with the &lt;a href=\"Adaptability\"&gt;Adaptability&lt;/a&gt; stat, in that raising the two stats at the same rate will grant extra natural &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnlike in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Souls\"&gt;Demon's Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", raising Endurance does not improve a character's &lt;a href=\"Equip%20Load\"&gt;Equip Load&lt;/a&gt;.\nStat development.\nDefense Bonus is leveled by the average level of between &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, Endurance and &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;. Every &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; piece can have a Scaling percentage that determines how it multiplies this value. Unarmored Head / Chest / Hand / Legs scale with this value at 7.5 / 22.5 / 7.5 / 12.5%."}
{"id": "130189", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130189", "title": "Endurance (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Endurance is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nOverview.\nEndurance governs the player's overall stamina, flat defense against &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage and resistance to &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; build-up. Leveling up Endurance will raise the player's stamina by 1 - 3 points up until 40, which is the softcap. At 40 points or greater, 5 or more levels will have to be invested into the stat to receive additional points in stamina.\nStamina is needed to perform various actions in the game, such as guarding, attacking, casting various spells, running, jumping, and dodging, to name a few. Once a player's stamina is exhausted, they will be unable to perform actions until it regenerates. Attempting to perform any actions after stamina is depleted will delay the rate at which it begins to regenerate.\nPlayers that guard against attacks will eventually have their &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Break\"&gt;guard broken&lt;/a&gt; once their stamina is depleted, resulting in them staggering back and being prone to a critical attack.\nVarious items and equipment found throughout the game can improve stamina regeneration or hamper it. Such items include &lt;a href=\"Green%20Blossom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Green Blossoms&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Grass%20Crest%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Grass Crest Shield&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Chloranthy%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Chloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Greatshield%20of%20Glory%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Greatshield of Glory&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "133828", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133828", "title": "Great Mace", "text": "The Great Mace is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Consumed%20King%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Consumed King's Garden&lt;/a&gt;\nCharacteristics.\nAlthough matched or slightly bested by some other great hammers in terms of damage, the Great Mace is lighter than its rivals (though middle of the road weight-wise otherwise), making it a choice pick for strength builds seeking efficiency.\nStrangely, it has slightly stronger scaling on a Lightning-infusion than on a Crystal-infusion, though this only ever amounts to about 10 more AR for the former\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with .\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "55457", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55457", "title": "Great Machete", "text": "The Great Machete\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Reapers\"&gt;reaper&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nRare drop from the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Jailer\"&gt;Undead Jailer&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"The%20Lost%20Bastille\"&gt;The Lost Bastille&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe Great Machete is a Reaper-&lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Types%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;type&lt;/a&gt; weapon. Due to the fact that its &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; is superior to its &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; scaling, it is one of the better Reapers for Strength builds, and has lower requirements than the &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Scythe\"&gt;Bone Scythe&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "130284", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130284", "title": "Great Machete (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Great Machete is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Manservant\"&gt;Hollow Manservant&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Great Machete provides one of the earliest accesses to heavy weaponry in the game, should the player is lucky enough to obtain one as a drop from a &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Manservant\"&gt;Hollow Manservant&lt;/a&gt; while traversing the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile its 24 &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement will have the player investing frequently in this attribute, the rewards are well worth the effort, since the force with which each swing with this weapon is performed will kill most enemies in only one or two hits, making it also a good choice for spending the first obtained on it.\nIt has the basic &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; moveset and also has decent reach.\nIts &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, \"Sharpen\", boosts the weapon's attack rating by 10%.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
