{"id": "133921", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133921", "title": "Great Magic Shield", "text": "Great Magic Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by a &lt;a href=\"Corpse%20Grub\"&gt;Corpse Grub&lt;/a&gt; in a cell found in the &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. After the first &lt;a href=\"Jailer\"&gt;Jailer&lt;/a&gt;, drop down one floor and open the door to the creature.\nEffect.\nGreatly reinforces &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in the left hand, increasing damage absorption in all categories to 100% regardless of prior resistances, while increasing &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; by 50%. &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt;s that inflict damage through raised shields such as &lt;a href=\"Blind%20Spot\"&gt;Blind Spot&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Splitter\"&gt;Shield Splitter&lt;/a&gt; will also be completely blocked. Effects last for 30 seconds, and duration can be increased by equipping a &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "4631", "revid": "357124", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4631", "title": "Great Magic Weapon", "text": "Great Magic Weapon (\u5f37\u3044\u9b54\u6cd5\u306e\u6b66\u5668) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGreat Magic Weapon is located in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, on a chandelier in a structure housing the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;. To obtain the spell, the chain holding the chandelier must be cut while traversing the rafters on the upper levels of the room; the sorcery can be collected after reaching the lower level.\nGeneral information.\nGreat Magic Weapon may only be used on enchantable &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, which are those that are &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt; down the &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Raw%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; paths, as well as a limited amount of &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation%23Non-standard%20weapons\"&gt;exceptions&lt;/a&gt;.\nGreat Magic Weapon is a stronger version of the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Weapon\"&gt;Magic Weapon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;augmentation&lt;/a&gt;, but with fewer casts and weaker than &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Magic%20Weapon\"&gt;Crystal Magic Weapon&lt;/a&gt;. It adds a flat amount of magic attack power to the weapon equal 1.1 times the catalyst's magic adjust. Great Magic Weapon does not benefit from the &lt;a href=\"Bellowing%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;, although it does benefit from the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nDue to its somewhat low stat requirement, the spell is a good candidate for use with the &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Ivory%20Catalyst\"&gt;Oolacile Ivory Catalyst&lt;/a&gt;. giving non magic users a powerful weapon buff with only a few points of stat investment.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52366", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52366", "title": "Great Magic Weapon (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Great Magic Weapon is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nApplies a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; buff to the weapon in the hand opposite the &lt;a href=\"Staves\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt; used to cast the spell. This is the intermediate sorcery weapon buff, between the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Weapon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Magic%20Weapon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; variants, and as such has a moderate amount of casts, medium duration, and decent requirements. This places it in a somewhat awkward spot between the ease of acquisition and use of Magic Weapon and the power of Crystal Magic Weapon that makes it more suitable for a character with middling amounts of Intelligence, such as a character adding some decently powerful spells to their weapon usage. \nThe total bonus is difficult to calculate, but is roughly 20% of the sum (30 + weapon's Magic scaling * character's Magic bonus + weapon's Base damage), with a small additional damage bonus on &lt;a href=\"Faintstone\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; infused weapons.\nThe duration scales with Intelligence, starting 27 seconds at 10 Intelligence when this spell is spiced down going all the way up to 108 seconds when the duration scaling caps at 27 Intelligence. \nAttunement Milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:\nDuration Scaling Information.\nDuration values are listed in seconds. Base duration of this spell only depends on Intelligence. Base duration shown as well as values with the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest&lt;/a&gt; variants applied and pieces of &lt;a href=\"Northwarder%20Set\"&gt;Northwarder Set&lt;/a&gt; applied."}
{"id": "133920", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133920", "title": "Great Magic Weapon (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Great Magic Weapon is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, down the path from the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep%20Perimeter\"&gt;Farron Keep Perimeter&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, past the &lt;a href=\"Ravenous%20Crystal%20Lizard\"&gt;Ravenous Crystal Lizard&lt;/a&gt; and near the shortcut gate back to the &lt;a href=\"Crucifixion%20Woods\"&gt;Crucifixion Woods&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nReinforces right-hand weapon with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;, adding 85% of the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; as Magic damage for 60 seconds. The duration of the buff can be extended by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor catalysts that scale with both &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt;, only the Intelligence portion of the Spell Buff is counted. Special catalysts such as the &lt;a href=\"Archdeacon%27s%20Great%20Staff\"&gt;Archdeacon's Great Staff&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Man-grub%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Man-grub's Staff&lt;/a&gt; are treated as having the base 100 Spell Buff.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "52259", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52259", "title": "Great Moth", "text": "Great Moths are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nGreat Moths are generally harmless, remaining stationary on walls or high above on trees. However, they will release a large cloud of poisonous powder when the player is nearby. The cloud inflicts &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; build-up at an alarming rate, and only a few seconds of exposure is needed to poison the player. As such, it is advised to keep an eye out for them to avoid being poisoned while exploring or fighting.\nGreat Moths have very low HP and can be taken out by a single hit from most attacks. However, they are usually outside of melee range, so one must use ranged weapons or magic to fight them.\nIt can be worthwhile to seek out and kill them whenever they are encountered, as they always drop a clump of &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Moss\"&gt;Poison Moss&lt;/a&gt; upon death. In \"\", additional moths have been added to several other areas throughout the game and have more advanced guaranteed drops.\nLocations.\nA large number of Great Moths can be found throughout the &lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse\"&gt;Huntsman's Copse&lt;/a&gt;, past the &lt;a href=\"Huntsman%27s%20Copse%23Bonfires\"&gt;Bridge Approach&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nScholar of the First Sin.\nIn \"\", many non-respawning Great Moths have been added to other various locations in the game. Their presence only serves to provide the player with their guaranteed drops, as long as they keep an eye looking for them.\nDrops.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Huntsman's Copse =\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
