{"id": "58009", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=58009", "title": "Great Resonant Soul", "text": "Great Resonant Soul is a &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;hex&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nAn improved variation of &lt;a href=\"Resonant%20Soul\"&gt;Resonant Soul&lt;/a&gt;; fires a large, straight-flying mass of dark energy. The damage of the spell is vastly increased when the player pays the optional cost of 500 souls per cast. The damage calculation is roughly (1.89 x D) + 287, where D equals the catalyst's total &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "5239", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5239", "title": "Great Scythe", "text": "The Great Scythe is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Great Scythe is found late in &lt;a href=\"the%20Catacombs\"&gt;the Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;, after the fourth &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt;. It is visible from inside the room with the stone plate door's lever leading to the 2nd switch bridge (the corpse is inaccessible a level above your head). Pass through the stone plate door after opening it, instead of turning left, carry on few steps to the stairs connected to nothing (falling to your death alert), drop off on your right to a ledge, then to another back to the main Catacombs rocky block.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Great Scythe deals decent damage, and its low requirements and weight make it easily accessible to most players, primarily scaling off &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; unlike the usual \"Quality Scaling\" of most weapons in the &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; class. The fast and wide running attack and strong attacks make the Great Scythe a great weapon for \"dead-angling\" though this unintended mechanic has been removed in the Remastered version of the game. \nLike all Halberds, if the attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal. This means that Great Scythe is capable of getting &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Sweet_Spot_Damage_Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; Bonus Damage. Unlike most Halberds, Great Scythe does not deal &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage and does not get &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Counter_Damage\"&gt;Counter Damage&lt;/a&gt; bonuses, making it and the other Scythe-named the weaker weapons within the Halberd class.\nThe Great Scythe builds up &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; at a rate of 30 per strike and is very similar to the &lt;a href=\"Lifehunt%20Scythe\"&gt;Lifehunt Scythe&lt;/a&gt;, possessing near-identical stats and an identical moveset. The Great Scythe holds the advantage over the Lifehunt Scythe of not having self-bleed buildup, as well as being &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;enchantable&lt;/a&gt;. On the other hand, it inflicts less buildup on opponents and deals slightly less base &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage%20Types\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "55458", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55458", "title": "Great Scythe (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Great Scythe is a &lt;a href=\"Reapers\"&gt;reaper&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe longest of the Reaper class weapons, the Great Scythe requires proper spacing to deal the most damage. The player would want to avoid standing too close to their target, as attacking with anything other than the blade will deal significantly less damage."}
{"id": "130375", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130375", "title": "Great Scythe (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Great Scythe is a &lt;a href=\"Reapers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;reaper&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt;. From the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement%23Bonfires\"&gt;Dilapidated Bridge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;, head onward and enter the destroyed house located in front of the graveyard where the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Archer%20of%20the%20Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;giant archer&lt;/a&gt;'s arrows start raining down. Go upstairs, turn around and jump toward the broken wooden floorboards to reach it.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Great Scythe is the archetype of its weapon class, a long-reaching polearm which can damage targets through raised shields.\nFound early in the game, the Great Scythe's attributes make it attractive to builds that specialize in &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. It is also the lightest reaper in the game, allowing builds with low &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; to wield it with few problems. As with other polearms, it possesses a sweet-spot mechanic where hitting a target with the blade of the weapon will inflict full &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage, but if the target is inside of the weapon's arc it will inflict reduced damage and deal &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage instead.\nIt is one of two reapers in the game that can be &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt; to meet the wielder's specific build needs, the other being the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Corvian%20Scythe\"&gt;Great Corvian Scythe&lt;/a&gt;. Compared to its larger cousin, the Great Scythe has more lenient stat requirements, making it more ideal for elemental builds that do not wish to level &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and Dexterity too much. However, its damage output is weaker in virtually all cases, making the Corvian Scythe much more favored, especially in &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; situations.\nHowever, the Great Scythe's most powerful asset is that, on top of being the lightest reaper in the game, it is also the one with the longest reach. With proper spacing, the Great Scythe is able to defeat virtually all &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;halberds&lt;/a&gt; in the game, and can even outreach most &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spears&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"pikes\"&gt;pikes&lt;/a&gt;. In the hands of one with patience, the Great Scythe is a powerful asset.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with .\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "47828", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47828", "title": "Great Soul Arrow", "text": ""}
{"id": "4501", "revid": "357125", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4501", "title": "Great Soul Arrow (Dark Souls)", "text": "Great Soul Arrow (\u5f37\u3044\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u306e\u77e2) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nGreat Soul Arrow has 20 casts per copy and requires 14 &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; to use. Shoot a vivid blue bolt of energy at &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt;. It requires slightly more time to cast than regular &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and has 10 less charges,\u00a0but deals greater damage. It has a magic attack power of 1.5 times the catalyst's magic adjust.\nThe higher damage almost perfectly counters the lower number of uses, and makes it so that Great Soul Arrow has almost the same amount of total damage per &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot as the regular Soul Arrow spell. The higher power of the Great version makes it more useful for efficiently combating mid-to-late game enemies.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "47831", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47831", "title": "Great Soul Arrow (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Great Soul Arrow is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nUnleashes a small bolt of magic, stronger than that of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, with a slightly longer casting time. The bolt travels a long distance, however, it can only travel in a straight line, meaning that mobile enemies can easily dodge it.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "133919", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133919", "title": "Great Soul Arrow (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Great Soul Arrow is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nA stronger variant of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;. Fires a soul arrow at the target, dealing 1.5 times the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage. Has the same cast time as Soul Arrow but deals more damage, though still less than &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Heavy Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "150710", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150710", "title": "Great Soul Dregs", "text": "Great Soul Dregs (\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u306e\u5927\u6fb1) is a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dark&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Dreg%20Heap\"&gt;The Dreg Heap&lt;/a&gt;. After finding the first &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Knight\"&gt;Lothric Knight&lt;/a&gt;s in the area, players can exit to the left of the small chapel and into a building infested with &lt;a href=\"Murkmen\"&gt;Murkmen&lt;/a&gt;. At the end of the corridor is an &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt; that reveals a staircase to the second floor. The spell can be found at the end of the last room, guarded by numerous Dregs-possessed Murkmen.\nEffect.\nConjures a large soul dreg which accelerates upon cast and homes in on its target, exploding and inflicting 2.55 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage upon impact. Certain Dark catalysts will boost the damage output of this spell, and allow the wielder to take advantage of &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nThe most powerful member of the &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Soul\"&gt;Deep Soul&lt;/a&gt; family, though in appearance it resembles a singular, massive orb similar to those of &lt;a href=\"Affinity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Affinity&lt;/a&gt;. This spell deals massive damage, albeit not as efficient as &lt;a href=\"Great%20Deep%20Soul\"&gt;Great Deep Soul&lt;/a&gt; in terms of damage-to-&lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; cost.\nThough it has no piercing abilities and will not go through enemies that are lined up, it may indeed hit multiple enemies if they are sufficiently clustered as it has a blast radius.\nOnline gameplay.\nGreat Soul Dregs is essentially the Dark analogue to &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Crystal Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt;, in that it takes longer &lt;a href=\"Casting%20Speed\"&gt;to cast&lt;/a&gt; but inflicts significantly more damage. Damage-wise, its damage output rivals Crystal Soul Spear when boosted by the proper catalyst, but it is also significantly harder to dodge due to its slow travel speed and moderate tracking. As well, it has a relatively fast casting animation, though still slower than Deep Soul, meaning that it does not require &lt;a href=\"Sage%20Ring\"&gt;Sage Ring&lt;/a&gt; in order to cast properly.\nIts sheer size makes it hard to roll away from in tight quarters, as rolling towards it will likely result taking the full blast of the spell head-on.\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
