{"id": "133829", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133829", "title": "Great Wooden Hammer", "text": "The Great Wooden Hammer is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Peasant%20Hollow\"&gt;Peasant Hollow&lt;/a&gt;s who wield them in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irithyll Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nDespite its comical appearance, the Great Wooden Hammer is a very unique weapon that occupies a very unique niche.\nCompared to other great hammers, this weapon comes up woefully inadequate, as it possesses poor &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and as a result inflicts far less physical damage than its heavier brothers. However, it requires the least amount of Strength to wield of all great hammers, weighs less than a &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and consumes far less &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; per swing than everything short of the &lt;a href=\"Pickaxe%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Pickaxe&lt;/a&gt;, while still possessing the same &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; health and inflicting the same Poise damage of a great hammer. As well, it is one of two great hammers that possess the &lt;a href=\"Spin%20Bash\"&gt;Spin Bash&lt;/a&gt; skill, allowing it to be used in ways that other great hammers cannot.\nCombined with the above strengths, the Great Wooden Hammer can also still be &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infused&lt;/a&gt;. This means that it can be used as a large Poise weapon on builds that have not greatly leveled Strength or &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;; namely, elemental melee builds.\nMoveset.\n&lt;br&gt;\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
