{"id": "34026", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34026", "title": "Greataxe (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greataxe, while rather standard, can prove to be a rather solid and efficient &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. It has the lowest &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement of the greataxes that have the heavy greataxe moveset, as well as the lowest &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, making it much easier to wield for lower level builds. It has the highest &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; of all the greataxe-class weapons, being tied with the &lt;a href=\"Gyrm%20Greataxe\"&gt;Gyrm Greataxe&lt;/a&gt; at 80. Although the &lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper%27s%20Greataxe\"&gt;Drakekeeper's Greataxe&lt;/a&gt; has longer reach and better &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;, the standard Greataxe is made available much earlier in the game and has the same moveset."}
{"id": "130276", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130276", "title": "Greataxe (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Greataxe is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;\nCharacteristics.\nWhat the Greataxe lacks in reach, it makes up with sheer damage. Fully upgraded, it can easily surpass 700 attack damage using Warcry.\nThe Greataxe's very low Dexterity requirement and early availability make it a promising choice for strength-focused builds. It is also relatively light for its class. \nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
