{"id": "3146", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3146", "title": "Greataxes", "text": "Greataxes are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nGreataxes are among the heaviest weapons in the game. Correspondingly, they also have some of the highest &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirements in order to wield them. Each swing with these large weapons requires large amounts of &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;, but this power not only delivers heavy damage, but also breaks through blocking or guarding through shields quite easily. Most greataxes have the weakness of having very high ending lag to their attacks, making wielders easy to punish. Their arc also isn't as wide as a normal &lt;a href=\"Axes\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt;, focusing instead on generating the maximum force possible in the area they do cover.\nGreataxes.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52284", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52284", "title": "Greataxes (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Greataxes are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "133856", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133856", "title": "Greataxes (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Greataxes are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOne of the three classes of ultra weapons, greataxes are characterized by their heavy &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, hefty &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; cost and slow swing speed, in exchange for providing strong &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; and high damage output. Like other ultra weapons, they benefit greatly from investing heavily in &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;.\nAmong all ultra weapons, greataxes have a mundane moveset and the least range, but make up for this by inflicting the most damage. As well, like &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;great hammers&lt;/a&gt; their vertical swings can inflict stagger on foes in an area around the impact point, making this weapon difficult to space against even by skilled opponents. As the big brother to the &lt;a href=\"Axes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; weapon class, several greataxes also possess the &lt;a href=\"Warcry\"&gt;Warcry&lt;/a&gt; skill, allowing them to amplify their already high damage output to extreme levels.\nGreataxes.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
