{"id": "133861", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133861", "title": "Greatbows (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Greatbows are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCompared to normal &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt;, greatbows are heavier and have considerably greater &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; requirements, along with a much slower fire rate, however they more than make up for it with their tremendous damage output. Their shots, when using the proper &lt;a href=\"Ammunition%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatarrows&lt;/a&gt;, are capable of knocking down foes if they connect.\nUnlike bows and &lt;a href=\"Crossbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;crossbows&lt;/a&gt;, greatbows cannot be fired while moving, requiring the wielder to remain stationary. Because the player is required to hold the greatbow with both hands to fire, the &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement is effectively only 66% of the displayed value. All greatbows have a zoom feature that allows the user to get a closer look at their aim point. As with normal bows and crossbows, &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt; can be increased by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "132997", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132997", "title": "Greatlance", "text": "The Greatlance is a &lt;a href=\"Pikes\"&gt;pike&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Barracks\"&gt;Dragon Barracks&lt;/a&gt;, go upstairs and head left to find the Greatlance guarded by a red-eyed &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Knight\"&gt;Lothric Knight&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe strong attacks have the ability to hit enemies multiple times. The lance's general feature of each attack advancing the player forward can be used to punish retreating players, however, due to the buildup before each strike, the greatlance is easily avoided and dodged in most scenarios, making it inadequate for &lt;a href=\"PvP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor PvP, if you can land a weak attack while two-handing or using a &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; allowing use for a &lt;a href=\"weapon%20art\"&gt;weapon art&lt;/a&gt; while one-handing, you can follow up the weak attack with the weapon art which hits multiple times.\nNotes.\nCan benefit from &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
