{"id": "3816", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3816", "title": "Greatshield of Artorias", "text": "The Greatshield of Artorias is a &lt;a href=\"greatshield\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Greatshield of Artorias can be created at the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; with a +10 &lt;a href=\"Shield\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Sif\"&gt;Soul of Sif&lt;/a&gt; and 5,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatshield of Artorias is arguably one of the best greatshields in the game, with the highest stability of any non-crystal shield combined with complete &lt;a href=\"status\"&gt;status&lt;/a&gt; resistance.\nHowever, it has underwhelming &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; defenses and is the fourth heaviest shield in the game.\nResistance defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status build-up while blocking.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;Upgrading&lt;/a&gt; the shield will only improve its damage characteristics."}
{"id": "67533", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67533", "title": "Greatshield of Glory", "text": "The Greatshield of Glory\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Greatshield of Glory can be obtained as a drop from the warpick and greatshield wielding\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Drakekeeper\"&gt;Drakekeeper&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Shrine\"&gt;Dragon Shrine&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatshield of Glory is an overall improvement to the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Tower Shield&lt;/a&gt;, providing marginally stronger defenses in exchange for more weight, less &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, and a higher &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement. On the other hand, this greatshield has a very high resistance to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;, though the &lt;a href=\"Gyrm%20Greatshield\"&gt;Gyrm Greatshield&lt;/a&gt; will still outclass it in terms of stability coupled with its innate immunity (100% reduction) to fire damage.\nUnlike the Gyrm Greatshield, however, this shield possesses much more resilient elemental defenses and resistances, allowing it to be used in many more areas outside of fire-themed locations.\nInterestingly, the shield deals both physical and fire damage when used to bash enemies, yet the fire damage does not scale at all. It does, however, improve as it is upgraded.\nThe Greatshield of Glory upgrades with &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Shard%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;titanite&lt;/a&gt;, up to +10."}
{"id": "134866", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134866", "title": "Greatshield of Glory (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Greatshield of Glory is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by a &lt;a href=\"Mimic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt;, in the treasury room to the right of &lt;a href=\"Yhorm%20the%20Giant\"&gt;Yhorm the Giant&lt;/a&gt;'s boss arena.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatshield of Glory is a titan of a greatshield that is renowned for being extremely difficult to penetrate.\nBoasting the highest stability in the game, it is capable of shrugging off most attacks with minimal stamina damage. This makes it particularly tough, even among greatshields, as it allows its wielder to absorb numerous consecutive attacks and then be able to retaliate once the opponent has exhausted their stamina. Its elemental resistances are respectable for the most part, being able to block &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; attacks particularly well.\nHowever, the drawback of this greatshield, beyond its massive &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; wielding requirement, is that while equipped it reduces stamina regeneration by 20 points per second, effectively halving it from the default 45 points per second. This can prove to be a fatal flaw should the wielder exhaust their stamina while blocking attacks, as it will take twice as much time to recover stamina, and smart opponents can exploit this weakness by stacking numerous stamina debuffs, such as &lt;a href=\"Impact\"&gt;Impact&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Frost\"&gt;Frost&lt;/a&gt;, to render the wielder helpless. This means that in order to mitigate this flaw, it may be necessary to commit a ring slot to a &lt;a href=\"Chloranthy%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Chloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt; and to actively consume &lt;a href=\"Green%20Blossom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Green Blossoms&lt;/a&gt; while using this shield.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "6040", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6040", "title": "Greatshields", "text": "Greatshields are a type of &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nGreatshields differ from their &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;lighter&lt;/a&gt; counterparts, predominantly in that they trade the ability to &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; for a shield bash. Shield bashes are good for stunning enemies and still partially block attacks, making them good against relentless hordes of enemies. However, their lack of parrying ability makes them a poor choice for &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;. They can be highly effective against bosses, most of which hit hard and are impossible to parry.\nGreatshields usually come with better defensive values and stability than small and medium shields, but at the cost of greater weight. They also all have heavy deflection.\nGreatshields.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "67545", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67545", "title": "Greatshields (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Greatshields are a type of &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nGreatshields are the largest and &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heaviest&lt;/a&gt; of the shields, but provide the most defense in return. Greatshields trade the ability to &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; in return for a heavy shield bash.\nGreatshields.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "133638", "revid": "340561", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133638", "title": "Greatshields (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Greatshields are a type of &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGreatshields are characterized by their immense &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, high &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement, and extremely strong defenses. Because of their high weight, most greatshields will require the wielder to invest not only in Strength, but also &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt; to fortify their &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; pool. However, properly wielded, a greatshield will easily protect the player from most forms of damage from all but the strongest of foes. Greatshields are incapable of performing &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parries&lt;/a&gt;, and instead allow the wielder to &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Bash\"&gt;Shield Bash&lt;/a&gt; their foes, or perform the &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Skill\"&gt;Weapon Skill&lt;/a&gt; of their right-hand weapon without having to two-hand it.\nBecause of their innately high &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, upgrading a greatshield is crucial, as increasing their already strong stability will allow them to virtually ignore the stamina damage dealt by smaller weapons."}
{"id": "5129", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5129", "title": "Greatsword", "text": "The Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatsword is very similar to the &lt;a href=\"Zweihander\"&gt;Zweihander&lt;/a&gt;, having identical base damage, scaling, reach, and a mostly similar moveset. However, the Greatsword requires four extra strength to use and weighs two units more. In turn, it also gains the ability to thrust with its strong attacks, as opposed to the Zweihander's overhead swings.\nContrary to popular belief, Greatsword is NOT a \"Strength Weapon\" but is a \"Quality\" Scaling weapon meaning it scales near equally off &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; and will be at its full potential at the relevant stat softcaps. \nThe thrust attacks have the advantage of dealing &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage, which is usually more damaging than a &lt;a href=\"Regular%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;regular&lt;/a&gt; attack with the same attack rating. The attack is relatively fast, and has a good range, allowing it to be used somewhat like a heavy version of the &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;. It works well for counterattacks, and when combined with the &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;, can be absolutely devastating. However, the thrust attack doesn't deal as much poise damage as the Zweihander's strong attack, meaning heavily armored foes may become more troublesome to deal with.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "46905", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46905", "title": "Greatsword (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatsword is a fairly powerful weapon for a &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; build. Unfortunately, because the weapon weighs in at 22.0 units, it is also exceptionally heavy, making it difficult to use effectively at lower levels.\u00a0\nWith broad swipes and immense power, its strong attacks can knock down multiple enemies with ease. It also can stagger opponents easily because of its very high poise damage, making it an exceptional weapon for crowd control situations. However, this weapon swings slowly and suffers from a large stamina cost for each swing, as is common of all ultra greatswords.\nBecause of its higher STR scaling bonus and heavy weight, this weapon is ideal for STR-based builds."}
{"id": "130280", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130280", "title": "Greatsword (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Greatsword is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, on top of one of the two broken bridge sections, near the area with the first brazier and opposite to some &lt;a href=\"Purple%20Moss%20Clump%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Purple Moss Clumps&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatsword is an extreme ultra greatsword, giving up versatility and efficiency for sheer size and raw power. Its overhead swings reach high above the wielder, and its horizontal attacks cover a large area in front of the wielder. The Greatsword also features a low &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirement of 10 and the highest potential attack rating of all &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Gem\"&gt;Heavy&lt;/a&gt;-infused ultra greatswords, lending itself well to &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; builds looking to overpower their enemies. Its high base damage also lends itself well to the non-scaling &lt;a href=\"Deep%20Gem\"&gt;Deep&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Gem\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; infusions, although &lt;a href=\"Raw%20Gem\"&gt;Raw&lt;/a&gt; is always outperformed by Heavy.\nHowever, it is the third heaviest ultra greatsword in the game at 20 &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; units, and its two-handed attacks can be difficult to use against nimble opponents, as the vertical nature of the light attacks make them relatively easy to avoid.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with ."}
