{"id": "94085", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=94085", "title": "Greatsword Phantom", "text": "The Greatsword Phantom is a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt; in .\nAppearance.\nThe Greatsword Phantom wields a &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Orma%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Orma's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, and wears the &lt;a href=\"Llewellyn%20Set\"&gt;Llewellyn Set&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Helm\"&gt;Drangleic Helm&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe also notably has the red aura of high-ranking members of the &lt;a href=\"Brotherhood%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Brotherhood of Blood&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nThe Greatsword Phantom stands guard in front of the fog door to the &lt;a href=\"Executioner%27s%20Chariot\"&gt;Executioner's Chariot&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nThe Greatsword Phantom is a very dangerous enemy, especially for newer players who are unaware of his location outside the boss area. His &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Greatsword&lt;/a&gt; offers him a lot of range and inflicts heavy damage should he manage to hit the player. He will try to sweep at the player if they go around him. This dark spirit does roll often, even if not being engaged by the player, and his attack patterns are very erratic, making him a dangerous opponent.\nDespite having a greatshield, he rarely uses it to block, occasionally even preferring to ignore it entirely and two-hand his Greatsword.\nAn easy way to defeat him (especially for low level players) is to bring enough &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Throwing Knives&lt;/a&gt; and follow these steps:"}
{"id": "4991", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4991", "title": "Greatsword of Artorias", "text": " \nThe Greatsword of Artorias is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Greatsword of Artorias can be created by &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;ascending&lt;/a&gt; a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Sword%20Hilt\"&gt;Straight Sword Hilt&lt;/a&gt; +10 or a &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Straight%20Sword\"&gt;Broken Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt; +10 at the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, with the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Sif\"&gt;Soul of Sif&lt;/a&gt; and 5,000 &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s.\nUsing the Soul of Sif with any other &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Daggers\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt;, will create the &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20of%20Artorias%20%28Cursed%29\"&gt;Cursed&lt;/a&gt; variant.\nCharacteristics.\nIt has the highest &lt;a href=\"Divine%20%28Auxiliary%20Effect%29\"&gt;Divine&lt;/a&gt; modifier of any weapon at 140 and due to this &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeletons&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;The Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; will not reassemble when killed with it even if the Necromancers are still alive as well as the ones in &lt;a href=\"Gravelord%20Nito\"&gt;Gravelord Nito's&lt;/a&gt; boss arena in &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;. The Greatsword of Artorias also has a unique 20% damage modifier against the \"servants of dark\". These include &lt;a href=\"Darkwraith%20%28enemy%29\"&gt;Darkwraiths&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Four%20Kings\"&gt;Four Kings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kirk%2C%20Knight%20of%20Thorns\"&gt;Kirk, Knight of Thorns&lt;/a&gt;, and if they were able to be killed &lt;a href=\"Kingseeker%20Frampt\"&gt;Frampt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Darkstalker%20Kaathe\"&gt;Kaathe&lt;/a&gt;. For this it uses a 1.2x &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Damage modifier&lt;/a&gt; applied after defense calculations. Unlike the Cursed version, this one does receive scaling with Intelligence and Faith.\nRequiring 24/18/20/20 in four different stats means most builds will not likely be able to wield it. Due to its split in AR, even with scaling from high levels in higher game cycles, its damage and DPS are out damaged by many &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;enchantable&lt;/a&gt; weapons with significantly lower necessary investment.\nIn the German translation, this sword is called \"Finstert\u00f6ter\" (Darkslayer) while the Cursed version is called \"Gro\u00dfschwert von Artorias\" (Greatsword of Artorias)."}
{"id": "4992", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4992", "title": "Greatsword of Artorias (Cursed)", "text": "The Greatsword of Artorias is the Cursed version of the &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;Greatsword of Artorias&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". In-game, it is displayed as \"Greatsword of Artorias\".\nAvailability.\nThe cursed Greatsword of Artorias can be created by &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;ascending&lt;/a&gt; any &lt;a href=\"Standard%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;standard&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0+10 &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Daggers\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; (with the exception of the &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Sword%20Hilt\"&gt;Straight Sword Hilt&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Straight%20Sword\"&gt;Broken Straight Sword&lt;/a&gt;) at the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Sif\"&gt;Soul of Sif&lt;/a&gt; and 5,000 &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Cursed variant of the Greatsword of Artorias has the &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; effect, which allows it to hit the &lt;a href=\"Ghost\"&gt;Ghost&lt;/a&gt;s and block their attacks when in &lt;a href=\"New%20Londo%20Ruins\"&gt;New Londo Ruins&lt;/a&gt;. This variant shares the same &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; as the true version, &lt;a href=\"Greatsword%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;Greatsword of Artorias&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen ascending the weapon, it will only be displayed as \"Greatsword of Artorias\", it will not say \"cursed\". To be certain of which sword is already created and which is being created, look at the stats which are unique. Despite having Intelligence and Faith scaling values present, the weapon does not receive any damage bonus from them. To wield the sword effectively however, users must meet both requirements. Requiring 24/18/18/18 in stats means most builds will not likely be able to wield it effectively, since at least one of the four is usually not invested in. In particular, few builds tend to invest 18 in both Intelligence and Faith.\nIn the German translation, this sword is called \"Gro\u00dfschwert von Artorias\" (Greatsword of Artorias), while the non-cursed version is called \"Finstert\u00f6ter\" (Darkslayer)."}
{"id": "131432", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131432", "title": "Greatsword of Judgment", "text": "The Greatsword of Judgment is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nTranspose the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Soul of Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt; for 3,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatsword of Judgment is a peculiar greatsword that is useful for builds that level &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, but not beyond 40 for any. Because its damage scales with all three stats, it is capable of dealing split damage, making it a good weapon for fighting shield-equipped opponents.\nUtilizing the &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; moveset, the Greatsword of Judgment specializes in horizontal and vertical swings and as a result can be lacking in reach. However, these wide swings also give it strong area coverage, allowing it to clear crowds with the horizontal swings and hit overhead targets with the vertical swings. Use of a weak attack from the &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;'s stance also gives it the ability to perform a thrust attack, covering the weakness in its standard moveset.\nWhile it cannot be buffed by spells or resins, &lt;a href=\"Stance%20of%20Judgment\"&gt;Stance of Judgment&lt;/a&gt; allows the player to temporarily increase the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage it deals for a time after performing a powerful attack. While this buff adds less damage and persists for a shorter duration than a properly built &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Magic%20Weapon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Crystal Magic Weapon&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Darkmoon%20Blade%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Darkmoon Blade&lt;/a&gt;, the buff is integrated into the special attacks from the stance, and thus can be activated quickly in the midst of battle while also inflicting strong damage against a foe with the attack itself. This gives the Stance of Judgment an advantage over standard buffs due to the speed with which it can be applied, lack of requirement of an &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot, and comparatively low &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; cost. As well, this buff is applied on top of existing Magic damage, which is otherwise not possible in any case outside of buffing a &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Greatsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Drakeblood Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;.\nDue to the high FP cost of the skill, investment into Attunement and equipping an off-hand &lt;a href=\"Simple%20Gem\"&gt;Simple&lt;/a&gt;-infused weapon/shield may be useful."}
{"id": "128553", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=128553", "title": "Greatsword of the Forlorn", "text": "The Greatsword of the Forlorn is a &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatsword&lt;/a&gt; exclusive to \"\".\nAvailability.\nPurchased from &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt; for 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;, once five or more &lt;a href=\"Forlorn\"&gt;Forlorn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"dark%20spirit\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt;s are defeated, with the fifth, or latter, being a greatsword-wielder. The Forlorn found in &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt; do not count, as they are not invaders.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Greatsword of the Forlorn is a very potent &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;, with the ability to deal massive damage in three different ways.\nThe weapon deals a great deal of both &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; damage, as well as a good amount of &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt;. This makes the weapon useful against most foes.\nThe weapon's main mechanic is that it, similarly to the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Pyromancy%20Flame\"&gt;Dark Pyromancy Flame&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Scythe%20of%20the%20Forlorn\"&gt;Scythe of the Forlorn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scaling%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scales&lt;/a&gt; with how &lt;a href=\"Hollowing%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hollow&lt;/a&gt; the player is. In human form, it will have an extremely low attack rating, while it will have a slightly above-average damage output when fully hollowed.\nIts &lt;a href=\"Moveset%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; is similar to that of the &lt;a href=\"Charred%20Loyce%20Greatsword\"&gt;Charred Loyce Greatsword&lt;/a&gt;; however, two-handed light attacks are standard greatsword swings.\nThe Greatsword also has a very interesting interaction with some &lt;a href=\"infusion\"&gt;infusion&lt;/a&gt;s. Infusing the weapon with &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Stone\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; will give the weapon poison damage without reducing any base damage stats. However, physical scaling is still reduced, although the Dark scaling will be boosted to a B. Infusing the weapon with &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20Stone\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; will actually give a small \"increase\" to all base damage, with the Bleed damage receiving a much larger boost. The scaling will take a similar effect to poison infusions, however. Infusing the weapon with &lt;a href=\"Darknight%20Stone\"&gt;dark&lt;/a&gt; will only grant a C scaling, but due to matching the innate Dark damage, the player will get considerably more scaling out of this C than the B scaling the status infusions provide."}
