{"id": "31219", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31219", "title": "Guardian's Seal", "text": "The Guardian's Seal is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGiven to the player by &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinel%20Targray\"&gt;Blue Sentinel Targray&lt;/a&gt; upon joining the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Sentinels\"&gt;Blue Sentinels&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nMuch like the &lt;a href=\"Bell%20Keeper%27s%20Seal\"&gt;Bell Keeper's Seal&lt;/a&gt;, wearing the Guardian's Seal allows the player to automatically come to the aid of invaded &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Way of Blue&lt;/a&gt; members. The player must be human to be summoned."}
{"id": "8283", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8283", "title": "Guardian Armor", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Guardian Armor is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Set\"&gt;Guardian Set&lt;/a&gt;, and is only available in the \"&lt;a href=\"AotA\"&gt;AotA&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC.\nCharacteristics.\nOffers very high defense, resistance and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; at the cost of very high &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. It is comparable to &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Armor\"&gt;Havel's Armor&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "46075", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46075", "title": "Guardian Dragon", "text": "The\u00a0Guardian Dragon is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nDescription.\nA thin red drake trapped in a cage in &lt;a href=\"Aldia%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Aldia's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. Three are later encountered as non-respawning enemies in &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aerie\"&gt;Dragon Aerie&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnly in : There is one at &lt;a href=\"Heide%27s%20Tower%20of%20Flame\"&gt;Heide's Tower of Flame&lt;/a&gt;, in front of the drawbridge leading into the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Cathedral of Blue&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe \"Guardian Dragon\" is a wyvern that guards the way to &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Aerie\"&gt;Dragon Aerie&lt;/a&gt;. Thanks to his experiments and magic, &lt;a href=\"Aldia%2C%20Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Aldia&lt;/a&gt; learned how to control wyverns, commanding this subject to act as a guardian and closing it inside a improvised cage located between his Keep and the Aerie. \nIn the ruins of Heide, another \"Guardian Dragon\" can be found guarding the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Blue\"&gt;Cathedral of Blue&lt;/a&gt;. It is possible that it is the mount of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonrider\"&gt;Dragonrider&lt;/a&gt; who resides nearby in Heide, the elite knights of Vendrick who once rode earth dragons and that would mount wyverns after Aldia learned to control them.\nSummoning.\nIn , &lt;a href=\"Sellsword%20Luet\"&gt;Sellsword Luet&lt;/a&gt; can be summoned from the bottom level of the large room with the dragon skeleton.\nStrategy.\nThis boss isn't too complex. Most of its melee attacks are not much of a threat. Its most dangerous attacks involve its fire breath, which has a large area of effect. Staying underneath it while it is on the ground is a good tactic, as it has only one attack that can reach you there, and it is easily dodged.\nAs it is a dragon, it is weak to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt;. Make use of this weakness and the battle won't last for very long.\nThe Guardian Dragons in the Aerie will receive power boosts if the player destroys the eggs around the area. They will also become more aggressive and will attack on sight. If the player wishes to fight the dragons but has already broken several eggs, it is advisable to rest at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. This will respawn the eggs and reset the dragons' attack power to normal.\nIn this battle, mobility is better than toughness. Being able to run away at anytime from its fire attack beats trying to shield &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, and getting run down on &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;.\nAttacks.\nStomp: The dragon attempts to hit the player with its foot. Easy to dodge out of the way.\nBite: The dragon lowers its head and bites to the side. &lt;a href=\"Rolling\"&gt;Rolling&lt;/a&gt; under its body is a good method.\nTail Swipe: The dragon swipes its long tail twice behind it. Roll underneath it, as it may still hit you if you go to its side.\nGround Fire Breath: The dragon lowers its head and breathes a stream of fire towards the player. Deadly if it connects, but if not, then it offers a very good chance to wail on the dragon as it cannot do anything while this attack is in process.\nAerial Fireball: The dragon flies into the air and launches a single fireball at the player. Does a pretty good amount of damage and has a fair area of effect. Snap out of your lock on and sprint as far away from the dragon as soon as he flies up.\nAerial Fire Breath: The dragon flies up in the air and breathes fire at the ground. this fire radiates over a long range. Snap out of your lock on and run away from the fire.\nAerial Turning Fire Breath: The dragon flies up in the air and breathes fire around the arena while turning. Snap out of your lock on and run away from the fire.\nGrounded Sweeping Fire Breath: Breathes fire from right to left. Difficult to avoid.\nDiagonal Fire Breath: Clings to the wall and breathes fire in a non-sweeping diagonal direction.\nDefenses.\nGuardian Dragon (boss)\n (Stats are from Param Studio and are not estimated)&lt;br&gt;Strike/Slash/Thrust defense are applied on top of Physical Defense.\nMusic.\n&lt;embedvideo service=\"youtube\" alignment=\"center\" description=\"Dark Souls 2 \u2014 Guardian Dragon by \"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MHTZNpd6SSA&lt;/embedvideo&gt;"}
