{"id": "111299", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=111299", "title": "Gyrm", "text": "The Gyrm are &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nGyrm are found in the &lt;a href=\"Doors%20of%20Pharros\"&gt;Doors of Pharros&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe stocky Gyrm are kind-natured, but &lt;a href=\"humans\"&gt;humans&lt;/a&gt; deemed them impure and drove them underground.\nStrategy.\nAlthough small, the Gyrm fight with vicious force. They wield flails that they swing like whips and can combo up to three swings in a row. Due to their small size, they can be easily stun-locked. This can be used to gain a significant advantage over them.\nThey are often found in a sitting position, facing away from the player's path. This, combined with their poor hearing, makes them very susceptible to &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;s."}
