{"id": "52487", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52487", "title": "Gyrm Great Hammer", "text": "The Gyrm Great Hammer\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nCommon drop from the &lt;a href=\"Gyrm%20Warrior\"&gt;Gyrm Warrior&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Doors%20of%20Pharros\"&gt;Doors of Pharros&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Gyrm Great Hammer is a strong great hammer. Compared to the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Tooth%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dragon Tooth&lt;/a&gt; that has the same weight, it has the same attack rating, but much shorter range and does not have the unique bonus defense. In fact, it is the shortest great hammer in the game.\nWhat makes this great hammer useful is it's moveset, which helps dealing more &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; damage than many other great hammer."}
{"id": "52399", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52399", "title": "Gyrm Greataxe", "text": "The Gyrm Greataxe\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Greataxes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greataxe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Gyrm Greataxe is the strongest physical greataxe due to its high scaling, gaining an A in its Strength scaling from +2 onwards. However, this comes at the cost of being the second heaviest weight in the weapon type and the highest Strength requirement, which also makes it nigh impossible to use in a &lt;a href=\"Power%20Stance\"&gt;Power Stance&lt;/a&gt; unless at very high levels. It is also quite short. \nThe light attacks are unique compared to other axes, as the one-handed ones are slightly quicker horizontal slashes instead of side-to-side smashes while the two-handed ones unexpectedly have a slight, peculiar upward tilt. "}
{"id": "62025", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=62025", "title": "Gyrm Greatshield", "text": "The Gyrm Greatshield\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nMay be dropped by &lt;a href=\"Gyrm%20Warrior\"&gt;Gyrm Warrior&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Doors%20of%20Pharros\"&gt;Doors of Pharros&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nBecause of its innate immunity (100% reduction) to both &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, as well as possessing very high &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, this shield sees heavy use against enemies and bosses that deal those two damage types, such as the &lt;a href=\"Smelter%20Demon\"&gt;Smelter Demon&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Dragon\"&gt;Guardian Dragon&lt;/a&gt;.\nOutside of this, the shield is a poor choice against anything other than that, as its other &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; defenses and resistances are underwhelming, even when fully-reinforced."}
