{"id": "77556", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=77556", "title": "Gyrm Set", "text": "The Gyrm Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Gyrm Set is the heaviest medium armor set available in the game, topping off at a &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; of 29.7 units, surpassing the weight of both the &lt;a href=\"Drakeblood%20Set\"&gt;Drakeblood Set&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Benhart%27s%20Set\"&gt;Benhart's Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt first glance, this set appears to be rather redundant in most regards, as many players are often thrown off at the very low &lt;a href=\"elemental%20defense\"&gt;elemental defense&lt;/a&gt;s the set provides; this set is ill-advised to be used against mages and the like, but players can mitigate this somewhat with the use of the &lt;a href=\"Dispelling%20Ring\"&gt;Dispelling Ring&lt;/a&gt; (+1) or &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Barrier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic Barrier&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Great%20Magic%20Barrier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Magic Barrier&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, where this set shines is in the amount of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;; it provides the highest amount of Poise out of all the medium armor sets, even besting the amount provided by the lighter &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;heavy armor sets&lt;/a&gt;. It also has a resistance to every &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;auxiliary effect&lt;/a&gt; present in the game, most notably its unusually high resistance to &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;, and very high &lt;a href=\"physical%20defense\"&gt;physical defense&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "67244", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67244", "title": "Gyrm Warrior", "text": "Gyrm Warriors are enemies in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nMost Gyrm descendants refuse contact with outsiders and live with a sense of deep contempt for those who exiled them.\nLocation.\nGyrm Warriors are found in the &lt;a href=\"Doors%20of%20Pharros\"&gt;Doors of Pharros&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nThese warriors are slow, but they hit hard. Most of the time they will block rather than attack; this makes them vulnerable to guard breaking. They are also very easy to backstab after performing their overhead strikes and are easy to stagger. Their health pool is in a medium range.\nAttacks.\nDouble Strike: Performs a double overhead strike.\nAxe Throw: Throws two axes consecutively."}
