{"id": "3922", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3922", "title": "Halberd", "text": "The Halberd is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Halberd can be obtained in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Parish\"&gt;Undead Parish&lt;/a&gt; to the left of the front doors at the Undead Church on a corpse. A &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; Halberd can be found early in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, obtained off a &lt;a href=\"Mimic\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Halberd combines ranged &lt;a href=\"thrust\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; attacks with wide sweeps. However, the vertical hit-boxes of its thrust attacks are small, sometimes going under tall &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es if not aimed right. Halberd is a \"Quality\" Scaling weapons meaning that it scales near equally off of &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; and will be its best at 27 Strength and 40 Dexterity while two-handed.\nThis weapon deals &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; and can be boosted by the &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt; for an increase to its &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Counter_Damage\"&gt;Counter Damage&lt;/a&gt; Bonus. Like all &lt;a href=\"Halberds\"&gt;Halberds&lt;/a&gt;, if an attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal making this weapon capable of gaining &lt;a href=\"https%3A//darksouls.fandom.com/wiki/Damage_%28Dark_Souls%29%23Sweet_Spot_Damage_Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; damage bonus. \nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "54704", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54704", "title": "Halberd (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Halberd is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nDespite lacking any major qualities, it is, in essence, a starting weapon. Easy to use, lightweight and with low requirements, though with very solid damage, it is nothing special, yet it is not bad either.\nIt is also rather long, and while this can be a boon for players who like to fight from afar; the weapon will deal much less damage if the shaft connects with the opponent, making it less effective if not used at the proper range."}
{"id": "134112", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134112", "title": "Halberd (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Halberd is a &lt;a href=\"Halberds%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;\nCharacteristics.\nThe archetype of the weapon class, the Halberd is a basic tool that can be effective in the right hands.\nAs it utilizes the thrusting halberd moveset, the Halberd's basic attacks inflict &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage, which can deal increased damage if a &lt;a href=\"Counter%20Attack\"&gt;Counter Attack&lt;/a&gt; can be achieved. These thrusting attacks with the heavy bladed head also have uncommon hitstun properties, sometimes allowing the wielder to consecutively hit a target more than twice. However, unlike most other weapons in its class, these thrusting attacks cannot benefit from &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt;, meaning that the wielder must be patient and wield the weapon more akin to a &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt;, keeping foes at the weapon's maximum reach whenever possible.\nCompared to the only other thrusting halberd in the game, the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Hilted%20Halberd\"&gt;Red Hilted Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, the normal Halberd possesses different &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; values as well as a different &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;. Whereas the Red Hilted Halberd can perform &lt;a href=\"Perseverance%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt; and engage foes head-on, the normal Halberd possesses a &lt;a href=\"Charge\"&gt;Charge&lt;/a&gt; attack that can be useful for &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; trades or for running down fleeing targets. In terms of damage, the Red Hilted Halberd is stronger when it comes to &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;infusions&lt;/a&gt; that enhance physical attributes, particularly the &lt;a href=\"Sharp%20Gem\"&gt;Sharp&lt;/a&gt; infusion. However, when infused down the elemental path such as with a &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Gem\"&gt;Lightning Gem&lt;/a&gt;, the normal Halberd has superior performance.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Shard%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3149", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3149", "title": "Halberds", "text": "Halberds are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nHalberds offer a mixture of the &lt;a href=\"spears\"&gt;spears&lt;/a&gt;' range and &lt;a href=\"thrust\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt;ing attacks, along with a bladed edge similar to an &lt;a href=\"Axes\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; for attacks that deal &lt;a href=\"Regular\"&gt;Regular&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Slash\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage. Because of the increased weight at the end of the weapon, however, the attacks are not quite as precise as they are with a Spear, and each swing tends to take one slightly off balance. Most of the spears' quick strikes are lost too, in favor of slower, but slightly more powerful attacks. The ability to use a variety of attack types at range, however, can be a very useful thing, as it enables one to be effective against most types of enemies.\nAll halberds besides the &lt;a href=\"Scythe\"&gt;Scythe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Great%20Scythe\"&gt;Great Scythe&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lifehunt%20Scythe\"&gt;Lifehunt Scythe&lt;/a&gt; deal &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage on their weak attacks and are therefore eligible for &lt;a href=\"Counter%20Attack\"&gt;counter attack&lt;/a&gt; bonuses.\nHalberds.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52288", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52288", "title": "Halberds (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Halberds are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "133857", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133857", "title": "Halberds (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Halberds are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nA special type of polearm, halberds possess sweeping attacks combined with long range to give their attacks strong coverage and reach. With the exception of attacks that perform thrusting attacks, they can also take advantage of &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt;, meaning that &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; will allow them to engage foes inside of the arc of their blades. However, like other polearms, halberds will deal reduced damage to targets that are not hit by the head of the weapon itself.\nHalberd &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;s are divided into two general categories, those with sweeping weak attacks and those with thrusting weak attacks. However, in practice, only two halberds possess the thrusting moveset, the &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Hilted%20Halberd\"&gt;Red Hilted Halberd&lt;/a&gt;. These thrusting halberds have the advantage of attacks that inflict &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage and thus benefit from &lt;a href=\"Counter%20Attack\"&gt;Counter Attack&lt;/a&gt;s, however this is offset by their inability to utilize Hyper Armor with these thrusting attacks.\nHalberds.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "150043", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150043", "title": "Halflight", "text": ""}
{"id": "150046", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150046", "title": "Halflight, Spear of the Church", "text": "Halflight, Spear of the Church is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThe Spear of the Church is a unique boss and has a mechanic similar to that of the &lt;a href=\"Looking%20Glass%20Knight\"&gt;Looking Glass Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIf the player is offline, the fight functions very similar to most fights with NPCs. Halflight wields the &lt;a href=\"Frayed%20Blade\"&gt;Frayed Blade&lt;/a&gt; and makes frequent use of the &lt;a href=\"Ritual%20Spear%20Fragment\"&gt;Ritual Spear Fragment&lt;/a&gt;. Occasionally, magic orbs that function similar to &lt;a href=\"Homing%20Soulmass%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Homing Soulmass&lt;/a&gt; will appear around him, appearing more frequently if the player has more summons.\nIf the player is online, however, they will likely fight another player and the fight will effectively be a &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; match. However, this is not a duel, and the player summoned to be the boss will have increased defenses and the magic orbs will automatically appear around them through intervals of time. Similar to Halflight, the player will gain higher defense values and the magic orbs will appear more frequently the more summons the host has. The boss player also isn't capable of using their &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Estus Flasks&lt;/a&gt; to heal, but can use healing miracles.\nSummoned Church Guardians are weak against &lt;a href=\"Frost\"&gt;Frost&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; and resistant against &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt;. They also can't be rapported or allured. &lt;a href=\"Vow%20of%20Silence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vow of Silence&lt;/a&gt; is helpful while facing them, as it will block healing miracles.\nLocation.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;, inside the &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29%23bonfires\"&gt;Church of Filianore&lt;/a&gt;, just after the &lt;a href=\"Darkeater%20Midir\"&gt;Darkeater Midir&lt;/a&gt; encounter at the bridge past the &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City%20%28location%29%23bonfires\"&gt;Shared Grave&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Spear of the Church is a servant of &lt;a href=\"Judicator%20Argo\"&gt;Judicator Argo&lt;/a&gt;, and works to preserve &lt;a href=\"Filianore\"&gt;Filianore&lt;/a&gt;'s slumber. One of the last recorded warrior among them was a young man named Halflight, a former missionary from an ancient land of sorcery, who decided to stay behind and defend the church.\nStrategy.\nWhile the player enters boss fight arena, &lt;a href=\"Judicator%20Argo\"&gt;Judicator Argo&lt;/a&gt; will give a speech about violating &lt;a href=\"Filianore\"&gt;Filianore&lt;/a&gt;'s slumber, which gives player enough time to buff weapon or cast spells. A few second later the first Church Guardian appears (second, when Spear of the Church hp is lowered by 40-45 percent). After ending this speech, Argo vanishes and Spear of Church appears (or Halflight, if Argo fails to summon player on time or player, which tries to break &lt;a href=\"Filianore\"&gt;Filianore&lt;/a&gt;'s slumber, is offline). \nSummons.\n&lt;a href=\"Unbreakable%20Patches\"&gt;Unbreakable Patches&lt;/a&gt;: After completing &lt;a href=\"Amnesiac%20Lapp\"&gt;Amnesiac Lapp's questline&lt;/a&gt;, he can be summoned for the fight. His summon sign is located behind the right door of the cathedral."}
