{"id": "5249", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5249", "title": "Hammer of Vamos", "text": "The Hammer of Vamos is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Vamos\"&gt;Vamos&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"the%20Catacombs\"&gt;the Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; upon death, along with his &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Helm\"&gt;Royal Helm&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nAn overall poor weapon. It is heavier than most hammers, with no extra range. It deals mainly &lt;a href=\"Strike\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt; damage and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage. Unfortunately, factoring in the split AR, the weapon's Attack Rating and practical damage will still be lower than that of almost every other weapon in the &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Hammer&lt;/a&gt; category. \nLike all &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Hammers&lt;/a&gt;, if an attack doesn't connect with an enemy, the user will stumble and seem to not be able to handle the weight. If the hit connects, the stumble animation does not come into play and the user moves as normal. This animation means that this Hammer gains &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Dark%20Souls%29%23Sweet%2520Spot%2520Damage%2520Bonus\"&gt;Sweet Spot&lt;/a&gt; Damage bonus.\nUpgrades.\n Damage bonus."}
{"id": "141201", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=141201", "title": "Hammers", "text": ""}
{"id": "3150", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3150", "title": "Hammers (Dark Souls)", "text": "Hammers are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nHammers are an interesting group of weapons in that they mostly deal &lt;a href=\"Strike%20Damage\"&gt;Strike Damage&lt;/a&gt;, along with two that deal &lt;a href=\"Thrust\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt;. They share similar attack animations with &lt;a href=\"Axes\"&gt;Axes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greataxes\"&gt;Greataxes&lt;/a&gt;, and their general usage is similar too. While hammers have \"slightly\" inferior attack rating compared to their axe counterpart, the damage type they deal means they tend to deal higher damage to armored opponents.\nThese weapons are designed for single hit damage rather than a quick succession of hits. This means their attacks are often quite labored and slow. On the other hand, hammers &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; opponents with relative ease. The sheer force of the blows also makes them very effective against highly defensive opponents, because it will not take long to break their guard.\nSuccessfully striking an opponent greatly reduces the ending lag of the blow, allowing the player to swing again relatively fast. Missing with a hammer will leave the player wide open though. The first strike is the most delicate, however, if it does connect, given the force of the blow and staggering power, it is almost always possible to follow it up with extra strikes, and potentially a &lt;a href=\"stun-lock\"&gt;stun-lock&lt;/a&gt;. Against turtling opponents, it is also possible to pound away at the &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; with relative ease.\nHammers.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52289", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52289", "title": "Hammers (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Hammers are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "133858", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133858", "title": "Hammers (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Hammers are a &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Types%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon type&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHammers are generally blunt weapons which inflict &lt;a href=\"strike\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"thrust\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage, depending on the specific weapon. They are the smallest-sized weapons which have &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; frames, allowing them to take advantage of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, though they are generally only effective at trading against similarly sized weapons. Offensively, they have moderate swing speed and crushing overhead strikes which are powerful for dealing with single targets, and they can deal Poise damage rivaling that of &lt;a href=\"Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Greatswords&lt;/a&gt;. Most Hammers, with the exception of the &lt;a href=\"Drang%20Hammers\"&gt;Drang Hammers&lt;/a&gt;, have relatively low &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; requirements, making them ideal for &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; builds.\nHammers.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
