{"id": "51898", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51898", "title": "Handmaid's Ladle", "text": "The Handmaid's Ladle is a &lt;a href=\"Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAfter defeating the two\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ogre\"&gt;Ogre&lt;/a&gt;s on the beach in &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things Betwixt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Milibeth%20the%20Housekeeper\"&gt;Milibeth the Housekeeper&lt;/a&gt; will give the player the Handmaiden's Ladle upon talking to her.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Handmaiden's Ladle is the weakest weapon in the game, dealing very little damage and featuring no\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt;. Its only benefits are its low &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; requirements and how early it may be obtained. The only reasons a player may wish to obtain it are:\nWhile unstated in the item's description, holding the Handmaiden's Ladle in hand increases &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt; by one level and &lt;a href=\"Adaptability\"&gt;Adaptability&lt;/a&gt; by two, while decreasing &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; by one level.\nIt can be given some power imbued with &lt;a href=\"Mundane\"&gt;Mundane&lt;/a&gt; with the correct build. To prevent breaking due to its low &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, wear the &lt;a href=\"Bracing%20Knuckle%20Ring\"&gt;Bracing Knuckle Ring&lt;/a&gt; or have a stock of &lt;a href=\"Repair%20Powder%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Repair Powder&lt;/a&gt;. Or ignore the durability, as only 10\u201320 points of damage are lost when broken."}
