{"id": "2992", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2992", "title": "Havel's Greatshield", "text": "Havel's Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"greatshield\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nHavel's Greatshield is found in a chest in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;, in the basement behind the &lt;a href=\"illusory%20wall\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt; in the fireplace, along with Havel's &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers\"&gt;Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Tooth\"&gt;Dragon Tooth&lt;/a&gt;, and other items.\nCharacteristics.\nHavel's Greatshield transforms the user into a living, near-impregnable wall. It also has heavy deflection. However, the &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; has a 50 &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement, and is very heavy. Only those with the highest Strength and &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt; will be able to wield this shield effectively.\nUsing the heavy attack on the shield will grant the user a temporary defensive buff similar to &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Flesh\"&gt;Iron Flesh&lt;/a&gt; (but with no movement penalty or added defenses other than deflection). Using this attack drains the shield by 300 &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt;, however, so it can only be cast once before needing repairs (the shield has a total of 500 durability). The effect lasts for 40 seconds.\nWhile it does not have as much &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; as the &lt;a href=\"Greatshield%20of%20Artorias\"&gt;Greatshield of Artorias&lt;/a&gt;, it makes up for this with its spectacular &lt;a href=\"elemental%20defense\"&gt;elemental defense&lt;/a&gt;s (including the highest &lt;a href=\"magic%20defense\"&gt;magic defense&lt;/a&gt; of any shield, tied with the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Ring%20Shield\"&gt;Crystal Ring Shield&lt;/a&gt;). This makes it useful against strong enemies with mixed elemental attacks (such the &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary%20Guardian\"&gt;Sanctuary Guardian&lt;/a&gt;), or against mages (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Bloathead%20Sorcerer\"&gt;Bloathead Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;).\nResistance defense.\nAlong with &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and Elemental damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status &lt;a href=\"build-up\"&gt;build-up&lt;/a&gt; while blocking.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;Upgrading&lt;/a&gt; this shield will only improve its damage characteristics."}
{"id": "45539", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45539", "title": "Havel's Greatshield (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Havel's Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nHavel's Greatshield is found on a corpse in a pot behind dozen of poison traps in the &lt;a href=\"Upper%20Gutter\"&gt;Upper Gutter&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0The player must have the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Key\"&gt;Forgotten Key&lt;/a&gt;, which is gained from killing both of\u00a0the &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Giant\"&gt;Elite Giant&lt;/a&gt;s at the bottom of &lt;a href=\"Black%20Gulch\"&gt;Black Gulch&lt;/a&gt;, hidden away near &lt;a href=\"The%20Rotten\"&gt;The Rotten&lt;/a&gt;. It is acquired with the rest of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Havel's Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nHavel's Greatshield is one of the, if not the best greatshield available in the game. Boasting a complete resistance to &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt; and high resistance to &lt;a href=\"elemental%20damage\"&gt;elemental damage&lt;/a&gt;, shrugging off any blows that come its way. Unfortunately, unlike its predecessor, it lacks the stone flesh skill that allows the user to have an innate &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Flesh%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Iron Flesh&lt;/a&gt; ability when the time comes.\nThat being said, it has a very demanding &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement \u2014 45 levels, to be precise. This blocks most of its usage for builds that do not invest heavily in Strength.\nUpgrades.\nUpgrades with &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Twinkling Titanite&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "134867", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134867", "title": "Havel's Greatshield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Havel's Greatshield is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe final word on defensive equipment, Havel's Greatshield returns as one of the strongest greatshields available in the game.\nBoasting extreme elemental defense and stability, there is almost no offense that Havel's Greatshield cannot weather, being able to virtually ignore any sustained barrage while taking little to no chip damage from any elemental attack and losing very little stamina per attack. However, this comes at the cost of being the heaviest greatshield in the game, requiring heavy investment in &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;, as well as requiring the wielder to hit the first soft cap for &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnlike other greatshields which typically boast the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Bash\"&gt;Shield Bash&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, Havel's Greatshield has a unique skill in &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Flesh\"&gt;Stone Flesh&lt;/a&gt;, which grants the wielder an &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Flesh%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Iron Flesh&lt;/a&gt;-like defensive buff, significantly boosting their defensive power for any attacks that are not blocked by the shield."}
