{"id": "2977", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2977", "title": "Havel's Ring", "text": "Havel's Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\n&lt;a href=\"Havel%20the%20Rock\"&gt;Havel the Rock&lt;/a&gt; drops this ring when killed. He can either be accessed through a door in the latter half of the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt; through use of the &lt;a href=\"Master%20Key\"&gt;Master Key&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0or accessed through a door just prior to the &lt;a href=\"Hydra\"&gt;Hydra&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Darkroot%20Basin\"&gt;Darkroot Basin&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nRaises the player's maximum equipment burden by 50%.\nOverview.\nHavel's Ring is one of the first rings accessible to the player assuming the Master Key was chosen as the &lt;a href=\"Starting%20Gifts\"&gt;starting gift&lt;/a&gt;. It is a useful ring, allowing many classes to upgrade from slow roll to mid roll or better and giving players a wider range of equipment options without sacrificing mobility. Later, the player may want to invest in &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Endurance&lt;/a&gt; to free up their ring slot, although certain players may require both the ring and high endurance if they seek out the heavier weapons and armor. Prior to &lt;a href=\"Patch%20Information\"&gt;patch 1.06&lt;/a&gt; Havel's ring was inferior in many ways to the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood%20Grain%20Ring\"&gt;Dark Wood Grain Ring&lt;/a&gt;, but the two rings can be combined to use most of the game's equipment with ease."}
{"id": "131380", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131380", "title": "Havel's Ring (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Havel's Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "7812", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7812", "title": "Havel's Set", "text": "Havel's Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe set is located in the &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; cathedral interior, past the two &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knight&lt;/a&gt; Archers. A room near the bonfire will have an empty fireplace serving as an &lt;a href=\"Illusory%20Wall\"&gt;illusory wall&lt;/a&gt;, which leads to a basement. The set, along with &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Tooth\"&gt;Dragon Tooth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;, is located in a group of four chests. The separate fifth one is a &lt;a href=\"mimic\"&gt;mimic&lt;/a&gt; holding an &lt;a href=\"Occult%20%28upgrade%20path%29\"&gt;Occult&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Club\"&gt;Club&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nCarved from solid rock, it is worn by Havel's soldiers and &lt;a href=\"Havel%20the%20Rock\"&gt;Havel the Rock&lt;/a&gt; himself.\nCharacteristics.\nHavel's Set boasts some of the highest elemental resistances and physical defense in the game, as well as the highest &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; in the game. However, it is also the heaviest armor set. Although losing to the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Set\"&gt;Black Iron Set&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Set\"&gt;Giant Set&lt;/a&gt; in terms of physical defense, Havel's Set does not require upgrading. It is also one of only three heavy sets to offer &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance, having more than twice as much as &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Set\"&gt;Smough's Set&lt;/a&gt; and considerably more than even a fully-upgraded &lt;a href=\"Black%20Iron%20Set\"&gt;Black Iron Set&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55352", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55352", "title": "Havel's Set (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Havel's Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained in &lt;a href=\"The%20Gutter\"&gt;The Gutter&lt;/a&gt;, behind a locked door near the first &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. There are two stages to acquiring this set.\nCharacteristics.\nIt has some of the highest defensive stats and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; in the game, boasting great &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;auxiliary&lt;/a&gt; resistances (specifically its &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleed&lt;/a&gt; resistance), save for &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;; only the helm is bested by the &lt;a href=\"Smelter%20Demon%20Helm\"&gt;Smelter Demon Helm&lt;/a&gt; and its poise is outclassed by the &lt;a href=\"Gyrm%20Warrior%20Greathelm\"&gt;Gyrm Warrior Greathelm&lt;/a&gt;. For this reason, this is one of the most broadly-used heavy armor sets in the game, and players typically don a piece of this set, as every piece of the set has great defenses, even when matched with lighter, less-resistant armor.\nOne thing to keep in mind with such heavy armor is that unless players possess extremely high &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; builds, wearing the full set will most definitely cause them to \"fat &lt;a href=\"roll\"&gt;roll&lt;/a&gt;\" due to surpassing the 70% &lt;a href=\"equip%20load\"&gt;equip load&lt;/a&gt; capacity. As such, it is encouraged that the &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Soldier%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Royal Soldier's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Third%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Third Dragon Ring&lt;/a&gt; are used simultaneously. The player may also choose to ignore rolling entirely but beware the risks it might bring, as some attacks of certain &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bosses&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; are often unblockable, not to mention that the fact that in &lt;a href=\"PvP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, rolling becomes an essential to most successful players."}
{"id": "135195", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135195", "title": "Havel's Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Havel's Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound on a corpse in the area guarded by the &lt;a href=\"Stray%20Demon%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Stray Demon&lt;/a&gt; on the bridge above the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep%23Bonfires\"&gt;Old Wolf of Farron&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe corpse will only appear after defeating &lt;a href=\"Havel%20the%20Rock%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel the Rock&lt;/a&gt; at the top of &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;. Defeating the version summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Man%20Serpent%20Summoner\"&gt;Man Serpent Summoner&lt;/a&gt; will not cause the set to appear.\nCharacteristics.\nHavel's Set returns once more as one of the heaviest, yet most protective, armor sets in the game. Being lighter only than &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Smough's Set&lt;/a&gt;, the player will need to make a heavy investment in &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; in order to be able to even move around, but the investment can be more than worth it if the set is used right.\nThe set provides extreme resistance to physical damage, with even its \"weakness\" to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage being higher than the regular physical defenses of most other sets in the game. Its elemental defenses are lower but still sound across the board, being especially resistant to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage to resist the breath of the dragons. Its resistance to &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt; is also very well-rounded, even sporting resistance against &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; buildup.\nUnsurprisingly, Havel's Set boasts extreme amounts of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, allowing the wielder to trade against virtually any attacks in the game while still poising through."}
