{"id": "4119", "revid": "357159", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4119", "title": "Hawk Ring", "text": "The Hawk Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". Along with the &lt;a href=\"Leo%20Ring\"&gt;Leo Ring&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Hornet%20Ring\"&gt;Hornet Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Wolf%20Ring\"&gt;Wolf Ring&lt;/a&gt;, the Hawk Ring was one of the four rings gifted to the four knights of &lt;a href=\"Gwyn%2C%20Lord%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lord Gwyn&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nIn a chest hidden behind the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;. It is not required to kill the blacksmith to get it; simply walk around him.\nEffect.\nThe Hawk Ring boosts the &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;Bows&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Crossbows\"&gt;Crossbows&lt;/a&gt; by 65%, aiding archers by increasing the distance and the effectiveness of arrows and bolts. It also increases the distance one can zoom in while aiming.\nThe bonus is especially useful for the &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Bow\"&gt;Composite Bow&lt;/a&gt;, allowing &lt;a href=\"Large%20Arrow\"&gt;Large Arrows&lt;/a&gt; to be used at long ranges."}
{"id": "48326", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48326", "title": "Hawk Ring (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The\u00a0Hawk Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe ring is available from a corpse in the pit containing several &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Salamander\"&gt;Flame Salamander&lt;/a&gt;s at the bottom of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants%23Bonfires\"&gt;Cardinal Tower&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt;. This area can be accessed by jumping off on to the rubble on the side of the pit and wearing either the &lt;a href=\"Silvercat%20Ring\"&gt;Silvercat Ring&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Flying%20Feline%20Boots\"&gt;Flying Feline Boots&lt;/a&gt;, or by using the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Key\"&gt;Iron Key&lt;/a&gt; on the door located just before the &lt;a href=\"The%20Last%20Giant\"&gt;Last Giant&lt;/a&gt; boss room.\nEffect.\nIncreases the effective &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt; of arrows by 7.55% for each &lt;a href=\"Bows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; when equipped. This means arrows will travel a longer distance in a straight line before arcing toward the ground."}
{"id": "132478", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132478", "title": "Hawk Ring (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Hawk Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nThe Hawk Ring greatly extends the &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Arrows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt;, reducing both damage drop-off and arc on long distance shots. It also increases the zoom distance of binoculars and bows/crossbows (up and down on dpad to zoom in).\nThe ring also reduces damage drop-off of &lt;a href=\"Kukri\"&gt;Kukri&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Throwing Knives&lt;/a&gt; that are thrown beyond the normal lock-on range. Additionally, it dramatically changes the arc of items like &lt;a href=\"Firebomb%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firebombs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Urn%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning Urns&lt;/a&gt;, but not items like &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Hunter%20Charm\"&gt;Undead Hunter Charm&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Alluring%20Skull%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Alluring Skulls&lt;/a&gt;, when thrown without locking on an enemy."}
{"id": "5458", "revid": "48110874", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5458", "title": "Hawkeye Gough", "text": "Hawkeye Gough (\u9df9\u306e\u76ee \u30b4\u30fc) is a &lt;a href=\"character\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", encountered only in the \"&lt;a href=\"Artorias%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Artorias of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt; DLC\". He is voiced by , who also voiced &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3ABiorr%20of%20the%20Twin%20Fangs\"&gt;Biorr of the Twinfangs&lt;/a&gt; and Blacksmiths &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3ABlacksmith%20Ed\"&gt;Ed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Ademonssouls%3ABlacksmith%20Boldwin\"&gt;Boldwin&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Souls\"&gt;Demon's Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nPlayers can find Gough after defeating &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Artorias\"&gt;Knight Artorias&lt;/a&gt; by heading up a set of stairs opposite the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Stoicism%20Gazebo\"&gt;Battle of Stoicism Gazebo&lt;/a&gt;. However, he can only be reached after finding the &lt;a href=\"Crest%20Key\"&gt;Crest Key&lt;/a&gt;, which is dropped by a &lt;a href=\"Mimic\"&gt;Mimic&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Oolacile%20Township\"&gt;Oolacile Township&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nGough is found alone on top of a locked tower. There he acts as a to the &lt;a href=\"Chosen%20Undead\"&gt;Chosen Undead&lt;/a&gt;, offering a variety of wares, including unique items that he personally crafted.\nGough eventually offers to assist the player in killing &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Kalameet\"&gt;Black Dragon Kalameet&lt;/a&gt;, but only after the player first encounters the &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt;. Should the player answer \"Yes\" to both of his questions, Gough will shoot down the \"old bat\", forcing the dragon to engage the player on the ground. It is not necessary for Gough to shoot Kalameet in order to kill the dragon, but it makes the fight significantly easier. Gough gifts his bow to the player upon Kalameet's defeat after several prompts.\nLore.\nHawkeye Gough is one of the &lt;a href=\"Four%20Knights%20of%20Gwyn\"&gt;Four Knights of Gwyn&lt;/a&gt; and the owner of the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hawkeye%20Gough%27s%20Set\"&gt;Hawkeye Gough's Set&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Gough%27s%20Greatbow\"&gt;Gough's Greatbow&lt;/a&gt;. It is said that he could knock a flying &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt; out of the sky with his mighty bow.\nGough was the leader of the Dragonslayers. He wielded the mightiest of greatbows as he was the only one who had the strength to handle such power. Gough fought bravely in the war against the &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;dragons&lt;/a&gt; at the dawn of the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Age of Fire&lt;/a&gt; and was given numerous honors by &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Gwyn\"&gt;Lord Gwyn&lt;/a&gt;.\nGough was not without his enemies, however. His sight was impaired by those who dismissed Gough as a brutish giant, packing the eye holes of his helm with tree resin; although this did not impair his ability to shoot with deadly precision.\nAt some point while in &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt; Gough was imprisoned within a tower. There he created innumerable &lt;a href=\"carvings\"&gt;carvings&lt;/a&gt;, through which he achieved personal enlightenment.\nGough hinted at his relationship with the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Blacksmith\"&gt;Giant Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nGough has very high &lt;a href=\"hitpoints\"&gt;hitpoints&lt;/a&gt; and can dish out a lot of damage. The confined area in which he resides can make it difficult to avoid his blows.\nDue to Gough's blindness, wearing the &lt;a href=\"Slumbering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring\"&gt;Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt; will cause him to stop and listen for the player's whereabouts.\nHe is susceptible to &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;blood loss&lt;/a&gt;."}
