{"id": "130389", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130389", "title": "Hawkwood's Shield", "text": "Hawkwood's Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Cemetery%20of%20Ash\"&gt;Cemetery of Ash&lt;/a&gt;, in front of a gravestone located on the right path before entering &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Starved%20Hound\"&gt;Starved Hound&lt;/a&gt;. It is the same grave where &lt;a href=\"Hawkwood%20the%20Deserter\"&gt;Hawkwood the Deserter&lt;/a&gt; can sometimes be found praying.\nThe shield will only appear here if Hawkwood is killed, or after he leaves the shrine once the &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Watchers\"&gt;Abyss Watchers&lt;/a&gt; have been defeated.\nCharacteristics.\nAn unremarkable Small Shield, Hawkwood's Shield serves mainly to provide lore and little else. Its wielding requirements are trivial, though it does provide moderate &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; absorption. However, as with other Small Shields, it is a poor choice for defending oneself and is more suitable for &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parrying&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard ."}
{"id": "137459", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137459", "title": "Hawkwood's Swordgrass", "text": "Hawkwood's Swordgrass is a in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nOnce the player has obtained the &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Dragon%20Torso%20Stone\"&gt;Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;, the swordgrass will be given to the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Andre&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, along with a message from &lt;a href=\"Hawkwood%20the%20Deserter\"&gt;Hawkwood&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nBears a message from &lt;a href=\"Hawkwood%20the%20Deserter\"&gt;Hawkwood&lt;/a&gt;:\n\"Come to the mausoleum in Farron. Only one can take the path of ancient dragons.\"\nWhile this item by itself does not have any particular use, it hints the player into visiting the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep%23Bonfires\"&gt;mausoleum in Farron&lt;/a&gt; once more, in the same place where they fought the &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Watchers\"&gt;Abyss Watchers&lt;/a&gt;. Upon arrival, &lt;a href=\"Hawkwood%20the%20Deserter\"&gt;Hawkwood&lt;/a&gt; will be already expecting them and challenge them to a duel to the death for the &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Dragon%20Torso%20Stone\"&gt;Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone&lt;/a&gt; and the title of who is the best \"dragon\" of both."}
{"id": "130419", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130419", "title": "Hawkwood the Deserter", "text": "Hawkwood the Deserter is a &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;character&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is voiced by , who also voiced &lt;a href=\"Griggs%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Griggs of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" and &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Sorcerer%20Navlaan\"&gt;Royal Sorcerer Navlaan&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nHawkwood wears the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Legion%20Set\"&gt;Undead Legion Set&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Helm%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Chain Helm&lt;/a&gt; and wields a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt; along with his &lt;a href=\"Hawkwood%27s%20Shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n&lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;\nSummons.\n&lt;a href=\"Consumed%20King%27s%20Garden\"&gt;Consumed King's Garden&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Archdragon%20Peak\"&gt;Archdragon Peak&lt;/a&gt;\nPlot.\nHawkwood is a deserter from &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Watchers\"&gt;Farron's Undead Legion&lt;/a&gt;. He decides that he is not fit to fulfill his duty of searching for the &lt;a href=\"Lords%20of%20Cinder\"&gt;Lords of Cinder&lt;/a&gt;, so instead takes up residence in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;. Once the player defeats the &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Watchers\"&gt;Abyss Watchers&lt;/a&gt;, he will disappear from the shrine.\nIf speaking with &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Andre&lt;/a&gt; or visiting a grave beside the shrine, the player will come in possession of &lt;a href=\"Hawkwood%27s%20Shield\"&gt;Hawkwood's Shield&lt;/a&gt;, which he left behind for the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20One\"&gt;Ashen One&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the player has acquired the &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Dragon%20Torso%20Stone\"&gt;Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Andre\"&gt;Andre&lt;/a&gt; will give the player &lt;a href=\"Hawkwood%27s%20Swordgrass\"&gt;Hawkwood's Swordgrass&lt;/a&gt;, which contains a message challenging the player to a duel at the mausoleum in Farron Keep, where the &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices%23Bonfires\"&gt;Abyss Watchers&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; is located. If the player defeats Hawkwood, they will acquire the &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Dragon%20Head%20Stone\"&gt;Twinkling Dragon Head Stone&lt;/a&gt;. If Hawkwood kills the player, he will take the &lt;a href=\"Twinkling%20Dragon%20Torso%20Stone\"&gt;Twinkling Dragon Torso Stone&lt;/a&gt;. The player can reacquire it by killing him."}
