{"id": "101443", "revid": "27795815", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=101443", "title": "Headshot", "text": "Headshots are from of &lt;a href=\"critical%20attack\"&gt;critical attack&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"gameplay%20mechanic\"&gt;gameplay mechanic&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nHeadshots are performed by shooting either a &lt;a href=\"bow\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"crossbow\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt; at the enemy's head. If it connects it will deal extra damage and usually &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; the enemy. When used against humanoid enemies, such as other players, headshots will always stagger regardless of one's &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. The amount of bonus damage depends on the type of headgear the stricken person wears. Interestingly, players wearing the &lt;a href=\"Bloated%20Head\"&gt;Bloated Head&lt;/a&gt; take the same amount of headshot damage as someone wearing no headgear at all.\nCrossbows are not well suited for headshots due to the difficulty of precise aiming.\nMedium Headshot damage (+30%).\nAny open-faced headgear made out of sturdier materials such as stone, iron, steel or other metals.\nLow Headshot damage (+10%).\nAny headgear made out of sturdier materials that provides full protection to one's face.\nShooting a limb will deal the same amount of bonus damage, but will not stagger the enemy."}
{"id": "171862", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=171862", "title": "Headshots", "text": ""}
{"id": "4058", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4058", "title": "Heal", "text": " \nHeal (\u56de\u5fa9) is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nHeal recovers a moderate amount of &lt;a href=\"Health\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, that is 3.0 times the &lt;a href=\"magic%20adjustment\"&gt;magic adjustment&lt;/a&gt; of the equipped &lt;a href=\"Talismans\"&gt;talisman&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhat long casting time with distinctive animation and sound.\nHeal benefits from &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20Synergy\"&gt;miracle synergy&lt;/a&gt;, the healing multiplier increases by 0.25 for each level of miracle synergy, granting a total of up to 4.0x MagAdjust in healing.\nOverview.\nIn PvE, Heal is most commonly used to supplement Estus, especially as an alternative heal in situations when the player is not in danger. In PvP, Heal is popular among invading phantoms that don't use Estus and would or could not use humanity for healing.\n&lt;a href=\"Great%20Heal\"&gt;Great Heal&lt;/a&gt; is the next miracle in the line of healing miracles, healing more HP with the same casting time. However, it has fewer casts, so Heal may be the superior choice for patching up lesser amounts of damage, and gives players greater control over how much HP they want for regeneration.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "31127", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31127", "title": "Heal (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Heal is a &lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nAt the base level with 12 &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cleric%27s%20Sacred%20Chime\"&gt;Cleric's Sacred Chime&lt;/a&gt;, Heal regenerates 450 HP per use. As healing in this fashion takes longer than drinking &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;estus&lt;/a&gt;, it is best to use this when out of danger, and conserve estus for more perilous situations.\nCompared to later variants of heal such as &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Heal&lt;/a&gt;, Heal does not heal as much HP, but has a lower Faith requirement.\nCasting it during &lt;a href=\"Co-op%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;co-op&lt;/a&gt; will heal nearby allies, as well as the caster. The range for this heal is very small.\nIt is possible to hold a Heal by holding the cast button. This allows the player to ready the cast, but activate it once it's needed. The player can't move so it is nearly useless outside of co-op.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "133472", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133472", "title": "Heal (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Heal is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nRestores &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; for the caster and nearby allies equal to 3 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst, and consumes 92 &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;. For catalysts that also scale with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Chime\"&gt;Crystal Chime&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sunless%20Talisman\"&gt;Sunless Talisman&lt;/a&gt;, only the Spell Buff from &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; is taken into account."}
{"id": "133470", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133470", "title": "Heal Aid", "text": "Heal Aid is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nEffect.\nRestores &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; for the caster equal to 1.5 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst, and consumes 61 &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;. For catalysts that also scale with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Chime\"&gt;Crystal Chime&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sunless%20Talisman\"&gt;Sunless Talisman&lt;/a&gt;, only the Spell Buff from &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; is taken into account.\nUnlike other healing Miracles, this spell does not force the caster to kneel down in prayer, and casts extremely quickly. However, it only heals the user and not nearby allies, unlike the other healing Miracles. &lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "16312", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16312", "title": "Healing", "text": "Healing is a &lt;a href=\"gameplay%20mechanic\"&gt;gameplay mechanic&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nHealing restores &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, which can be done in a variety of ways and ultimately prevent &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. The most basic way of healing is to simply rest at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nEnemies, such as the &lt;a href=\"Berenike%20Knight\"&gt;Berenike&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Balder%20Knight\"&gt;Balder Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, will have little to no &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; while drinking &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Estus&lt;/a&gt; and can be staggered by nearly any weapon.\nEnemies.\nOccasionally, &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"characters\"&gt;characters&lt;/a&gt; that can heal themselves, or others, are encountered."}
{"id": "128584", "revid": "27795815", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=128584", "title": "Healing (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Healing is a &lt;a href=\"Gameplay%20Mechanics%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;gameplay mechanic&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nHealing restores &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, which can be done in a variety of ways and ultimately prevent &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. The most basic way of healing is to simply rest at a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nUse.\nItems.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"PvP%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Phantoms&lt;/a&gt; cannot use healing items. Members of the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Remnants\"&gt;Dragon Remnants&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; can heal, however."}
{"id": "16319", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16319", "title": "Health", "text": " Health, also known as Hit Points or HP, is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nHealth is a numerical stat that represents the survivability of the player. It depletes when is received and can be restored by &lt;a href=\"healing\"&gt;healing&lt;/a&gt;.\nOne health bar on player's HUD equals 135.7 HP. When it reaches zero, &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0occurs.\nIncreasing.\nThe main way of increasing Health is through adding points to the &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; stat when &lt;a href=\"leveling%20up\"&gt;leveling up&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can also be passively raised while wearing the &lt;a href=\"Tiny%20Being%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Tiny Being's Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Favor%20and%20Protection\"&gt;Ring of Favor and Protection&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Mask%20of%20the%20Mother\"&gt;Mask of the Mother&lt;/a&gt;. These items can be stacked to further increase Health.\nConversely, Health is lowered if the player is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;cursed&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0or if they equip the &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20Crown%20Ring\"&gt;Dusk Crown Ring&lt;/a&gt;. These effects can be stacked, as well."}
