{"id": "128586", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=128586", "title": "Health (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Health, also known as Hit Points or HP, is a &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nHealth is a numerical stat that represents the survivability of the player. It depletes when damage is received and can be restored by healing. When it reaches zero, &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; occurs.\nIncreasing Health.\nThe main way of increasing Health is through adding points to the &lt;a href=\"Vigor\"&gt;Vigor&lt;/a&gt; stat when &lt;a href=\"Level%20Up%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;leveling up&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can also be passively raised while wearing the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Seal\"&gt;Blue Seal&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Life%20Ring\"&gt;Life Ring&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"First%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;First&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Second%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Second&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Third%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Third Dragon Ring&lt;/a&gt;s. These items can be stacked to further increase Health."}
