{"id": "67541", "revid": "35416778", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67541", "title": "Heavy Armor Sets (Dark Souls II)", "text": "For categorization purposes on this wiki, Heavy Armor Sets are &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;armor sets&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\" that have a total &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; of 30 or more.\nHeavy armor sets, such as &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Havel's Set&lt;/a&gt;, are good for tanking because of their high defense and &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;. They allow for moderate to high damage to be taken without killing the player, however no armor set can make the player invincible, so caution is still your best defense.\nHeavy sets, while they provide high defense also make moving and &lt;a href=\"rolling\"&gt;rolling&lt;/a&gt; much harder. The &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Soldier%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Royal Soldier's Ring&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"First%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;First&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Second%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Second&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Third%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Third Dragon Ring&lt;/a&gt; all increase Maximum &lt;a href=\"Equip%20Load\"&gt;Equip Load&lt;/a&gt;, thus possibly allowing for faster rolling.\nAgain, strong armor does not make a player invincible. So focus and concentration can still trump having heavy armor."}
{"id": "131252", "revid": "27795815", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131252", "title": "Heavy Armor Sets (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Armor is a type of equipment in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nFor categorization purposes on this wiki, heavy armor sets are armor sets in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\" that have a total &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; of 29 or more.\nCharacteristics.\nHeavy armor sets provide the strongest defenses and the most &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;. However, they are also extremely costly in weight, meaning that the wearer must invest heavily in &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; if they intend to use heavy armor.\nBecause of the high absorption values and the great amount of Poise provided, heavy armor is ideal protection for players who intend to equip ultra weapons and perform &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; trades with opponents. Ultra weapons tend to weigh a lot and cost tremendous amounts of &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; to swing, so equipment such as &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chloranthy%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Chloranthy Ring&lt;/a&gt; tend to go hand-in-hand with such builds.\nBecause virtually all heavy sets are plate metal-based, most sets in this category tend to be weak to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; attacks, though exceptions do exist. Their plate metal nature, however, also tends to make them highly resistant to &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage and &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"buildup\"&gt;buildup&lt;/a&gt;."}
