{"id": "5294", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5294", "title": "Heavy Crossbow (Dark Souls)", "text": "The Heavy Crossbow is a &lt;a href=\"Crossbows\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Heavy Crossbow can be found off of a corpse in the &lt;a href=\"Depths\"&gt;Depths&lt;/a&gt;, along with 11 &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Bolt\"&gt;Heavy Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s, on the stone balcony overlooking the &lt;a href=\"Gaping%20Dragon\"&gt;Gaping Dragon's&lt;/a&gt; chamber.\nCharacteristics.\nHeavier and more powerful than the &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;, the Heavy Crossbow deals the most damage per shot of all the crossbows, making it potentially more useful than &lt;a href=\"Avelyn\"&gt;Avelyn&lt;/a&gt; against nimble opponents.\nLike all crossbows, you cannot aim down sights so the &lt;a href=\"Binoculars\"&gt;Binoculars&lt;/a&gt; can help with aiming. With the Binoculars, line the target up in the exact center of the screen. Change to Heavy crossbow without moving the camera, then fire. Like all crossbows, Heavy Crossbow does not scale off any stats though upgrading increases base damage, if infusing the AR of elemental bolts is added to the elemental AR of the infusion, which can be beneficial. Use &lt;a href=\"Ammunition\"&gt;ammo&lt;/a&gt; types that elementally match the infusion when possible and factor in enemy resistances when choosing an infusion and/or ammo type."}
{"id": "47567", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47567", "title": "Heavy Crossbow (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Heavy Crossbow is a &lt;a href=\"Crossbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "132923", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132923", "title": "Heavy Crossbow (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Heavy Crossbow is a &lt;a href=\"Crossbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by the crossbow-wielding &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20Knight\"&gt;Cathedral Knight&lt;/a&gt; found on the rafters of the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Heavy Crossbow is a very rare weapon, as it can only be dropped by a single enemy in the entire game. However, it is a very useful addition to one's arsenal, especially as an invader, due to its well-balanced attributes.\nIt is 25% lighter than the &lt;a href=\"Arbalest\"&gt;Arbalest&lt;/a&gt;, and only marginally heavier than the &lt;a href=\"Knight%27s%20Crossbow\"&gt;Knight's Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;, while dealing a respectable amount of pure physical damage. As well, it has better range than the Knight's Crossbow, allowing it to maintain its damage output against enemies that are farther away. Its lack of split damage allows it to take advantage of specialized ammunition more easily, rather than relying on maximizing &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage output by using &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning Bolts&lt;/a&gt;, which makes it a more flexible weapon. The only drawback is that it requires more &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield than the Knight's Crossbow.\nIts combination of light weight and respectable damage makes the Heavy Crossbow a favorite for players that do not wish to invest in the &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; to wield an off-hand &lt;a href=\"Avelyn%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Avelyn&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "127359", "revid": "43756993", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=127359", "title": "Heavy Crossbow Dark Spirit", "text": "Heavy Crossbow Dark Spirit is an that appears in &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things Betwixt&lt;/a&gt; in either &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt; or in NG after burning a &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Ascetic\"&gt;Bonfire Ascetic&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Keepers%27%20Dwelling\"&gt;Fire Keepers' Dwelling&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThis &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit\"&gt;Dark Spirit&lt;/a&gt; dons the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; and is armed with a &lt;a href=\"Shortsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Shortsword&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nAlbeit shabby in appearance, this enemy hits hard and can tank quite a lot of hits.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Scholar&lt;/a&gt;, he'll aggro as soon as the player approaches the first &lt;a href=\"Fog%20Door%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;fog gate&lt;/a&gt; and will attempt to take them down with his &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. The player will find themself most vulnerable to his &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Bolt%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bolts&lt;/a&gt; while using the ladder next to the nest of &lt;a href=\"Dyna%20%26amp%3B%20Tillo\"&gt;Dyna and Tillo&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile he may lose sight of the player as they travel inside the trees, he'll never descend from his spot and will just wander around the bridge. This can be exploited to the player's advantage, since he won't be able to find a cover to avoid ranged attacks.\nWhen engaged, he'll switch between one-handing and two-handing his &lt;a href=\"Shortsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt;, firing shots only when the player strays away too far from his reach.\nDespite his many &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt;, his lack of &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; makes him extremely susceptible to stunlocks.\nHe may replenish his &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; up to ten times via &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus&lt;/a&gt;, if given the chance.\nLocation.\nHe is found at the bottom of the tree closer to Majula.\nHe spawns atop the bridge erupting from the second tree."}
{"id": "135982", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135982", "title": "Heavy Gem", "text": "Heavy Gems are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUsage.\nInfusing a weapon with the Heavy property will significantly improve the &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; on that weapon, but compromises the &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; by completely removing it, putting emphasis on only Strength after the infusion is done.\nLike most other infusions, it will also lower the weapon's base damage slightly. Heavy infusions should only be used if there is a large gap between one's Strength and Dexterity, as if both are nearly equal to one another, the weapon's overall damage after the infusion may be lower than it was prior to."}
