{"id": "59916", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=59916", "title": "Heide Knight Set", "text": "The Heide Knight Set is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nPieces of the set are dropped by &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Knight\"&gt;Heide Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, a non-respawning enemy, and only drops when the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt; the Knight is closest to is at &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20Intensity\"&gt;intensity&lt;/a&gt; 2 or higher. This makes the set hard to obtain, but the knights will always drop a random piece of their armor, or the weapon the defeated Knight is wielding, with the exception of the Heide Knight near the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Winter\"&gt;Shrine of Winter&lt;/a&gt;, who uses a sword, but drops the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Lance\"&gt;Heide Lance&lt;/a&gt; at intensity 1 and the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Greatlance\"&gt;Heide Greatlance&lt;/a&gt; at intensity 2.\nIn \"\", there are respawning Heide Knights at &lt;a href=\"Heide%27s%20Tower%20of%20Flame\"&gt;Heide's Tower of Flame&lt;/a&gt;, which makes it much easier to obtain the set. However, drop rate is low at the lowest bonfire intensity, and increases once the second intensity is reached.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Heide Knight Set is a fairly balanced set, with its best qualities being its high defenses, along with decent &lt;a href=\"Poison%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bleeding&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance. However, it has unremarkable &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;, no &lt;a href=\"petrify\"&gt;petrify&lt;/a&gt; resistance and is one of the heaviest medium armor sets.\nOnce fully upgraded, the defense is much higher, making it one of the better medium armor sets if one can handle its the poor poise-to-&lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; ratio."}
{"id": "44905", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44905", "title": "Heide Knight Sword", "text": "The Heide Knight Sword is a &lt;a href=\"Straight%20Swords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;straight sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped from the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Knight\"&gt;Heide Knight&lt;/a&gt; encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt;.\nDropped from the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit%20Heide%20Sword%20Knight\"&gt;Dark Spirit&lt;/a&gt; wielding it in the King's Door courtyard or near &lt;a href=\"Mild-Mannered%20Pate\"&gt;Pate&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Bonfire Intensity&lt;/a&gt; 2+.\nIn \"\" it's a random drop from the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Knight\"&gt;Heide Knight&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Heide%27s%20Tower%20of%20Flame\"&gt;Heide's Tower of Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Heide Knight Sword is a relatively robust straight sword with a varied moveset. It is capable of horizontal as well as vertical slashes, and a thrusting attack on the second strong attack when one-handed. It also possesses higher than usual durability, making it a rather reliable weapon to use on longer journeys.\nIts main characteristic, however, is that it deals &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage, making it a fairly useful weapon for &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; builds. Combined with its early availability (it can be found in one of the two immediately accessible areas at the start of the game) as well as its low physical stat requirements, and it becomes a very strong candidate for &lt;a href=\"Infusion\"&gt;infusing&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Boltstone\"&gt;Boltstone&lt;/a&gt;, and even for &lt;a href=\"Power%20Stance\"&gt;Power Stancing&lt;/a&gt; (requiring as little as 16 &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and 15 &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;). However, this second option is only viable in \"Scholar of the First Sin\"."}
{"id": "52775", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52775", "title": "Heide Lance", "text": "The Heide Lance is a &lt;a href=\"Lances\"&gt;lance&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nAcquired from the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Knight\"&gt;Heide Knight&lt;/a&gt; that's on the path leading to &lt;a href=\"Drangleic%20Castle\"&gt;Drangleic Castle&lt;/a&gt;, just after the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Winter\"&gt;Shrine of Winter&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn \"\", it is dropped by a Heide Knight in &lt;a href=\"The%20Gutter\"&gt;The Gutter&lt;/a&gt;, who also drops the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Knight%20Iron%20Mask\"&gt;Heide Knight Iron Mask&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Heide Lance is a lance type weapon and its moveset contains only thrusting type attacks making it useful for corridors and narrow lanes. It is not the most damage efficient weapon until being fully upgraded, and its late position in the game means that the player may find more suitable weapons early on.\nThe Heide Lance, like other Heide weaponry, possesses lightning damage and scales with Faith."}
{"id": "52553", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52553", "title": "Heide Spear", "text": "The Heide Spear\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGuaranteed drop from the &lt;a href=\"Heide%20Knight\"&gt;Heide Knight&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0encountered in &lt;a href=\"The%20Lost%20Bastille\"&gt;The Lost Bastille&lt;/a&gt;. This knight has been moved to &lt;a href=\"Sinners%27%20Rise\"&gt;Sinners' Rise&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nRandom drop from the spear wielding\u00a0Heide Knight\u00a0in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Heide%27s%20Tower%20of%20Flame\"&gt;Heide's Tower of Flame&lt;/a&gt; (\"SotFS\" only).\nCharacteristics.\nThe Heide Spear inflicts both physical and lightning damage. \u00a0Like other spears, a useful perk to this weapon is that you can use one-handed weak attacks while holding up your shield, allowing you to deal damage while blocking incoming attacks. \u00a0This does less damage than while not holding up the shield, however, and does not have the longer-reaching second attack."}
