{"id": "45399", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45399", "title": "Heirs of the Sun", "text": "The\u00a0Heirs of the Sun is a &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". Members of this covenant aid others in their worlds by being summoned as golden phantoms. The Heirs of the Sun covenant operates much like the &lt;a href=\"Warrior%20of%20Sunlight\"&gt;Warrior of Sunlight&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0covenant from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nRequirements.\nNone; the player may join the covenant upon reaching the Altar of Sunlight, located in &lt;a href=\"Harvest%20Valley\"&gt;Harvest Valley&lt;/a&gt;.\nBenefits.\nUpon joining; players receive the &lt;a href=\"Sun%20Seal\"&gt;Sun Seal&lt;/a&gt; ring. While in the covenant, the player's white summon signs and phantom appears as gold instead of white, and the time they can spend in another world is extended.\nUpon defeating a boss after being summoned with the &lt;a href=\"White%20Sign%20Soapstone%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;White Sign Soapstone&lt;/a&gt;, both the host and phantom will receive a &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Medal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sunlight Medal&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0These are used to level up in the covenant. Each gold phantom that fullfills their duty at once will grant the host an additional Sunlight Medal. The Sunlight Medal replaces the &lt;a href=\"Token%20of%20Fidelity\"&gt;Token of Fidelity&lt;/a&gt; that is normally awarded. Additionally, Warriors of the Sun that are summoned through the &lt;a href=\"Small%20White%20Sign%20Soapstone\"&gt;Small White Sign Soapstone&lt;/a&gt; will not be awarded with a Sunlight Medal upon completion of their duty, and will instead receive the usual &lt;a href=\"Smooth%20%26amp%3B%20Silky%20Stone\"&gt;Smooth &amp; Silky Stone&lt;/a&gt;.\nFurther rewards are granted upon leveling up:"}
