{"id": "7836", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7836", "title": "Silver Knight Set", "text": "The Silver Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nAvailability.\nFound in two chests guarded by two &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knight&lt;/a&gt;s in the trophy room of &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\nWorn by the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knight&lt;/a&gt;s of Anor Londo.\u00a0\nCharacteristics.\nWhile this set offers good defense for its &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt; initially, it is eventually outclassed by the fully upgraded &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Knight%20Set\"&gt;Elite Knight Set&lt;/a&gt;, only offering increased &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Defense\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; resistance and one more &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt; in exchange for much less &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Defense\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Defense\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Defense\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; resistance. It is however easier to &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Modification\"&gt;upgrade&lt;/a&gt;, and will thus reach its full potential more quickly."}
{"id": "135218", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135218", "title": "Silver Knight Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Silver Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Silver Knights&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll of the Boreal Valley&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nMaking a return from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", the Silver Knight Set has a moderate weight cost amongst heavy armor sets, and offers strong and balanced defenses in return.\nWhile it has relatively moderate resistance to &lt;a href=\"Regular%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Standard&lt;/a&gt; physical damage, the set offers very impressive absorption against &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage, making it useful to wear against specialty weapons. While it is weak to &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage like other plate metal sets, it can still ward off an acceptable amount of damage from blunt weapons. Its elemental defenses are quite well-balanced, providing good resistance against &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, and its weaknesses to &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dark&lt;/a&gt; are still quite tolerable. It offers good all-round defense against &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; buildup, with no major weaknesses to exploit.\nWith a strong &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio, the Silver Knight Set is well-suited to wielding large weapons to back up its high defenses."}
{"id": "6075", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6075", "title": "Silver Knight Shield", "text": "The Silver Knight Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knight&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Silver Knight Shield is one of the best medium shields in the game, with the highest &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; of its class, both before and after &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgrading&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0(except the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20%28Upgrade%20Path%29\"&gt;Crystal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Balder%20Shield\"&gt;Balder Shield&lt;/a&gt; +5), as well as the highest resistance total. It also does not require valuable &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Chunk\"&gt;Titanite Chunk&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20Slab\"&gt;Slabs&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade.\nIts only real downside is the above-average weight and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement for a medium shield. Like most metal shields, its &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Damage%20Type%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; defense remains somewhat weak.\nIt has a medium deflection and normal &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte\"&gt;parrying&lt;/a&gt; speed.\nResistance Defense.\nAlong with Physical and Elemental damage reduction, weapons also have hidden stats that reduce the amount of status build-up while blocking."}
{"id": "132004", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132004", "title": "Silver Knight Shield (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Silver Knight Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Silver Knights&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nA well-balanced medium shield, the Silver Knight Shield provides reliable defense in most situations.\nIt possesses 100% defense against physical damage, and a respectable array of elemental absorption values. It has good base stability that scales well with upgrades, allowing it to reliably block most attacks with little stamina loss. And to round everything out it possesses the &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Parry&lt;/a&gt; skill, allowing players to turn the tables on enemies and inflict &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ripostes&lt;/a&gt; to quickly defeat them.\nUnfortunately, it also loses out in many ways against the &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Knight%20Shield\"&gt;Lothric Knight Shield&lt;/a&gt;, which on top of being lighter and having higher stability also specializes in defending against &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; damage. The only true advantage that the Silver Knight Shield has is that it requires less &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield, making it more ideal on builds that attempt to limit their amount of Strength investment in favor of other stats.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "5032", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5032", "title": "Silver Knight Spear", "text": "The Silver Knight Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Spears\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\u00a0\nAvailability.\n2% drop by Spear wielding &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Knight\"&gt;Silver Knights&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Silver Knight Spear has the second highest reach out of any &lt;a href=\"Spears\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; and is only outmatched by the &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Spear\"&gt;Demon's Spear&lt;/a&gt;. The spear's length is unusually long compared to others due to the fact that you hold this one by the hilt end rather than the middle of the spear.\nThe Silver Knight Spear is the only weapon with the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20%28auxiliary%20effect%29\"&gt;Divine&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Auxiliary%20Effect\"&gt;Auxiliary Effect&lt;/a&gt; that does not have a &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; or scale off this stat. This makes it a good alternative to use in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Catacombs\"&gt;The Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Giants\"&gt;Tomb of the Giants&lt;/a&gt;. However, having Divine Auxiliary means it cannot be &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Augmentation\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt;."}
