{"id": "54150", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54150", "title": "Skeptic's Spice", "text": "Skeptic's Spice is an in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSkeptic's Spice is used to lower the &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; requirement of a\u00a0spell. It can be used by talking to &lt;a href=\"Magerold%20of%20Lanafir\"&gt;Magerold of Lanafir&lt;/a&gt; and accessing the \"Incense\" option in his dialogue menu.\nThe effectiveness of the spell will still depend on the associated Attack Bonus, and using a spell below its base requirements may result in reduced effectiveness (for instance, casting &lt;a href=\"Denial\"&gt;Denial&lt;/a&gt; with less than 24 Faith will reduce the duration of the spell). However, reducing a spell's requirements can be useful for gaining access to certain spells without leveling beyond the associated stat's soft cap, such as &lt;a href=\"Blinding%20Bolt\"&gt;Blinding Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sunlight%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sunlight Spear&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Profound%20Still\"&gt;Profound Still&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "131970", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131970", "title": "Skill", "text": "Skills, formerly known as Battle Arts or Weapon Arts, are a &lt;a href=\"Gameplay%20Mechanics%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;gameplay mechanic&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nWeapon skills allow the execution of powerful special moves with &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;, and boost the damage output of &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; at the cost of &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt;.\nWeapons that belong to the same weapon-type variety, usually share the same skill. There are some exceptions, however, and some &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;unique weapons&lt;/a&gt; may have a particular skill specific to them.\nThe original game included 85 skills. With the release of the first downloadable content, \"&lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\", 13 new skills were added for a total of 98 different skills."}
