{"id": "18419", "revid": "4066758", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18419", "title": "Slash (damage type)", "text": "Slash is a that can be inflicted in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSlash Damage is one of four &lt;a href=\"Physical%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;physical damage types&lt;/a&gt; and is dealt by &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Swords\"&gt;curved swords&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Curved%20Greatswords\"&gt;curved greatswords&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"katanas\"&gt;katanas&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"daggers\"&gt;daggers&lt;/a&gt; and many &lt;a href=\"halberds\"&gt;halberds&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor the most part, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; protects against Slash Damage more than the other physical damage types. This is especially true for &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;medium&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;heavy&lt;/a&gt; armor sets. Although many sets protect well against Slash Damage, many &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; that inflict it also posses the &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; .\nDefense.\n To lower Slash Damage, it is necessary to raise the Slash Defense &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt;.\nStats.\nAt lower levels, increasing any while &lt;a href=\"Level%20Up\"&gt;leveling up&lt;/a&gt; will raise Slash Defense to some degree, however, &lt;a href=\"Resistance\"&gt;Resistance&lt;/a&gt; will raise it more than any other.\nEquipment.\nArmor.\nAs a general rule, the heavier an armor piece is, the higher its defense against &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage will be.\nOf the &lt;a href=\"Starting%20Armor%20Sets\"&gt;starting armor sets&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Set\"&gt;Knight Set&lt;/a&gt; offers the highest Slash Defense.\n&lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Light armor sets&lt;/a&gt; are not the best choice to reduce Slash Damage, however, the &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Set\"&gt;Chain Set&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Xanthous%20Set\"&gt;Xanthous Set&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lord%27s%20Blade%20Set\"&gt;Lord's Blade Set&lt;/a&gt; are the heaviest of all light armors, and therefore offer higher defense against Slash Damage. When fully upgraded, the Chain Set offers the highest Slash Defense of any light armor set. Lighter armor sets that offer very good Slash Defense, while still being lightweight, are the &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Set\"&gt;Crimson Set&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%27s%20Set\"&gt;Big Hat's Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nWithin &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;medium armor sets&lt;/a&gt;, the fully upgraded &lt;a href=\"Steel%20Set\"&gt;Steel Set&lt;/a&gt; offers the highest Slash Defense. &lt;a href=\"Ornstein%27s%20Set\"&gt;Ornstein's Set&lt;/a&gt; is also a good choice when receiving Slash Damage and does not require upgrading.\n&lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Heavy armor sets&lt;/a&gt; offer the best choices when raising Physical Defense. &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Set\"&gt;Havel's Set&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Set\"&gt;Smough's Set&lt;/a&gt; and the fully upgraded &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Set\"&gt;Giant Set&lt;/a&gt; are excellent choices.\nThe fully upgraded &lt;a href=\"Fang%20Boar%20Helm\"&gt;Fang Boar Helm&lt;/a&gt; offers the highest Slash Defense of any .\nRings.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Steel%20Protection\"&gt;Ring of Steel Protection&lt;/a&gt; raises all forms of Physical Defense.\nShields.\nUnlike &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"shields\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt; modify damage based on a percentage and all forms of &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical Damage&lt;/a&gt; are affected by its single modifier. Many &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shields\"&gt;standard shields&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Greatshields\"&gt;greatshields&lt;/a&gt; protect against 100% of Physical Damage; the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Shield\"&gt;Spider Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bloodshield\"&gt;Bloodshield&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Shield\"&gt;Tower Shield&lt;/a&gt; are examples of these.\nWeapons.\nWhile many of the following weapons inflict only Slash Damage, some inflict both Slash and &lt;a href=\"Thrust\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, depending on which attack is used from its &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;.\nDaggers ( \u2020 ) denote weapons that also inflict &lt;a href=\"Thrust\"&gt;Thrust Damage&lt;/a&gt; as part of its &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;.\nSlashes ( / ) denote weapons that also inflict &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; buildup.\nAsterisks ( * ) denote weapons that also inflict &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nEnemies.\nThe following is a list of , and &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es that inflict Slash Damage by one or more of their attacks."}
