{"id": "143666", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143666", "title": "Slave Knight Set", "text": "The Slave Knight Set is a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;medium armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nAvailability.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;. In the &lt;a href=\"Corvian%20Settlement\"&gt;Corvian Settlement&lt;/a&gt;, navigate to the rooftops and into the tower with the ladder that leads to the bridge to the cliffside. Inside the tower is a drop-down which leads to a locked room with three &lt;a href=\"Forlorn%20Corvian%20Settler\"&gt;Forlorn Corvian Settler&lt;/a&gt;s within. The set will be on a corpse inside.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Slave Knight Set is renowned for possessing the best physical protection to weight ratio among all armor sets in the game, providing strong defenses against physical damage for a very light weight. It possesses equal amounts of resistance to &lt;a href=\"Regular%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Regular&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slash%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; damage, and its weakest elemental defenses, against &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, are also equivalent.\nGiven its weight, it provides respectable &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt;, albeit not a significant amount."}
{"id": "9063", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9063", "title": "Slime", "text": "Slimes are &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThese creatures seem to be made entirely out of slime with metal spikes embedded in them. They stick on the ceiling in some areas of the sewers awaiting to fall onto the player. Their blood is not red but bluish-green, like that of some mollusks.\nStrategy.\nBeware of their falling attack which can cause excessive damage. It is wise to check the ceiling using the &lt;a href=\"lock%20on\"&gt;lock on&lt;/a&gt; function while navigating the sewers.\nWhen on the ground however, their slow movement and attack speed make them more of a nuisance than a threat.\nThey have incredible &lt;a href=\"physical%20resistance\"&gt;physical resistance&lt;/a&gt;, making killing them with conventional weaponry tedious. They are less resistant to &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, and are extremely vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf faced with multiple slimes, it is possible to round them up into a group whereby they can be dispatched simultaneously with a single &lt;a href=\"area%20of%20effect\"&gt;area of effect&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt;."}
