{"id": "5589", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5589", "title": "Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring", "text": "The Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nThe Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring masks the wearer's sound from enemies. This includes actions such as &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;bing or hitting weapons against a solid surface.\nThe Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring's effect is identical to that of the &lt;a href=\"Hush\"&gt;Hush&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis ring proves very useful when battling\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Hawkeye%20Gough\"&gt;Hawkeye Gough&lt;/a&gt;, as he is blind and requires the player to hit him or make noise if the player avoids his first attacks.\u00a0"}
{"id": "56473", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56473", "title": "Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nThe Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring is given by the &lt;a href=\"Rat%20King%20%28character%29\"&gt;Rat King&lt;/a&gt; as a reward for achieving rank 3 in the &lt;a href=\"Rat%20King%20%28covenant%29\"&gt;Rat King&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Covenant&lt;/a&gt;, which requires 35 &lt;a href=\"Rat%20Tail\"&gt;Rat Tail&lt;/a&gt;s from rank 0.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring masks the wearer's sound from enemies. This includes actions such as &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt;bing or hitting weapons against a solid surface. However, its use is rather limited in the natural progression of the campaign as it is only useful for sneaking up on enemies without direct line of sight to you."}
{"id": "132363", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=132363", "title": "Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nGift from &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; after purchasing the following &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;:\nEffect.\nSilences all sounds made by its wearer.\nUsage.\nWearing the Slumbering Dragoncrest Ring will silence the sounds made by the player completely, such as footsteps. It will not mask sounds made by breaking objects or by killing enemies, though.\nUseful for traversing crowded areas unnoticed, as long as the player keeps out of the enemies' sight. Very useful for approaching unaware enemies from behind at full speed and perform &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;backstabs&lt;/a&gt;. However, if there are many enemies grouped together and the player backstabs one of them, the sound of the kill will alert the others.\nThis ring, used in conjunction with the &lt;a href=\"Obscuring%20Ring\"&gt;Obscuring Ring&lt;/a&gt;, allows the player to scout areas with a certain degree of freedom as long as they don't walk too near in front of enemies."}
