{"id": "5979", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5979", "title": "Small Shields", "text": "Small Shields are a type of &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nSmall shields are the &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;lightest&lt;/a&gt; of the shields, making them good for faster &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; that do not want to be encumbered by heavy equipment. Small shields are poor at damage reduction and &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;. Many small shields have unique &lt;a href=\"parry\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; animations with different hit frames. The lightness of the shields themselves also causes them to only have light deflection.\nSmall Shields.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "67543", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67543", "title": "Small Shields (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Small Shields are a type of &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nSmall Shields are the smallest and &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;lightest&lt;/a&gt; of the shields, but provide the least defense in return. They are mostly used to &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;parry&lt;/a&gt; attacks coming in from an opponent. Small shields have a longer parry animation, which makes for an easier parry.\nSmall Shields.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "134871", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134871", "title": "Small Shields (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Small Shields are a type of &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nSmall shields are characterized by their light &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, minimal stat requirements, and modest resistances. They generally have poor &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt; and struggle to protect their wielders from any damage that they do block. However, they make up for this by facilitating ease of &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;parrying&lt;/a&gt;, and in fact a subset of small shields known as Parrying Shields have the fewest startup frames for initiating parries, allowing the wielder to easily deflect attacks on reaction, rather than prediction.\nBecause of their poor defensive capabilities, most small shields do not greatly benefit from upgrading. However, a select few are the exception to this rule due to either built-in offensive capabilities, or unusually high defensive capabilities."}
