{"id": "47544", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47544", "title": "Smelter Demon Soul", "text": "The Smelter Demon Soul\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;boss soul&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nUse.\nConsume for 8,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;trade&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt; along with 1,500 souls to acquire the &lt;a href=\"Smelter%20Sword\"&gt;Smelter Sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrade with &lt;a href=\"Weaponsmith%20Ornifex\"&gt;Weaponsmith Ornifex&lt;/a&gt; along with 1,500 souls to acquire the &lt;a href=\"Aged%20Smelter%20Sword\"&gt;Aged Smelter Sword&lt;/a&gt; after defeated the Smelter Demon of the Iron Passage. Either soul can be used when this trade is unlocked."}
{"id": "90920", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=90920", "title": "Smelter Hammer", "text": "The Smelter Hammer is a &lt;a href=\"Great%20Hammers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;great hammer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Old%20Iron%20King\"&gt;Dark Souls II: Crown of the Old Iron King&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nAvailability.\nThe Smelter Hammer is a rare drop from &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Warrior\"&gt;Iron Warrior&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower\"&gt;Brume Tower&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Passage\"&gt;Iron Passage&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Smelter Hammer is the heaviest weapon\u00a0available\u00a0in \"Dark Souls II\", outweighing the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Warrior%20Club\"&gt;Giant Warrior Club&lt;/a&gt; by 5.0 units. It also has the highest &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement out of all weapons in \"Dark Souls II\", requiring 70 Strength to wield in one-hand; however, it can be used in a &lt;a href=\"Power%20Stance\"&gt;Power Stance&lt;/a&gt; at 99 Strength.\nHowever, despite its high requirements, the Smelter Hammer is capable of massive damage, due to both its high base damage and decent Strength scaling.\nNotes.\nPressing the parry button while Two-handing initiates a powerful triple spin attack, while the fourth spin launches the player forward into the air, landing face down with the hammer striking the ground in all its length. This final hit takes roughly 1-2 seconds to recover from which, coupled with its high stamina consumption, makes it a very high-risk, high-reward attack to use. \nMost of the damage in this attack is in the final part, when the hammer strikes the ground. However, that doesn't mean the spins are worthless as they have fairly wide reach and decent stagger potential to keep enemies locked in for the final hit. \nOne thing that can help this weapon's usage is that certain enemies do not hit close enough to the ground to damage the player on the ground. Additionally, equipping this weapon in the left hand instead of the right hand so that the spins are clockwise instead of counter-clockwise, which can help in certain areas (such as the cliffside walk in &lt;a href=\"Brume%20Tower\"&gt;Brume Tower&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Fume%20Sorcerer\"&gt;Fume Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; shooting in the distance that has the right-side blocked by a snow wall). "}
{"id": "47534", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47534", "title": "Smelter Sword", "text": "The Smelter Sword\u00a0is an &lt;a href=\"Ultra%20Greatswords%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ultra greatsword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtaining the Smelter Sword requires the player to trade 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Smelter%20Demon%20Soul\"&gt;Smelter Demon Soul&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Straid%20of%20Olaphis\"&gt;Straid of Olaphis&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nWhilst being one of the &lt;a href=\"Weight\"&gt;heaviest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; in the game, as well as possessing a relatively slow &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt;, the Smelter Sword is quite powerful in the right hands. It also features a unique moveset, where each strong attack is a combustion-inducing strike, creating a small, fiery explosion when the sword makes contact. Strong attacks consume 10 &lt;a href=\"durability\"&gt;durability&lt;/a&gt; each; this can be partially mitigated with use of the &lt;a href=\"Bracing%20Knuckle%20Ring\"&gt;Bracing Knuckle Ring&lt;/a&gt; variants.\nUnlike most weapons, the Smelter Sword cannot be &lt;a href=\"infuse\"&gt;infuse&lt;/a&gt;d.\nDespite appearances, the explosion on this weapon's strong attacks deals physical damage. This can be verified by using it on &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Salamander\"&gt;Flame Salamanders&lt;/a&gt;, which are immune to fire.\nNotes.\ne &lt;a href=\"Aged%20Smelter%20Sword\"&gt;Aged Smelter Sword&lt;/a&gt; allows for a large mixed red and blue fire explosion."}
