{"id": "7814", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7814", "title": "Smough's Set", "text": "Smough's Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Domhnall%20of%20Zena\"&gt;Domhnall of Zena&lt;/a&gt; after defeating &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Slayer%20Ornstein%20and%20Executioner%20Smough\"&gt;Dragon Slayer Ornstein and Executioner Smough&lt;/a&gt;. Smough must be killed after Ornstein in order for Domhnall to sell this set once per playthrough. \nPlot.\nWorn by &lt;a href=\"Executioner%20Smough\"&gt;Smough&lt;/a&gt;, the cannibalistic executioner who guards the &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; cathedral.\nCharacteristics.\nSmough's Set initially offers the highest &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental\"&gt;Elemental&lt;/a&gt; defense among the heavy sets, and a remarkable &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; resistance, but cannot be &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt;. This puts it at a disadvantage against upgradeable armor sets in its weight class; for example, the fully upgraded &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Set\"&gt;Giant Set&lt;/a&gt; is superior in almost every way. However Smough's Set does offer a small but notable amount of &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance.\nHowever, Smough's set offers the highest lightning and bleed resistance available among the heavy sets, and even when upgrades are accounted for, it is one of the three best heavy sets in all fields except &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Poise&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;, where it is in fourth and fifth place, respectively. Overall, this makes it a solid all-around armor that requires very little investment.\nSmough's Set has the same weight as the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Set\"&gt;Stone Set&lt;/a&gt;, at 45.2 units. However, the Stone Set offers less defense in all regards, except Poise. Smough's Set is also slightly less &lt;a href=\"Durability\"&gt;durable&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nAccording to an interview for \"Dark Souls: Design Works\", Smough's Set is one of &lt;a href=\"Hidetaka%20Miyazaki\"&gt;Hidetaka Miyazaki&lt;/a&gt;'s favourite armor designs."}
{"id": "135219", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135219", "title": "Smough's Set (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Smough's Set is a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Armor%20Sets%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;heavy armor set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; for a total of 31,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; after defeating &lt;a href=\"Aldrich%2C%20Devourer%20of%20Gods\"&gt;Aldrich, Devourer of Gods&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nReturning from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\", the armor once worn by &lt;a href=\"Executioner%20Smough\"&gt;Executioner Smough&lt;/a&gt; is the heaviest set of armor in \"Dark Souls III\", but is well worth the price should the wearer invest in the &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; to equip it.\nIts physical defenses rival or exceed those provided by even &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel's Set&lt;/a&gt;, allowing the wearer to shrug off damage easily when combined with the innate defense provided by equipping large weapons. Unlike other plate metal sets, Smough's Set provides extremely high defense against &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; damage, which is in fact greater than its defense against &lt;a href=\"Regular%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Regular&lt;/a&gt; damage. Rather, its \"weakest\" physical defense is against &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt; damage, which is still quite high.\nWhile its defense against elemental damage is poor for its weight, even here Smough's Set is extremely resilient. It has no severe weaknesses against any elemental damage type, and in fact resists &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; the most out of all elements, again complementing its resistance to Strike damage. This is backed by all-round resistance to &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Status%20Effects%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; buildup, which the set has no particular weaknesses against.\nThe set's \"poor\" &lt;a href=\"Poise%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;poise&lt;/a&gt;-to-weight ratio is largely due to its extreme weight, as the raw amount of Poise it provides is still exceedingly great, beaten only by Havel's Set in this regard. When paired with &lt;a href=\"Smough%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Smough's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, there is virtually nothing that the player cannot trade against."}
