{"id": "135860", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135860", "title": "Smouldering Ghru", "text": "Smouldering Ghrus are in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAlmost identical to their &lt;a href=\"Ghru\"&gt;lesser brethren&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt;, these Ghrus are stronger and some of them are able to inflict &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; status with their attacks. They smolder in a way similar to a player character who is currently in &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt; mode.\nLocation.\nSmouldering Ghrus conform the main opposing force throughout the &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Lake\"&gt;Smouldering Lake&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nSmouldering Ghrus have higher health, deal more damage, and seem to have a more aggressive attack patterns. Apart from these differences, they are almost identical to their surface &lt;a href=\"Ghru\"&gt;counterparts&lt;/a&gt; and similar tactics should be applied.\nSpecial care should be taken when dealing with Ghrus wielding &lt;a href=\"Rotten%20Ghru%20Spear\"&gt;spears&lt;/a&gt;, as they can perform a &lt;a href=\"Skill%23Shield%20Bash\"&gt;shield bash&lt;/a&gt; that drains a heavy amount of &lt;a href=\"Endurance%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; and which may break the player's guard easily, or they may perform their barrage attack, where they swing their weapon in a frenzied state while advancing menacingly. Retreat and counterattack as the Ghru swings its spear for the fifth time."}
{"id": "130756", "revid": "1188343", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130756", "title": "Smouldering Lake", "text": "The Smouldering Lake is an optional in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a subsection of the &lt;a href=\"Catacombs%20of%20Carthus\"&gt;Catacombs of Carthus&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThe Smouldering Lake is a shallow lake that lies deep underground. Enormous trees that smoulder with embers grow up to the ceiling and their roots reach far into the chambers below the lake. It has been known to be the remains of the once molten &lt;a href=\"Lost%20Izalith\"&gt;Lost Izalith&lt;/a&gt;, or an area adjacent to the lost city. After many years, the lava had subsided significantly; the evidence to this being the presence of the demon corpses that litter the ground in the &lt;a href=\"%23Bonfires\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, which in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" was the area one would have to go through to reach Lost Izalith.\nThis was once the home to the daughters of the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Witch of Izalith&lt;/a&gt; and the demons born from the &lt;a href=\"Flame%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Flame of Chaos&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike the &lt;a href=\"First%20Flame\"&gt;First Flame&lt;/a&gt;, which is tied to the souls of the undead, the faded Flame of Chaos was tied to the souls of the demons, and so the lifeless bodies of &lt;a href=\"Capra%20Demon\"&gt;Capra&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Taurus%20Demon\"&gt;Taurus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Asylum%20Demon\"&gt;Asylum&lt;/a&gt; and a single &lt;a href=\"Centipede%20Demon\"&gt;Centipede Demon&lt;/a&gt; can be found strewn throughout the ruins and piled high near the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Demon%20King\"&gt;Old Demon King&lt;/a&gt;, one of the last remaining demons of old. A petrified arachnoid body, resembling &lt;a href=\"Quelaag%27s%20Sister\"&gt;Quelaag's Sister&lt;/a&gt;, lies within the ruins, where a humanoid corpse holds the &lt;a href=\"Quelana%20Pyromancy%20Tome\"&gt;Quelana Pyromancy Tome&lt;/a&gt;, indicated that the sisters lived here at one point.\nOn the highest ledge above the Smouldering Lake, a colossal triple ballista fires giant bolts at anyone trying to cross the lake. It is fully automated and the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Slave\"&gt;Giant Slave&lt;/a&gt;s that maintained it are long dead. It represents a significant threat; however, it can be used to one's advantage by getting a bolt to hit the unstable floor in the middle of the lake, opening an entrance to the &lt;a href=\"%23Bonfires\"&gt;Old King's Antechamber&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, at the far wall left of the ballista is a crumbling wall which hides the &lt;a href=\"Speckled%20Stoneplate%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Speckled Stoneplate Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and demolishing the wall with a bolt allows access to it.\nAnother entrance to the &lt;a href=\"%23Bonfires\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt; lies straight ahead from the entrance to the lake, near the chamber of the Old Demon King. However, burrowed into the ground nearby is a &lt;a href=\"Carthus%20Sand%20Worm\"&gt;Carthus Sand Worm&lt;/a&gt;, which will shoot up when someone comes nearby. As bolts from the ballista can also reach this area, it is an extremely dangerous route to take.\nInside the Demon Ruins reside &lt;a href=\"Smouldering%20Ghru\"&gt;Smouldering Ghru&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Cleric\"&gt;Demon Cleric&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Statue\"&gt;Demon Statue&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Hound%20Rat\"&gt;Hound Rat&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Hound%20Rat\"&gt;Giant Hound Rat&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Basilisk%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Basilisks&lt;/a&gt;, and two &lt;a href=\"Black%20Knight%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Knights&lt;/a&gt;. To reach the upper reaches of the lake, a long, winding route through the ruins must be taken, with a great number of these enemies along the way.\nIn the deepest part of the ruins, above a pool of deadly lava, there is a ladder leading up to the high ledges above the lake, guarded by a Black Knight. Below, &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Slayer%20Tsorig\"&gt;Knight Slayer Tsorig&lt;/a&gt; can be found. Once emerging on the ledge, a few ballista bolts must be avoided, but the rock formations will prevent most of them from reaching below. A few &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Skeletons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Wheel\"&gt;Skeleton Wheel&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Swordsman%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Skeleton Swordsmen&lt;/a&gt; patrol this area. Past them, the ballista is spinning its gears and can be deactivated with a lever, making the lower area of the lake substantially safer to traverse. A series of ledges against the wall can be dropped down to reach the bottom quickly.\nAn unconfirmed, yet possible, theory is that the Smouldering Lake is another section of the &lt;a href=\"Ash%20Lake\"&gt;Ash Lake&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". This theory is supported by the presence of massive trees, resembling the &lt;a href=\"archtree\"&gt;archtree&lt;/a&gt;s that the ancient &lt;a href=\"dragons\"&gt;dragons&lt;/a&gt; once lived in and that the witches of Izalith burned with their &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt;. It is also supported by the close proximity the Ash Lake had to the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Ruins\"&gt;Demon Ruins&lt;/a&gt; as well. Looking from a top-down view from &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt;, one could see that the entrance to the Demon Ruins was right across from the entrance to the Ash Lake; and as both were beneath, then it would seem reasonable that the two areas were in close proximity to each other.\nBonfires.\nThe Smouldering Lake is a subsection of the Catacombs of Carthus and comprises the following &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfires&lt;/a&gt;:"}
{"id": "137517", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=137517", "title": "Smouldering Rotten Flesh", "text": ""}
{"id": "142991", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=142991", "title": "Snap Freeze", "text": "Snap Freeze (\u77ac\u9593\u51cd\u7d50) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Ashes%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Ashes of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nLocated after the &lt;a href=\"Depth%20of%20the%20Painting\"&gt;Depth of the Painting&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. Run to the left past the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Crab\"&gt;Great Crab&lt;/a&gt; and it will be on a corpse behind a &lt;a href=\"Birch%20Woman\"&gt;Birch Woman&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nCreates a cloud of freezing mist, rapidly inflicting 15 &lt;a href=\"Frost\"&gt;Frost&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"buildup\"&gt;buildup&lt;/a&gt; per tick on enemies within. Cloud persists for 5 seconds, and the duration cannot be extended by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nUse.\nSingle player.\nSnap Freeze can be useful for inflicting Frostbite on large and slow enemies that are vulnerable to the status effect, particularly certain &lt;a href=\"Boss%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bosses&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Pontiff Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Father%20Ariandel\"&gt;Father Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;, or on large groups of enemies where several can be caught in the cloud at once. As it costs less &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; and has a much shorter duration than &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Weapon\"&gt;Frozen Weapon&lt;/a&gt;, it is ideal for setting the status effect and then taking advantage of the defense reduction on afflicted foes, as opposed to proccing Frostbite for the burst damage, resetting the buildup with &lt;a href=\"Fire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage and then repeating.\nAs the cloud lingers for a short time, it is possible to inflict frostbite multiple times in one cast of snap freeze. When paired with a way of rapidly inflicting fire damage, such as with &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Surge%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Fire Surge&lt;/a&gt; or a quick-hitting fire weapon, it's possible to deal large bursts of damage. This can be a difficult tactic to pull off effectively, as it won't work if the enemy exits the cloud, or if they don't give an opening for the player to apply their fire damage.\nOnline gameplay.\nBecause it is a stationary cloud, Snap Freeze is more suited as a defensive sorcery than an offensive one, creating a terrain hazard at will that debuffs enemy players. Laying down a cloud as an invader can dissuade pursuing &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;phantoms&lt;/a&gt; from giving chase, and is particularly useful for blocking off narrow paths such as hallways and bridges to create space. This can open up opportunities for setting up ambushes later down the line, or creating a temporary barrier behind which one can cast offensive sorceries like &lt;a href=\"Great%20Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, and can even be used creatively to hinder escape routes after an ambush is set.\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "136104", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=136104", "title": "Sneering Mask", "text": "The Sneering Mask is a piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Shade%20Set\"&gt;Pale Shade Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, along with the rest of the set, after defeating the &lt;a href=\"Londor%20Pale%20Shade\"&gt;Londor Pale Shade&lt;/a&gt; in both of his invasions. The entire set can be found near &lt;a href=\"Yoel%20of%20Londor\"&gt;Yoel of Londor&lt;/a&gt;'s corpse."}
{"id": "8222", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8222", "title": "Snickering Top Hat", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nThe Snickering Top Hat is a &lt;a href=\"head%20armor\"&gt;head armor&lt;/a&gt; piece in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of &lt;a href=\"Chester%27s%20Set\"&gt;Chester's Set&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nChester's Top Hat has the second highest &lt;a href=\"Bleed%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; Resist of any headpiece when fully &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Modification\"&gt;upgraded&lt;/a&gt;. Its &lt;a href=\"Physical%20defense\"&gt;Physical defense&lt;/a&gt;, however, is average, with an unusual focus on &lt;a href=\"Strike\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt; resistance.\nUpgrades.\nRequires 200 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; per upgrade.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "7168", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7168", "title": "Sniper Bolt", "text": "Sniper Bolts are an &lt;a href=\"ammunition\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; type in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSniper Bolts have a longer &lt;a href=\"range\"&gt;range&lt;/a&gt; than other &lt;a href=\"crossbow\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt; bolts, although this is hard to utilize due to the fact that there is no effective way of aiming crossbows."}
{"id": "135575", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135575", "title": "Sniper Bolt (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Sniper Bolts are a type of &lt;a href=\"Ammunition%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "5295", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5295", "title": "Sniper Crossbow", "text": "The Sniper Crossbow is a &lt;a href=\"Crossbows\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound along with 12 &lt;a href=\"Sniper%20Bolt\"&gt;Sniper Bolt&lt;/a&gt;s on the roof of &lt;a href=\"Sen%27s%20Fortress\"&gt;Sen's Fortress&lt;/a&gt;; off a corpse not far from the &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. It can be reached by falling down the gap between the &lt;a href=\"Crestfallen%20Merchant\"&gt;Crestfallen Merchant&lt;/a&gt; and the rest of the level (the player will sustain a high amount of fall damage unless &lt;a href=\"Fall%20Control\"&gt;Fall Control&lt;/a&gt; is used).\nCharacteristics.\nThe Sniper Crossbow is heavier and weaker than the &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;, yet is stronger and heavier than the &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike all crossbows, you cannot aim down sights so the &lt;a href=\"Binoculars\"&gt;Binoculars&lt;/a&gt; can help with aiming. With the Binoculars, line the target up in the exact center of the screen. Change to Sniper crossbow without moving the camera, then fire. Like all crossbows, Sniper Crossbow does not scale off any stats though upgrading increases base damage, if infusing the AR of elemental bolts is added to the elemental AR of the infusion, which can be beneficial. Use &lt;a href=\"Ammunition\"&gt;ammo&lt;/a&gt; types that elementally match the infusion when possible and factor in enemy resistances when choosing an infusion and/or ammo type."}
{"id": "133460", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133460", "title": "Sniper Crossbow (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Sniper Crossbow is a &lt;a href=\"Crossbows%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Castle\"&gt;Lothric Castle&lt;/a&gt;, on a corpse on a small tower guarded by a &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Soldier%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hollow Soldier&lt;/a&gt; that throws &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Hunter%20Charm\"&gt;Undead Hunter Charm&lt;/a&gt;s, before reaching the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Barracks\"&gt;Dragon Barracks&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;. To reach it, the player must drop into the moat before the &lt;a href=\"Lothric%20Wyvern\"&gt;Lothric Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;s and follow the path to the right, defeating several &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Assassin\"&gt;Hollow Assassin&lt;/a&gt;s and a &lt;a href=\"Winged%20Knight\"&gt;Winged Knight&lt;/a&gt; in order to reach it.\nCharacteristics.\nGreatly improved over its \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" cousin, the Sniper Crossbow allows players to take aim and accurately deal damage to enemies over long distances. It possesses a range only slightly less than that of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Bow%20of%20Pharis%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Black Bow of Pharis&lt;/a&gt;, and like the Black Bow its range can be augmented through equipping the &lt;a href=\"Hawk%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Hawk Ring&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sniper%20Bolt%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sniper Bolts&lt;/a&gt; in order to maximize shot distance and minimize damage falloff.\nLike all other crossbows, the Sniper Crossbow lacks any &lt;a href=\"Parameter%20Bonus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;scaling&lt;/a&gt; in any category. This means that even with only small investments in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, it is possible to inflict respectable damage at long range. When two-handed, the Sniper Crossbow requires only 12 Strength and 16 Dexterity to be operated, meaning that it can be handy on caster builds that cannot afford to invest many points into physical damage stats.\nHowever, the Sniper Crossbow also comes with critical drawbacks. It is tied for being the heaviest crossbow in the game, alongside the &lt;a href=\"Avelyn%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Avelyn&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Repeating%20Crossbow\"&gt;Repeating Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;, both of which excel at short ranges rather than long. As well, it has an increased delay before firing a shot, alongside the loading time that all crossbows have, greatly decreasing its firing rate. This second drawback in particular makes it difficult to perform \"snap shots\" with the weapon, as each shot must be further readied in advance before a bolt can be loosed. These factors make the Sniper Crossbow a poor weapon for engaging enemies at lock-on range.\nUpgrades.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "14379", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14379", "title": "Snow Rat", "text": "Snow Rat is an &lt;a href=\"enemy\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLocation.\nLocated in the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariamis\"&gt;Painted World of Ariamis&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nVery similar to the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Rat\"&gt;Undead Rat&lt;/a&gt;, except its hits cause &lt;a href=\"Toxic%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Toxic&lt;/a&gt; buildup and deals 5 damage per second over 10 minutes once contracted."}
