{"id": "4237", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4237", "title": "Soothing Sunlight", "text": "Soothing Sunlight (\u592a\u967d\u306e\u5149\u306e\u7652\u3057) is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped from a docile &lt;a href=\"Pisaca\"&gt;Pisaca&lt;/a&gt; guarding Logan's prison in &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;The Duke's Archives&lt;/a&gt;.\nGeneral information.\nUsage of Soothing Sunlight requires that the caster belong to the &lt;a href=\"Princess%27s%20Guard\"&gt;Princess's Guard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"covenant\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt;. It restores HP for 6 times MagAdjust for the user and also any friendly &lt;a href=\"phantom\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt;s around them, including NPC summons and enemies affected by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Undead%20Rapport\"&gt;Undead Rapport&lt;/a&gt;.\nSoothing Sunlight benefits from &lt;a href=\"miracle%20synergy\"&gt;miracle synergy&lt;/a&gt;. Each level of synergy increases the healing multiplier by 0.25, increasing the multiplier to a maximum of 7.0\nOverview.\nGiven the fact that it requires membership of the unpopular Princess's Guard covenant and also the exorbitant faith requirement, Soothing Sunlight is a rare sight indeed. Also, it takes coordination for allies to get close to someone who is about to cast this miracle, and communications in Dark Souls is both time-consuming and limited. Ultimately, this limits Soothing Sunlight's practicality as a healing miracle.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "59239", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=59239", "title": "Soothing Sunlight (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Soothing Sunlight is a &lt;a href=\"Miracles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by killing &lt;a href=\"Licia%20of%20Lindeldt\"&gt;Licia of Lindeldt&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0while &lt;a href=\"invading\"&gt;invading&lt;/a&gt; her\u00a0using the &lt;a href=\"Crushed%20Eye%20Orb\"&gt;Crushed Eye Orb&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nSoothing Sunlight is without a doubt a very useful spell, though also very limiting.\nIt can be compared to &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heal%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Heal&lt;/a&gt; in order to better understand its qualities and disadvantages. It will heal slightly less health, and has fewer uses while needing one more &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; slot. However, the fact that it has the same &lt;a href=\"casting%20speed\"&gt;casting speed&lt;/a&gt; and can heal summoned players or NPCs from far away can make it much more practical in situations where the caster is not the focus of enemy attention.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain Attunement milestones:"}
{"id": "131081", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131081", "title": "Soothing Sunlight (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Soothing Sunlight (\u592a\u967d\u306e\u5149\u306e\u7652\u3057) is a &lt;a href=\"Boss%20Soul%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;soul-transposed&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained by transposing the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20of%20the%20Dancer\"&gt;Soul of the Dancer&lt;/a&gt; and 5,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nRestores &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Points%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; for the caster and allies within the general area equal to 7 times the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; of the catalyst, and consumes 205 &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt;. For catalysts that also scale with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Chime\"&gt;Crystal Chime&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sunless%20Talisman\"&gt;Sunless Talisman&lt;/a&gt;, only the Spell Buff from &lt;a href=\"Faith%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Faith&lt;/a&gt; is taken into account.\nDue to the high stamina cost of this spell, action after casting is severely restricted, preventing the caster from &lt;a href=\"rolling\"&gt;rolling&lt;/a&gt; or attacking immediately after.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "2080", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2080", "title": "Sorcerer", "text": "The Sorcerer is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThis class' primary form of attack is through casting &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;, and start the game with the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; sorcery. However, their high &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; means they can make the use of either sorceries and/or &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt;.\nSorcerers' expertise in sorceries are at the expense of having poor &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt; output. Their &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;dexterity,&lt;/a&gt; unlike their &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt;, is decent, however.\nFor new players playing blind, Sorcerers can be tricky, since the merchants for the other spells must be found before new spells can be obtained.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Pyromancer\"&gt;Pyromancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wanderer\"&gt;Wanderer&lt;/a&gt; classes both start with 4 free &lt;a href=\"Resistance\"&gt;Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and superior armor compared to the Sorcerer, and are better classes to choose for a dedicated mage if one purchases a &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%27s%20Catalyst\"&gt;Sorcerer's Catalyst&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Rickert%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Rickert of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; right after arriving in Lordran."}
{"id": "6479", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6479", "title": "Sorcerer's Catalyst", "text": "The Sorcerer's Catalyst is a &lt;a href=\"Catalysts\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Sorcerer's Catalyst is the first catalyst available to players. It scales well with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and is the best to use from 10 to 11 INT and between 27 to 40 INT. At 41 INT, it becomes inferior to &lt;a href=\"Logan%27s%20Catalyst\"&gt;Logan's Catalyst&lt;/a&gt;. \nFunctionally, the Sorcerer's Catalyst is identical to &lt;a href=\"Beatrice%27s%20Catalyst\"&gt;Beatrice's Catalyst&lt;/a&gt; and nearly identical to the &lt;a href=\"Izalith%20Catalyst\"&gt;Izalith Catalyst&lt;/a&gt;."}
