{"id": "131133", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131133", "title": "Sorcerer's Staff (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Sorcerer's Staff is a &lt;a href=\"Staves%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe most basic and easily available staff, the Sorcerer's Staff does not possess any notable traits but does not suffer from any major weaknesses either. It also has the lowest &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; requirement to wield, making it useful for builds that simply want to cast utility spells. While the &lt;a href=\"Heretic%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Heretic's Staff&lt;/a&gt; is a better catalyst before one reaches 45 Intelligence, the Sorcerer's Staff is still very well-balanced and remains a stable choice for beyond that point.\nIt holds up as the best staff if players wish to stop leveling Intelligence at level 50, and even at 60 Intelligence it ranks second only to the &lt;a href=\"Court%20Sorcerer%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Court Sorcerer's Staff&lt;/a&gt;. Even then, when compared to titans like the Court Sorcerer's Staff and &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Crystal%20Staff\"&gt;Sage's Crystal Staff&lt;/a&gt;, its &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; does not cost an unreasonable amount of &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; to use, allowing the wielder to conserve FP even when using &lt;a href=\"Steady%20Chant\"&gt;Steady Chant&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with regular .\n&lt;br&gt;"}
