{"id": "173168", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173168", "title": "Sorcerer (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Sorcerer is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%202\"&gt;Dark Souls 2&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is an &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;-based class, serving as an excellent base for a build focused on &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Hexes\"&gt;Hexes&lt;/a&gt;, and also possibly for a build using a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; infused weapon that wants to start with some spells. It has a decent starting &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; but a horrendous starting &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, barely even enough to wield their weapon and even with effective Strength being doubled when two-handing so the vast majority of weapons can't be wielded without some investment, only some &lt;a href=\"Daggers%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Daggers&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe starting &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Sorcerer's Staff&lt;/a&gt; is a decent, quick-casting spell tool for Sorceries that is worth upgrading, while the &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; is a decent, if short reaching weapon whose poor Durability should be supplemented by picking up a second copy in the &lt;a href=\"Things%20Betwixt\"&gt;Things Betwixt&lt;/a&gt; tutorial.\nThe initial &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; spell is fairly strong, strong enough to be able to kill any of the first few &lt;a href=\"Ogre\"&gt;Ogre&lt;/a&gt;s in the game, whether that be the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Ring\"&gt;Stone Ring&lt;/a&gt;-holding one before the hut in Things Betwixt or the &lt;a href=\"Scholar%20of%20the%20First%20Sin\"&gt;Scholar of the First Sin&lt;/a&gt;-exclusive one on the path to the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt;, giving a fair amount of early souls. Make sure to pick up a second copy from &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20Hag%20Melentia\"&gt;Merchant Hag Melentia&lt;/a&gt; to double the amount of uses. \nThe head and hands pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; can be put on for an extra 40% defence, at the cost of shortening the distance of their rolls by about 10% unless &lt;a href=\"Vitality%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt; is increased. \nThe combination of above average &lt;a href=\"Adaptability\"&gt;Adaptability&lt;/a&gt; and high &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; gives the class one of the best starting rolls, at 9 i-frames. \nStarting Equipment.\nAs with all starting classes in Dark Souls 2, the &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Set\"&gt;Imported Set&lt;/a&gt; (including a second set of &lt;a href=\"Imported%20Trousers\"&gt;Imported Trousers&lt;/a&gt;) worn before the character creation can be found unequipped in the character's inventory. "}
{"id": "173162", "revid": "26269363", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173162", "title": "Sorcerer (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Sorcerer is one of the &lt;a href=\"Classes%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%203\"&gt;Dark Souls 3&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is an &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;-focused starting class that also has good &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; and decent &lt;a href=\"Dexterity%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. It is the only class that starts with offensive &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorceries&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe two starting spells, &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Heavy Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, are both roughly equally effective damage-wise for the &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;Focus Points&lt;/a&gt; spent but the Heavy version is slower to cast and more of a waste if it misses, making it more effective for preliminary ambush attacks or slow enemies/bosses. While both of these spells are fairly cheap they still have far fewer casts than in previous games, and at least in the beginning will have to be heavily supplemented with a weapon. Additionally, their damage is boosted by 12% by the &lt;a href=\"Young%20Dragon%20Ring\"&gt;Young Dragon Ring&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe starting catalyst, the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%27s%20Staff%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorcerer's Staff&lt;/a&gt;, actually holds up fairly well at high levels of Intelligence even if it is never really the best and won't actually start scaling until the user's Intelligence is at least 19. Its &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Weapon Art&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Steady%20Chant\"&gt;Steady Chant&lt;/a&gt; will buff the damage of all Sorceries by 10% for 15 seconds, making it a useful thing to use just before fighting a strong enemy such as a boss. \nThe starting &lt;a href=\"Mail%20Breaker%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Mail Breaker&lt;/a&gt; is a pretty weak weapon and is suitable mostly for &lt;a href=\"Parry%20and%20Riposte%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Riposte&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;s, especially since the Weapon Art &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Splitter\"&gt;Shield Splitter&lt;/a&gt; is the user's only notable help against shields. \nHaving a &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Leather Shield&lt;/a&gt; probably won't help much with survivability due to it having the poor damage blocking and low &lt;a href=\"Stability\"&gt;Stability&lt;/a&gt; characteristic of a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt;, though it does have the advantage of a Small Shield's improved &lt;a href=\"Parry%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Parry skill&lt;/a&gt;. As such it is best ignored unless planning to use that parry. For those actually wishing to block, the &lt;a href=\"Large%20Leather%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Large Leather Shield&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20Handmaid\"&gt;Shrine Handmaid&lt;/a&gt; can be wielded with one more point in &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; or the even stronger &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Eagle%20Kite%20Shield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Silver Eagle Kite Shield&lt;/a&gt; can be found in &lt;a href=\"High%20Wall%20of%20Lothric\"&gt;High Wall of Lothric&lt;/a&gt; and wielded with 4 more Strength. \nWhile the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%20Set%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Sorcerer's Set&lt;/a&gt; has bad physical defences it has quite good elemental defences and surprisingly high &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; resistance. \nThose wishing to get a more usable weapon can wield either the &lt;a href=\"Shortsword%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Shortsword&lt;/a&gt; with one more point in Strength or the &lt;a href=\"Scimitar%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Scimitar&lt;/a&gt; with one more point in Dexterity, both buyable from the Shrine Handmaid. \nSorcery trainers can be found in &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Road%20of%20Sacrifices\"&gt;Road of Sacrifices&lt;/a&gt; for further development as a spellcaster. Additionally, the &lt;a href=\"Sage%27s%20Coal\"&gt;Sage's Coal&lt;/a&gt; in the nearby &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron Keep&lt;/a&gt; allows for the &lt;a href=\"Infusion%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Infusion&lt;/a&gt; of weapons with &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Gem\"&gt;Crystal Gem&lt;/a&gt;s to let them scale of Intelligence. "}
