{"id": "3498", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3498", "title": "Sorceries", "text": ""}
{"id": "161055", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=161055", "title": "Sorcery", "text": ""}
{"id": "3421", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3421", "title": "Sorcery (Dark Souls)", "text": "Sorcery is a form of in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSorceries are cast by &lt;a href=\"catalysts\"&gt;catalysts&lt;/a&gt;. Catalysts usually scale with the &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; stat, although there is one &lt;a href=\"Tin%20Darkmoon%20Catalyst\"&gt;exception&lt;/a&gt;.\nMost sorceries can be purchased from various found throughout the game. Some are found as lootable &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are more sorceries than either &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;pyromancies&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;miracles&lt;/a&gt;. While pyromancies focus on offensive spells and miracles focus on defensive and &lt;a href=\"healing\"&gt;healing&lt;/a&gt;, sorceries include a variety of utility and augmentation spells as well as a range of offensive spells.\nAll forms of offensive sorceries cause &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic Damage&lt;/a&gt;, which is typically effective against iron armor, tough scales, and other physically resilient materials.\nLore.\nSorcery is said to have originated with &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;Seath the Scaleless&lt;/a&gt;, the \"grandfather of sorcery\". The ancient land of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt; has its own sorceries, which are an \"approximation\" when compared to modern Sorcery and are characterized by augmenting the weapon or body, rather than causing offensive damage. &lt;a href=\"Manus%2C%20Father%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Manus, Father of the Abyss&lt;/a&gt; is the source of at least one &lt;a href=\"Abyss\"&gt;Abyss&lt;/a&gt; sorcery.\nThe other Abyss sorceries are said to be discovered by an Oolacile sorcerer on the brink of madness, they differ from normal offensive sorceries, which are derived from souls, in that they draw power from humanity and cause both &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Damage\"&gt;Physical Damage&lt;/a&gt; due to their \"weighty\" nature.\n&lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%20Logan\"&gt;Big Hat Logan&lt;/a&gt; of the Dragon School in &lt;a href=\"Vinheim\"&gt;Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; played a role in the development of numerous sorceries. During his infatuation with Seath in the Regal Archives, Logan developed new sorceries and boosted existing ones."}
{"id": "57564", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57564", "title": "Sorcery (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Sorcery is a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; type in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSorcery is cast through &lt;a href=\"staves\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt; as a medium and scale with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;.\nSome non-staff weapons exist which can be used to cast sorcery as well, such as the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Flame\"&gt;Blue Flame&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pilgrim%27s%20Spontoon\"&gt;Pilgrim's Spontoon&lt;/a&gt;.\nMost sorceries can be purchased from various &lt;a href=\"Merchants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;merchants&lt;/a&gt; throughout &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt;. Some sorceries, however, can be found as lootable items on corpses and in chests. Sorcery provides the user with a mix of augmentation and utility, while still giving a wide variety of fully offensive spells which exclusively deal &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;magic damage&lt;/a&gt;. The damage dealt by sorceries is influenced by the Magic Attack Bonus &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stat&lt;/a&gt;. Magic bonus is raised with Intelligence.\nSorceries typically work better on heavy armored enemies than light armored enemies such as &lt;a href=\"Retainer\"&gt;Retainer&lt;/a&gt;s. There are some exceptions to this, however, such as enemies that wear the &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Havel's Armor&lt;/a&gt;, but on the whole this serves as a good rule of thumb. Also, most enemies found in the DLCs have higher elemental resistances than enemies found in the core game."}
{"id": "133527", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133527", "title": "Sorcery (Dark Souls III)", "text": " are a class of spells in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSorceries are aligned with &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. To cast a sorcery, the player must first equip a &lt;a href=\"Staves%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;staff&lt;/a&gt;. There are also some weapons that can act as a catalyst for casting sorceries.\nSorceries can be purchased from various characters or found as loot on corpses or in chests. Giving scrolls to &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; will unlock additional sorceries for purchase.\nMost sorceries focus on dealing &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage, while others will focus on utility."}
{"id": "143777", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143777", "title": "Sorcery (Element)", "text": ""}
{"id": "161066", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=161066", "title": "Sorcery (disambiguation)", "text": ""}
{"id": "178232", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=178232", "title": "Sorcery (element)", "text": ""}
{"id": "143211", "revid": "51254358", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=143211", "title": "Sorcery (lore)", "text": "Sorceries are a form of &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; in the world of \"Dark Souls\".\nLore.\n Sorceries appear to be tied with the power of souls. In early times, the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Witch of Izalith&lt;/a&gt; was able to manipulate heat and flame, with a shamanic art called \"flame sorcery\". This ability was taught to her children, but it has unfortunately died with them when the Witch fell to Chaos and &lt;a href=\"Pyromancy%20%28disambiguation%29\"&gt;Pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; was created, with the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Firesage\"&gt;Demon Firesage&lt;/a&gt; being the last master of the original fire arts. Painted worlds are also known to harness their cold as magic, and &lt;a href=\"frost\"&gt;frost&lt;/a&gt; sorceries are apparently common to them. Even another kind of sorcery, called moon sorcery and connected to the ancient Darkmoon energy, was practiced by &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Sun%20Gwyndolin\"&gt;Gwyndolin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Darkmoon\"&gt;his knights&lt;/a&gt;.\n This being said, they are derived from the research of its founder &lt;a href=\"Seath%20the%20Scaleless\"&gt;Seath&lt;/a&gt;, an albino &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt; without scales, who sided with the &lt;a href=\"Lords\"&gt;Lords&lt;/a&gt; when they waged their war on dragon-kind. To aid them in killing the semi-mortal beings, Seath pillaged the Primordial Crystal, which granted him true immortality. \nWelcomed warmly into the newly established royalty, Seath became a Duke, and was permitted to keep the Crystal. He retreated into the &lt;a href=\"The%20Duke%27s%20Archives\"&gt;Archives&lt;/a&gt;, the library castle granted to him along with dukedom, to research the nature of his treasure and discover some other way to achieve immortality without scales. In his research, which drove him at least partially blind\u00a0and mad, he developed powerful arts using the energy extracted from the crystal. This would inspire the crystal sorceries.\n Despite his madness and the people he experimented on, Seath's work inspired many scholars, who derived soul sorceries from his study of souls.\u00a0Rather he continued searching for immortality, and eventually succeeded in connecting the Primordial Crystal with his own life force, becoming a \"true undead\" in that he could not be killed.\nSoon schools like &lt;a href=\"Vinheim\"&gt;Vinheim&lt;/a&gt;'s Dragon School were established, expanding on the work of Seath, and developing new sorceries, from clever sound manipulation, to the generation of powerful blasts of soul energy, often called magic. Meanwhile, in the land of &lt;a href=\"Oolacile\"&gt;Oolacile&lt;/a&gt;, their xanthous scholars developed sorceries that manipulated light energy, known as golden sorceries. During the disaster that consumed Oolacile in the &lt;a href=\"Chasm%20of%20the%20Abyss\"&gt;Abyss&lt;/a&gt;, some of the scholars were driven mad by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dark\"&gt;the Dark&lt;/a&gt; and realized the nature of &lt;a href=\"Humanity%20%28item%29\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt;, developing the first dark sorceries seen in modern times.\n At some point, the famous sorcerer \"Big Hat\" &lt;a href=\"Big%20Hat%20Logan\"&gt;Logan&lt;/a&gt; left the Dragon School, and came across the Archives, where he studied the innovations of Seath. Though his starting attempts were imitations and not as powerful, and sometimes seemed close to the Dark, he eventually succeeded in creating crystal medium to facilitate a stronger bond between souls and sorceries, honing it into piercing solid energy, which would become the world's first crystal sorceries. He even create a imitation spell of Seath's curse-laced crystalline White Dragon Breath, although the mental strain of developing such magic dislodged Logan's anchor for reason, driving him mad like his predecessor.\nTwo schools would evolve from the fundamental work of Logan. One was located within the court of the &lt;a href=\"Profaned%20Capital\"&gt;Profaned Capital&lt;/a&gt;, whose sorcerers also functioned as oracles, and emulated Logan using &lt;a href=\"Court%20Sorcerer%27s%20Staff\"&gt;copies of his staff&lt;/a&gt;. They also, through means unknown, recovered &lt;a href=\"Logan%27s%20Scroll\"&gt;a scroll written by Logan himself&lt;/a&gt;, containing the sorceries he made in his early days before gaining access to the Archives, and used it to assert themselves as heirs to the sorcerer. This school did not last long, as a certain oracle's &lt;a href=\"Monstrosity%20of%20Sin\"&gt;relatives&lt;/a&gt; triggered a curse called the Profaned Flame, which mutated the sorcerers responsible and burning the capital to the ground.\n While the oracles were somewhat unscrupulous in their claim, one other school made good on that very same assertion. This school was started by two preacher twins, who were said to be Logan's true spiritual successors, so that they were known to others as the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Sage\"&gt;Crystal Sage&lt;/a&gt;s. They were masters of the crystal magic, and eventually served as spiritual guides for the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives%20Scholar\"&gt;sorcerer scholars&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Archives\"&gt;Grand Archives&lt;/a&gt; in the kingdom of &lt;a href=\"Lothric\"&gt;Lothric&lt;/a&gt;. In a pact of uncertain terms, one of the twins traveled to &lt;a href=\"Farron%20Keep\"&gt;Farron&lt;/a&gt; and taught sorceries to the acolytes of the &lt;a href=\"Abyss%20Watchers\"&gt;Undead Legion&lt;/a&gt;, developed as simplifications to slower, less agile spells, due to the Legion's emphasis on speed over power.\nWhile this happened the other twin stayed with the scholars of Lothric, and like their predecessor - and the \"Paledrake\" Seath that they honored religiously - they came across &lt;a href=\"Clawed%20Curse\"&gt;destructive knowledge that threatened to pull away their reason&lt;/a&gt;, often causing the reader to &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;suddenly die and crystallize their soul&lt;/a&gt;. Those scholars would cake themselves in an \"ivory wax\" that protected themselves from this danger. Eventually both twins would go mad, just as Logan and Seath did, and the king of Lothric, &lt;a href=\"Oceiros\"&gt;Oceiros&lt;/a&gt;, would task the scholars with assisting him with creating the perfect heir. His search for Seath's moonlight not only drove him mad like the other scholars preceding him, but it turned him into an abomination somewhat similar in biology and magical nature to Seath, and he was dethroned and kept in the &lt;a href=\"Consumed%20King%27s%20Garden\"&gt;palace garden&lt;/a&gt;, coddling his &lt;a href=\"Ocelotte\"&gt;nonexistent son&lt;/a&gt;, protecting his life with his own.\nGeneral information.\nSorceries are a discipline tied to logic, and for this reason, one must be intelligent enough to cast them. With more intellectual development, one can increase the power of their sorcery. Most sorceries are channeled through a &lt;a href=\"catalyst\"&gt;catalyst&lt;/a&gt;, so named for its ability to quickly direct magic, and some also have natural sorcery altering properties. While the most common catalysts are some form of staff, there are other tools that can act as a catalyst for casting sorceries.\nIn the three games, most sorceries focus on dealing magic elemental\u00a0damage in some form, such as simple arrows to torrential blasts of soul energy. Others provide augmentations to equipment and to oneself, to make combat easier, or simply avoid combat altogether. Sorceries which provide that function mentioned last are usually golden.\nVariations.\nMost of the modern day sorceries are derived from the soul, and the soul they come from is essential to what kind of sorcery it will be classified as. Common sorceries, such as those taught by the Dragon School, are mainly drawn from the manipulation of common souls. Through a complex process of crystallization, this energy can be honed further and become solid magic with properties of both magic and solid items, at which point they are crystal sorceries. While trying to replicate the magic of Seath into an art usable by &lt;a href=\"humans\"&gt;humans&lt;/a&gt;, Logan developed powerful sorceries unique in their strength and nature, but their homing properties are more closely related to the Dark than to the crystal magic of Seath.\nIn Oolacile, the sorceries were designed to manipulate light, and have functions that none have been able to fully replicate. While sorcery has both offensive and defensive applications, golden sorceries are utilized to completely avoid dangerous situations, whether by lighting the path, concealing oneself as some inconspicuous item, or negating the physicality of magical energies to dispel harmful spells or slow them down. Whether they all happened to be designed like this, or if light is naturally passive like this, is not made certain.\n Some magics are derived from humanity, which is fragmented from a soul, and dark sorceries can be made. Magic of this type are both magical and physical, striking targets with weighty force, and having a natural harmfulness to living things. It is thought that the Dark is highly responsive to emotion, and is drawn towards emotional beings, which allows such magic to tenaciously pursue living things. Just as those who love and hate are undauntingly drawn to the object that they love or hate, humans are able to give this emotion to a portion of their disembodied humanity, which will follow that directive and cause harmful raw Dark to give chase to a target.\n Three forgotten sorceries exist as well. Frost sorceries manipulate the cold of Painted Worlds, and seem to be well known to the sorcerers who inhabit a painted world, where they imbue their weapons with it. They are unfortunately developed only in the painted worlds, and those who have not experienced any true loss, such as those born there naturally, do not share the affinity to the cold as others do, and almost never use them after exiting a painted world. For example, the frost sorcerer &lt;a href=\"Pontiff%20Sulyvahn\"&gt;Sulyvahn&lt;/a&gt; forsook some of his arts when he left the &lt;a href=\"Painted%20World%20of%20Ariandel\"&gt;Painted World of Ariandel&lt;/a&gt;, but used others to enchant the weapons of &lt;a href=\"Irithyll%20of%20the%20Boreal%20Valley\"&gt;Irithyll&lt;/a&gt; and coat &lt;a href=\"Anor%20Londo%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Anor Londo&lt;/a&gt; in the unnatural winter climate.\nThe other, truly lost art is flame sorcery, founded by the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Witch of Izalith&lt;/a&gt;. With her family dead or mutated, the daughter &lt;a href=\"Quelana%20of%20Izalith\"&gt;Quelana&lt;/a&gt; developed a flame manipulation art that she taught to a &lt;a href=\"Salaman%20the%20Master%20Pyromancer\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;, becoming the inventor of &lt;a href=\"pyromancy\"&gt;pyromancy&lt;/a&gt; and leaving behind a lasting legacy for ages to come.\nLast is an art called moon sorcery, practiced by Gwyndolin, the god of the Darkmoon. How this art works is not explained, but it allowed Gwyndolin to launch blasts of light blue energy, and is a matter of faith."}
{"id": "90823", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=90823", "title": "Sorcery Clutch Ring", "text": "The Sorcery Clutch Ring is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nEffects.\nThe Sorcery Clutch Ring increases the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; AR (attack rating) stat of a &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; and decreases the player's defense stats for &lt;a href=\"Strike\"&gt;Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Thrust\"&gt;Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Slash\"&gt;Slash&lt;/a&gt; by 80 points each. The following are the rules for the highly variable AR stat increases provided by the ring:"}
{"id": "129129", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=129129", "title": "SotFS", "text": ""}
{"id": "2891", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2891", "title": "Soul", "text": " Souls are the universal currency of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\". They are used to &lt;a href=\"level%20up\"&gt;level up&lt;/a&gt;, purchase &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Modification\"&gt;upgrade&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;ascend weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Modification\"&gt;enhance armor&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"repair%20equipment\"&gt;repair equipment&lt;/a&gt;.\nSouls are dropped upon &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;, but can be retrieved from the player's &lt;a href=\"bloodstain\"&gt;bloodstain&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0They are lost permanently if a\u00a0player dies again before reaching their bloodstain.\nGathering souls.\nSouls are gained by doing the following:\n1. Slaying &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt;\n2. Feeding items to &lt;a href=\"Kingseeker%20Frampt\"&gt;Kingseeker Frampt&lt;/a&gt;\n3. Consuming &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; that give souls\nSouls from enemies.\nAlmost all enemies drop souls. How many are dropped depends on the enemy type, the current difficulty level (the higher the &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt;, the more souls), and whether or not the player overkilled the opponent (dealing more than 150% of an enemy\u2019s total HP in one hit).\nOverkilling enemies grants around 20% more souls per kill. It is possible to further boost the amount of souls gained from killing enemies by wearing the &lt;a href=\"Symbol%20of%20Avarice\"&gt;Symbol of Avarice&lt;/a&gt; and/or the &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Silver%20Serpent%20Ring\"&gt;Covetous Silver Serpent Ring&lt;/a&gt;. The maximum percentage of souls attainable is 172.8% per kill."}
