{"id": "52342", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52342", "title": "Soul Appease", "text": "Soul Appease is a &lt;a href=\"Miracle%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;miracle&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nWhen cast, Soul Appease releases a yellow ring around the caster, dealing damage within a large &lt;a href=\"area-of-effect\"&gt;area-of-effect&lt;/a&gt;. It can hit through walls and deals considerable damage, but only to specific enemies. However, its area of effect is vaguely dome-shaped, meaning that while it is capable of hitting enemies above the caster, if an enemy is on an even slightly lower level than them it will miss them altogether.\nAlthough situational, Soul Appease is an effective way of clearing mobs of enemies affected by it. However, the fickle nature of what the spell considers &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; can make it difficult to tell when the spell can be used.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "44260", "revid": "3146905", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44260", "title": "Soul Arrow", "text": ""}
{"id": "4491", "revid": "357117", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4491", "title": "Soul Arrow (Dark Souls)", "text": "Soul Arrow (\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u306e\u77e2) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nFires a weakly homing projectile at one's target after locking on, inflicting &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28damage%20type%29\"&gt;Magic Damage&lt;/a&gt;. The arrow has a magic attack power of 1.1 times the catalyst's magic adjust.\nSoul Arrow is a highly efficient and accessible utility sorcery that can be used to augment many builds. With 30 uses per copy and a fast casting time, it is extremely flexible and can be used against any target. In addition to being a staple early-game spell for Sorcerers, Soul Arrow can provide ranged auxiliary firepower for any build, since even at low Intelligence levels it has a higher total damage per attunement slot than most Pyromancies.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "31122", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31122", "title": "Soul Arrow (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Soul Arrow is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nUnleashes a small bolt of magic. The bolt travels a long distance, and slightly homes in on its target. However, it can easily be dodged by strafing, meaning that agile enemies can easily dodge it.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones"}
