{"id": "104352", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=104352", "title": "Soul Memory", "text": "Soul Memory\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Stats_%28Dark_Souls_II%29\"&gt;character stat&lt;/a&gt; in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\" that equals the total number &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; acquired by that character. Soul Memory increases whenever the character gains souls, but does not decrease when the character spends or loses souls. The character's current Soul Memory is displayed in the upper right hand corner of the Player Status menu.\nEffect.\nSoul Memory is primarily used during &lt;a href=\"Matchmaking%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;online matchmaking&lt;/a&gt; to determine which characters can connect for &lt;a href=\"Cooperative%20Gameplay%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;co-op&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Player%20versus%20Player%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;. The only other known use of Soul Memory is opening the door of the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Winter\"&gt;Shrine of Winter&lt;/a&gt; which requires increasing Soul Memory by one million or more during a single playthrough (and an additional million per subsequent &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;New Game+&lt;/a&gt; cycle.)"}
{"id": "31124", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31124", "title": "Soul Shower", "text": "Soul Shower is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nA large blue orb is sent into the sky, raining down multiple &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Soul Arrows&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Area%20of%20effect\"&gt;area&lt;/a&gt; beneath it. \nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones:"}
{"id": "161062", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=161062", "title": "Soul Spear", "text": ""}
{"id": "136220", "revid": "357132", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=136220", "title": "Soul Spear (Dark Souls)", "text": "Soul Spear (\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u306e\u69cd) is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;Sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nLaunches a very powerful magical missile. It is much larger than the Soul Arrow variants. Casting time is relatively fast, essentially equivalent to a standard Soul Arrow cast, and the projectile moves quickly. Soul Spears can pierce through enemies and deal damage to multiple targets in a straight line until they eventually hit the ground. It has a magic attack power of 3.0 times the catalyst's magic adjust.\nDescription.\n&lt;tabber&gt;Official translation=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "31123", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31123", "title": "Soul Spear (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Soul Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nIdentical to its \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\" predecessor; when cast, a large and long projectile is released. Soul Spear is capable of piecing through several enemies before dispersing, making it very useful for crowd control. It also has a relatively quick cast &lt;a href=\"time\"&gt;time&lt;/a&gt;, similar to that of &lt;a href=\"Great%20Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Great Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;. However, it requires a large amount of &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Stamina&lt;/a&gt; to cast. Likewise, this also means blocking a Soul Spear consumes large portions of Stamina as well.\nAttunement milestones.\nLike all other spells, the amount of casts per slot increases upon reaching certain &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Attunement&lt;/a&gt; milestones,"}
{"id": "134030", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134030", "title": "Soul Spear (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Soul Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;sorcery&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nSold by &lt;a href=\"Orbeck%20of%20Vinheim\"&gt;Orbeck of Vinheim&lt;/a&gt; for 5,000 &lt;a href=\"Soul%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; once he has been given &lt;a href=\"Logan%27s%20Scroll\"&gt;Logan's Scroll&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffect.\nFires a soul spear at the target, dealing 2.5 times the &lt;a href=\"Catalysts%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;catalyst's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Buff\"&gt;Spell Buff&lt;/a&gt; as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; damage. The spear has a relatively short &lt;a href=\"cast%20time\"&gt;cast time&lt;/a&gt; and high travel speed, being capable of penetrating its target and hitting multiple foes at once if they are standing close together.\nUse.\nThis spell's usefulness comes from its moderate cast speed, long range, moderate projectile size, impressive travel speed and ability to pierce multiple foes. The individual projectile does not deal appreciably more damage than &lt;a href=\"Great%20Heavy%20Soul%20Arrow%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Great Heavy Soul Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, relative to its greatly increased &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; cost. Due to these characteristics, Soul Spear is best used for bombarding closely-grouped foes at long range, rather than for inflicting significant damage on a single foe.\nAlongside &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Soul%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Crystal Soul Spear&lt;/a&gt;, this spell has the longest range among all Sorceries.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
