{"id": "3007", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3007", "title": "Soul of a Lost Undead", "text": "The Soul of a Lost Undead is a consumable &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt; item in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nSoul items are not lost upon &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;, so it is useful to keep some in case players lose their &lt;a href=\"bloodstain\"&gt;bloodstain&lt;/a&gt; but need some &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s for &lt;a href=\"leveling%20up\"&gt;leveling up&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"repair\"&gt;repair&lt;/a&gt;s.\nSouls of Lost Undead can be fed to &lt;a href=\"Kingseeker%20Frampt\"&gt;Kingseeker Frampt&lt;/a&gt; for 500 souls, which is more than they would give if consumed (200), so it's a good idea to save them up until he is encountered.\nLocations.\nSouls of a Lost Undead are commonly found off corpses in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Burg\"&gt;Undead Burg&lt;/a&gt; and earlier areas, gradually becoming rarer as the game progresses.\n&lt;a href=\"Infested%20Ghoul\"&gt;Infested Ghoul&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Blighttown\"&gt;Blighttown&lt;/a&gt; also drop them semi-commonly."}
