{"id": "64718", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=64718", "title": "Southern Ritual Band", "text": "The Southern Ritual Band is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in\" &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nEffect.\nThe Southern Ritual Band increases the amount of &lt;a href=\"Attunement%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;attunement&lt;/a&gt; slots a player can have. One for the basic, two for the +1, three for the +2.\nAvailability.\nThe basic version can be found past the &lt;a href=\"Belfry%20Gargoyles%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Belfry Gargoyles&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Belfry%20Luna\"&gt;Belfry Luna&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe +1 variant can be found in a chest in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Brightstone%20Cove%20Tseldora\"&gt;Brightstone Cove Tseldora&lt;/a&gt;. From the bonfire after the chapel go along the path, until you find a zipline. Go down the zipline, and into the nearby house. Once through, drop down onto a ledge where a &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Mage\"&gt;Hollow Mage&lt;/a&gt; is. There is a house you must enter, and pulling a lever will lower the chest where the ring is hidden.\nThe +2 variant can be obtained by defeating &lt;a href=\"Scorpioness%20Najka\"&gt;Scorpioness Najka&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"New%20Game%20Plus%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;NG+&lt;/a&gt;."}
