{"id": "5028", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5028", "title": "Spear", "text": "The Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Spears\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\u00a0\nCharacteristics.\nThe Spear is the most basic spear-type &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. A good starting weapon for new players as it allows attacking while still keeping a &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; up. However, its short range means it is easily outclassed by other spear-type weapons. It is also prone to consuming &lt;a href=\"stamina\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; quickly early game if you use it too aggressively, so it's better used as a strategic poke and defend weapon.\nUpgrades.\nScaling Percentage Values.\nThe following chart lists the scaling percentages when this weapon is fully upgraded. Be advised that:"}
{"id": "57313", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57313", "title": "Spear (Dark Souls II)", "text": "The Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nMay be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Lenigrast\"&gt;Blacksmith Lenigrast&lt;/a&gt; for 1,400 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics.\nThough most players typically favor its winged &lt;a href=\"Winged%20Spear%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;counterpart&lt;/a&gt;, the Spear itself is actually a viable weapon in the hands of the capable. Like most other &lt;a href=\"Thrust%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;thrusting&lt;/a&gt; weapons, players can attack enemies with this spear from behind their &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, allowing for a safer approach in narrow spaces. Players should be cautious on attacking in this fashion for prolonged conflicts, as more &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; is consumed than usual with each attack (as well as the reduced stamina regeneration when one is blocking), which could make one more prone to having their &lt;a href=\"guard%20broken\"&gt;guard broken&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnusual for a weapon of this &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Types%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt;, it does not only thrust damage, but &lt;a href=\"Strike%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;strike&lt;/a&gt; damage with its first strong attack (1-handed and 2-handed), making it a very versatile spear. This is especially useful in the earlier parts of the game, as most enemies, especially &lt;a href=\"Old%20Ironclad%20Soldier\"&gt;heavily-armored&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Pursuer\"&gt;ones&lt;/a&gt;, are vulnerable to strike damage.\nHowever, the main drawback of the Spear is its incredibly-fast &lt;a href=\"degradation\"&gt;degradation&lt;/a&gt; in combat, especially if one is fighting armored foes, making it paramount for one to watch the durability of the weapon to ensure it does not break prior to reaching a bonfire. Having &lt;a href=\"Repair%20Powder%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;repair powder&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Repair%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;other means&lt;/a&gt; of repairing equipment or &lt;a href=\"Bracing%20Knuckle%20Ring\"&gt;preserving&lt;/a&gt; durability, can help mitigate this."}
{"id": "134046", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=134046", "title": "Spear (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Spear is a &lt;a href=\"Spears%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nThe Spear is an accessible &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; thanks to its low stat requirements and &lt;a href=\"weight\"&gt;weight&lt;/a&gt;. This coupled with its low &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; usage, compared to other spears, makes it an excellent early-game weapon. The low stamina usage also lets it excel when attacking from behind a &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, as the saved stamina can instead be used to maintain one's guard. Furthermore, it also means the Spear has the potential to kill enemies in fewer combos than heavier spears.\nThese strengths come at the cost of the spear being considerably shorter than other spears found near the start of the game. It also has a less versatile &lt;a href=\"moveset\"&gt;moveset&lt;/a&gt; than the &lt;a href=\"Partizan%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Partizan&lt;/a&gt;.\nContrary to what its low weight, stamina usage, and requirements may imply, the Spear's damage is similar to that of other early spears, its primary drawback being its low reach.\nUpgrades.\nReinforced with standard &lt;a href=\"Titanite%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Titanite&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe red tassel at the end of the spear's shaft exhibits cloth physics, similar to capes and robes. It also receives the same singed effect as armor when the wielder is a &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3178", "revid": "56333033", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3178", "title": "Spears", "text": "Spears are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls\"&gt;Dark Souls&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOverview.\nSpears are precise, long-reach weapons that predominantly use &lt;a href=\"thrust\"&gt;thrust&lt;/a&gt;ing attacks. The extra range that spears provide often allows wielders to attack foes before they are within range with their own weapons; in exchange, spears deal unremarkable damage and have poor &lt;a href=\"stagger\"&gt;stagger&lt;/a&gt; capabilities. Like &lt;a href=\"Thrusting%20Swords\"&gt;Thrusting Swords&lt;/a&gt;, spears have a very small and narrow hit radius, making them difficult to use against fast-moving opponents unless when used in a confined area. Another shared trait with the thrusting swords are the spears' ability to attack while simultaneously guarding with a &lt;a href=\"shield\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;. For their range and strength, Spears are also very fast, so they can be effective for interrupting enemy attacks. Given their strong defensive capabilities but poor damage, spears are a slow, but relatively safe, choice when it comes to taking down enemies. Spears do not do well against a shield. They glance off the shield and do not stagger shielded enemies as easily as other weapon attack types.\nSpears.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nDetailed=\nCondensed=\nUpgraded=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "52293", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52293", "title": "Spears (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Spears are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". They are defined by their long range and swift attack speed. They are the quintessential weapons that are used attacking in long and narrow hallways, where strafing would prove to be difficult. They can be used whilst behind the cover of a &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;, but extra care should be taken, as it demands copious of &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; to use. If all is depleted and the shield is struck, the player will be &lt;a href=\"guard%20broken\"&gt;guard broken&lt;/a&gt;, leaving them vulnerable to &lt;a href=\"riposte\"&gt;riposte&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "131635", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131635", "title": "Spears (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Spears are a type of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are characterized by their long range and fast attack speed. Spears are ideal for attacking in long hallways where the enemies will have a difficult time strafing. They can also be used to attack while guarding with a &lt;a href=\"Shields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;. Care should be taken by the player to watch their &lt;a href=\"Stamina%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;stamina&lt;/a&gt; closely when attacking behind a shield, as if the player's stamina is depleted and their shield is struck, they will be &lt;a href=\"guard%20broken\"&gt;guard broken&lt;/a&gt; and vulnerable to a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;riposte&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpears.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "150296", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150296", "title": "Spears of the Church", "text": "The Spears of the Church is a &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is introduced in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\" DLC.\nRequirements.\nThe player must have defeated &lt;a href=\"Darkeater%20Midir\"&gt;Darkeater Midir&lt;/a&gt; and acquired the &lt;a href=\"Spears%20of%20the%20Church%20%28item%29\"&gt;Spears of the Church&lt;/a&gt; covenant item.\nHow to join.\nThe player must simply equip the &lt;a href=\"Spears%20of%20the%20Church%20%28item%29\"&gt;Spears of the Church&lt;/a&gt; covenant item.\nBenefits.\nWhile a Spear of the Church, the player can be automatically summoned to another player's world to be a &lt;a href=\"Halflight%2C%20Spear%20of%20the%20Church\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;. While summoned as a boss, the player will be able to use the &lt;a href=\"Ritual%20Spear%20Fragment\"&gt;Ritual Spear Fragment&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Spear%20Fragment\"&gt;Divine Spear Fragment&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnlike other covenants, a Spear of the Church may be summoned in to combat a lone player who is not a &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt;, making this covenant the only one with such a mechanic in \"Dark Souls III\"."}
{"id": "150298", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150298", "title": "Spears of the Church (item)", "text": "The Spears of the Church is a &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nObtained after defeating &lt;a href=\"Darkeater%20Midir\"&gt;Darkeater Midir&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nEquip to pledge oneself to the &lt;a href=\"Spears%20of%20the%20Church\"&gt;Spears of the Church&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;covenant&lt;/a&gt; to be summoned to another players world as a boss."}
