{"id": "136557", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=136557", "title": "Merchant (Dark Souls III)", "text": "Merchants are &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;characters&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\" that trade in various goods, such as &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;.\nSome merchants are available from the start of the game, while others must be located throughout the world and brought back to &lt;a href=\"Firelink%20Shrine%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Firelink Shrine&lt;/a&gt;, with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Unbreakable%20Patches\"&gt;Patches&lt;/a&gt;, who may sell items once discovered in the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20the%20Deep\"&gt;Cathedral of the Deep&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnlike the previous games, all merchants (with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Ludleth%20of%20Courland\"&gt;Ludleth of Courland&lt;/a&gt;) are capable of selling and buying items and equipment.\nMerchants will increase their stock of sold goods once specific requirements are met."}
{"id": "31935", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31935", "title": "Merchant Hag Melentia", "text": "Merchant Hag Melentia is a &lt;a href=\"Merchants%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;merchant&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\". She is voiced by .\nLocation.\nFound in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Fallen%20Giants\"&gt;Forest of Fallen Giants&lt;/a&gt;, next to the &lt;a href=\"Cardinal%20Tower\"&gt;Cardinal Tower&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bonfire%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;bonfire&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter exhausting all of her dialogue and defeating &lt;a href=\"The%20Last%20Giant\"&gt;The Last Giant&lt;/a&gt; boss, she moves to &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt;, and settles on the left of the bonfire next to the wall.\nPlot.\nShe sells various wares to the player including pieces of &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Sorcery%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;sorceries&lt;/a&gt;. She will also sell the armor sets and weapons of certain &lt;a href=\"Characters%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;characters&lt;/a&gt; if the player has killed them. If the player speaks to her, she provides some information about &lt;a href=\"Drangleic\"&gt;Drangleic&lt;/a&gt;'s backstory. Melentia also sells &lt;a href=\"Lenigrast%27s%20Key\"&gt;Lenigrast's Key&lt;/a&gt;, which opens &lt;a href=\"Blacksmith%20Lenigrast\"&gt;Blacksmith Lenigrast's&lt;/a&gt; workshop in &lt;a href=\"Majula\"&gt;Majula&lt;/a&gt;, allowing the player to use his smithing services.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Silver%20Serpent%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Covetous Silver Serpent Ring&lt;/a&gt; +1 can be gifted to the player by spending 10,000 &lt;a href=\"Souls%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;souls&lt;/a&gt; in her shop and exhausting her dialogue.\nIt costs 4,000 souls to revive her.\nLore.\nThe traveling merchant Melentia is one of the few Drangleic survivors. She is always seen carrying her wares on her back. Melentia also seems to be slowly losing her mind.\nStrategy.\nWhen she becomes hostile, she can inflict &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"buildup\"&gt;buildup&lt;/a&gt;, instantly turning the player &lt;a href=\"Hollow\"&gt;Hollow&lt;/a&gt; if the meter should fill."}
