{"id": "172713", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172713", "title": "Miscellaneous Items", "text": ""}
{"id": "69766", "revid": "33084951", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=69766", "title": "Miscellaneous Items (Dark Souls II)", "text": "Miscellaneous Items are a type of &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20II\"&gt;Dark Souls II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral information.\nMiscellaneous items are anything that are found under the &lt;a href=\"Estus%20Flask%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;Estus Flask&lt;/a&gt; menu within the player's inventory. Up to ten can be assigned to belt slots for quick utilization. Miscellaneous items include, but are not limited to, &lt;a href=\"Restorative%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;restorative items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;offensive items&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Online%20Play%20Items%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;online play items&lt;/a&gt;.\nRestorative items.\nRestorative items are used to restore the player's &lt;a href=\"humanity\"&gt;humanity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stats%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;stats&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Equipment%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt;. They can also be used to mitigate damage.\nOffensive items.\nOffensive items include projectiles that inflict damage to &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; from afar, items that are used to boost damage inflicted, or items that otherwise affect enemies in a negative way.\nOther items.\nItems that do not fit into any subcategory are listed here.\nOnline play items.\nOnline play items are used to interact with other players while online and serve no practical purpose while offline.\nCovenant items.\nCovenant items are those that are required to join certain &lt;a href=\"Covenant%20%28Dark%20Souls%20II%29\"&gt;covenants&lt;/a&gt;, or are used to gain covenant ranks."}
