{"id": "130791", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=130791", "title": "Miyazaki Hidetaka", "text": ""}
{"id": "140390", "revid": "317106", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140390", "title": "Moan", "text": "Moan is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen activated, the wielder will raise the shield and offer a prayer to it. This animation takes roughly 2.5 seconds, and gives block frames for the duration of the prayer. Upon completion, the player will be buffed with an effect similar to an &lt;a href=\"Alluring%20Skull%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Alluring Skull&lt;/a&gt;, which will attract the attention of enemies which enter close proximity to the wielder for 30 seconds. This buff is independent of the shield being wielded, and cannot be extended by equipping the &lt;a href=\"Lingering%20Dragoncrest%20Ring%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lingering Dragoncrest Ring&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsage.\nSingle player.\nBecause it requires &lt;a href=\"Focus%20Points\"&gt;FP&lt;/a&gt; in order to use, this skill can be difficult to utilize, especially as the associated equipment requires copious amounts of &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield.\nOnline gameplay.\nThis skill's primary use is to attract and keep the attention of foes in co-operative gameplay, as the shield can provide powerful defense against their attacks."}
{"id": "150143", "revid": "40093575", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=150143", "title": "Moaning Knight", "text": "The Moaning Knight is an &lt;a href=\"Enemies%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;enemy&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"The%20Ringed%20City\"&gt;The Ringed City&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nA &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Spirit%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;dark spirit&lt;/a&gt; clad in &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Set\"&gt;Morne's Set&lt;/a&gt;. Comes armed with &lt;a href=\"Morne%27s%20Great%20Hammer\"&gt;Morne's Great Hammer&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Moaning%20Shield\"&gt;Moaning Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\n&lt;a href=\"Ringed%20City%20Streets\"&gt;Ringed City Streets&lt;/a&gt;, in the grave tower after escaping &lt;a href=\"Darkeater%20Midir\"&gt;Darkeater Midir&lt;/a&gt;'s ambush in the gorge. After dropping down to the lower section of the tower, the Moaning Knight will appear in one of the burial chambers near the connecting staircase. The player does not need &lt;a href=\"Host%20of%20Embers\"&gt;Host of Embers&lt;/a&gt; status for him to appear here.\nStrategy.\nThere are several &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Skeletons&lt;/a&gt; near the location where the Moaning Knight invades so it is recommended to eliminate them quickly to avoid becoming surrounded. The narrow confines of the area can make fighting the knight difficult, although the player can flee past to the upper level, where there is more space to fight.\nThe Knight is an aggressive fighter, although they have low vitality and can be easily staggered. As the tower has no barriers, they can be knocked off the ledge and may even fall off when attempting to evade an attack."}
{"id": "133511", "revid": "49243392", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=133511", "title": "Moaning Shield", "text": "The Moaning Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Greatshields%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;greatshield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAvailability.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Eygon%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Eygon of Carim&lt;/a&gt;, or found on his corpse inside of &lt;a href=\"Irina%20of%20Carim\"&gt;Irina of Carim&lt;/a&gt;'s cell in the &lt;a href=\"Undead%20Settlement\"&gt;Undead Settlement&lt;/a&gt; after completing her questline.\nCharacteristics.\nThe Moaning Shield is a very unique greatshield, with notably high &lt;a href=\"Magic%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; resistances. While heavy, it boasts extremely high &lt;a href=\"stability\"&gt;stability&lt;/a&gt;, being beat only by the &lt;a href=\"Greatshield%20of%20Glory%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Greatshield of Glory&lt;/a&gt;, while still being lighter than &lt;a href=\"Havel%27s%20Greatshield%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Havel's Greatshield&lt;/a&gt;. However, requiring 50 &lt;a href=\"Strength%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield, it has the highest strength requirement of any greatshield.\nThe Moaning Shield's &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Moan\"&gt;Moan&lt;/a&gt;, is unique in that it will cause the woman's face on the shield to emit a low moan, attracting nearby enemies. This can be useful when helping other players as a &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;phantom&lt;/a&gt;, as it allows one to draw the attention of enemies away from the host for various purposes."}
{"id": "177106", "revid": "35416778", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=177106", "title": "Molotov Cocktail (Dark Souls III)", "text": "The Molotov Cocktail is an which was &lt;a href=\"Removed%20Content%20%28Dark%20Souls%20III%29\"&gt;removed&lt;/a&gt; from the final release of \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "173442", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=173442", "title": "Molten Giant", "text": ""}
{"id": "140215", "revid": "5134030", "url": "https://darksouls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=140215", "title": "Molten Perseverance", "text": "Molten Perseverance is a &lt;a href=\"skill\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Souls%20III\"&gt;Dark Souls III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nWhen activated, the wielder anchors the weapon in the ground and gains temporary &lt;a href=\"Hyper%20Armor\"&gt;Hyper Armor&lt;/a&gt; while taking reduced damage, like normal &lt;a href=\"Perseverance\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt;. Following it up with a strong attack makes the player slam the hammer into the floor two more times, creating an explosion each time while leaving a lava pool around the wielder.\nUsage.\nSingle Player.\nThe explosions created by the strong attack of this skill can be useful for eliminating groups of enemies that the weapon's vertical moveset is ill-equipped to deal with. \nThe lava pools and fireballs can inflict hits multiple times a second, dealing extreme poise damage. This can be used to great effect against enemies such as &lt;a href=\"Sulyvahn%27s%20Beast\"&gt;Sulyvahn's Beasts&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Great%20Crab\"&gt;Great Crabs&lt;/a&gt;. \nOnline.\nThis skill grants the wielder a larger degree of flexibility than most great hammers. Simply activating the skill can give the wielder a standard Perseverance, useful for trading against opponents with large weapons. The strong attack may be handy for surprising players that are still willing to trade with the weapon, or for area denial when participating in co-op."}
